def: "Abnormal increase in diastolic blood pressure." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypovolemia
def: "An decrease in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Left-to-right shunt
def: "Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from the left side of the heart to the right." [HPO:mhaendel]

name: Bidirectional shunt
def: "Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from both right side of the heart to the left and vice versa." [HPO:mhaendel]

name: Right-to-left shunt
def: "Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from the right side of the heart to the left." [HPO:mhaendel]

name: Facial erythema
def: "Redness of the skin of the face, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perioral erythema
def: "Erythema (Redness of the skin caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin) localized to the region surrounding the mouth." []

name: Palmoplantar erythema
def: "Redness of the skin of the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin." []

name: Perianal erythema
def: "Erythema (Redness of the skin caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin) localized to the region surrounding the anus." []

name: Erythema migrans
def: "An expanding erythematous (red) skin lesion, usually round or oval, by definition at least 5 cm in size (in largest diameter)." [PMID:18452799]

name: Darier's sign
def: "A skin change elicited by briskly rubbing the skin lesion in urticaria pigmentosa (UP), whereby the area begins to itch and becomes raised and surrounded by erythema. Unlike other forms of dermatographism, Darier's sign refers to urtication that is limited to the UP involved areas and, as in this case, spares the skin unaffected by UP." [PMID:24701633]

name: Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum
def: "Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum (ACD) is typically characterized by innumerable small red to black papules which occur in clusters and are situated symmetrically in the bathing trunks area. The number of lesions and the extension of the body increase steadily with time so that generalization and mucosal involvement are common. The single lesion begins with a minute reddish papule which enlarges to up to 10 mm in diameter, becomes dark red to black with a discrete keratotic overgrowth. Histologically, the papules are characterized by superficial dilated capillaries in papillary dermis with epidermal proliferation." []

name: Diffuse telangiectasia
def: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) with a diffuse localization." [HPO:curators]

name: Livedo racemosa
def: "Livedo racemosa describes a reddish-blue mottling of the skin in an irregular, reticular pattern. It differs from the more common livedo reticularis by its shape. Livedo racemosa consists of broken circular segments resulting in a seemingly larger pattern, as opposed to the fine, regular, complete network of livedo reticularis. Livedo racemosa results from permanent impairment of peripheral blood flow and, unlike livedo reticularis, it persists on warming." [PMID:26500860, PMID:31753828]

name: Livedo reticularis
def: "Livedo reticularis is characterized by the presence of a bluish purple, mottled or netlike pattern in unbroken circles on the skin. Exposure to cold environments usually intensifies the vascular pattern. Presumably, the condition results from slow or stagnant blood flow, vessel-wall pathology, and decreased oxygen tension." []

name: Retinal capillary hemangioma
def: "A benign vascular tumor of the retina without any neoplastic characteristics." [HPO:probinson]

name: Choroidal hemangioma
def: "The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the choroid. These are generally reddish or orange or can have increased pigmentation maiking them difficult to distinguish from choroidal melanomas." [HPO:probinson]

name: Arachnoid hemangiomatosis
def: "The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the arachnoid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hemangioma of the lip
def: "A vascular malformation located in the lip that is related to vascular endothelial cell hyperplasia." [PMID:26618117]

name: Increased urinary copper concentration
def: "An increased concentration of copper in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Renal calcium wasting
def: "High urine calcium in the presence of hypocalcemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypocalciuria
def: "An abnormally decreased calcium concentration in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypernatriuria
def: "An increased concentration of sodium(1+) in the urine." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Renal sodium wasting
def: "An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the urine in the presence of hyponatremia." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Renal phosphate wasting
def: "High urine phosphate in the presence of hypophosphatemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperphosphaturia
def: "An increased excretion of phosphates in the urine." [HPO:curators]

name: Hypophosphaturia
def: "An abnormally decreased phosphate concentration in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Renal magnesium wasting
def: "High urine magnesium in the presence of hypomagnesemia." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Hypermagnesiuria
def: "An increased concentration of magnesium the urine." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Renal potassium wasting
def: "High urine potassium in the presence of hypokalemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased urinary potassium
def: "A decreased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased urinary potassium
def: "An increased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperchloriduria
def: "An increased concentration of chloride in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lacticaciduria
def: "An increased concentration of lactic acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypercitraturia
def: "A greater than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypocitraturia
def: "A lower than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased level of galactitol in urine
def: "An increase in the level of galactitol in the urine." [PMID:11092512, PMID:7671965]

name: Increased level of ribitol in urine
def: "An increase in the level of ribitol in the urine. Ribotol is a crystalline pentose alcohol (C5H12O5) and is a metabolic end product formed by the reduction of ribose." [PMID:14988808, PMID:26054712]

name: Increased level of L-fucose in urine
def: "An increase in the level of L-fucose in the urine." [PMID:2311216]

name: Increased urinary glycerol
def: "An increased concentration of glycerol in the urine." []

name: Increased level of ribose in urine
def: "An increase in the level of ribose in the urine." [PMID:14988808]

name: Increased level of xylitol in urine
def: "An increase in the level of xylitol in the urine." [PMID:14988808]

name: Galactosuria
def: "Elevated concentration of galactose in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased level of D-threitol in urine
def: "An increase in the level of D-threitol in the urine." [PMID:14988808]

name: Decreased level of erythritol in urine
def: "A decrease in the level of erythritol in the urine." [PMID:14988808]

name: Beta 2-microglobulinuria
def: "Increased level of beta 2-microglobulins in the urine." []

name: Decreased urinary sulfate
def: "Decreased concentration of sulfate in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperuricosuria
def: "An abnormally high level of uric acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased urinary urate
def: "Decreased concentration of urate in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased urinary O-linked sialopeptides
def: "Excretion of peptides conjugated to sialic acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aspartylglucosaminuria
def: "Excretion of excess amounts of aspartylglucosamine in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Exercise-induced myoglobinuria
def: "Presence of myoglobin in the urine following exercise." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent myoglobinuria
def: "Recurring episodes of myoglobinuria, i.e., of the presence of myoglobin in the urine. This is usually a consequence of rhabdomyolysis, i.e., of the destruction of muscle tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bicarbonaturia
def: "Abnormally increased concentration of hydrogencarbonate in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased urinary type 1 collagen N-terminal telopeptide level
def: "An increased concentration of type 1 collagen N-terminal telopeptide (NTx) level in the urine. Generally the test is performed over a period of time, for instance, 10 cc of morning urine can be collected following 12 hours overnight fasting or for 24 hours." [PMID:30572827]

name: Increased urine deoxypyridinoline level
def: "An increased level of deoxypyridinoline in the urine. Deoxypyridinoline is a crosslink product of collagen molecules found in bone and excreted in urine during bone degradation, has been described as a marker of bone turnover." [PMID:12661898, PMID:9127470]

name: Generalized aminoaciduria
def: "An increased concentration of all types of amino acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
def: "A lower than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
def: "A greater than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased urine harderoporphyrin level
def: "Increased amount of harderoporphyrin in the urine." [PMID:31085196]

name: Elevated urinary prostaglandin E2 level
def: "An increased amount of prostaglandin E2 in the urine." [PMID:24838973]

name: Oroticaciduria
def: "An increased concentration of orotic acid in the urine." [HPO:gcarlotti]

name: 3-Methylglutaconic aciduria
def: "An increased amount of 3-methylglutaconic acid in the urine." []

name: Increased level of hippuric acid in urine
def: "An increase in the level of hippuric acid in the urine." [PMID:19551947, PMID:22626821]

name: 3-Methylglutaric aciduria
def: "An abnormally increased level of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in the urine." [PMID:19177531]

name: Elevated urine acetoacetic acid level
def: "Elevated amount of acetoacetic acid in the urine." [PMID:11344564]

name: Microscopic hematuria
def: "Microscopic hematuria detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Macroscopic hematuria
def: "Hematuria that is visible upon inspection of the urine." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Red urine
def: "An abnormal red color of the urine." []

name: Red-brown urine
def: "An abnormal red-brown color of the urine." []

name: Pink urine
def: "An abnormal pink color of urine." []

name: Dark urine
def: "An abnormal dark color of the urine." []

name: Green urine
def: "An abnormal green color of urine." [PMID:28413291]

name: Purple urine
def: "An abnormal purple color of the urine." []

name: Low levels of vitamin A
def: "A reduced concentration of vitamin A." []

name: Low levels of vitamin K
def: "A reduced concentration of vitamin K." []

name: Low serum calcitriol
def: "A reduced concentration of calcitriol in the blood. Calcitriol is also known as 1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol or 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3." [HPO:probinson]

name: Low levels of vitamin D
def: "A reduced concentration of Vitamin D." []

name: Decreased circulating calcifediol concentration
def: "A reduced concentration of calcifediol in the blood. Calcifediol is also known as calcidiol, 25-hydroxycholecalciferol and 25-Hydroxyvitamin D3." [HPO:probinson]

name: High serum calcitriol
def: "An increased concentration of calcitriol in the blood. Calcitriol is also known as 1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol or 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3." [PMID:24246681, RGD:sjwang]

name: Low levels of vitamin E
def: "A reduced concentration of vitamin E in the blood circulation. Vitamin E is a lipophilic vitamin that is also known as alpha-tocopherol." [PMID:30559825]

name: Low levels of vitamin B2
def: "A reduced concentration of vitamin B2." []

name: Low levels of vitamin B1
def: "A reduced concentration of vitamin B1." []

name: Increased blood urea nitrogen
def: "An increased amount of nitrogen in the form of urea in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Reduced blood urea nitrogen
def: "An abnormally low concentration of urea nitrogen in the blood." []

name: Elevated circulating creatinine concentration
def: "An increased amount of creatinine in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Hyperuricemia
def: "An abnormally high level of uric acid in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypouricemia
def: "An abnormally low level of uric acid in the blood." [HPO:curators]

name: Decreased serum creatinine
def: "An abnormally reduced amount of creatinine in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elevated plasma pyrophosphate
def: "An abnormally increased diphosphate(4-) concentration in the blood. Diphosphate(4-), as ester with two phosphate groups, is also known as pyrophosphate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperphosphatemia
def: "An abnormally increased phosphate concentration in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Hypochloremia
def: "An abnormally decreased chloride concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperchloremia
def: "An abnormally increased chloride concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased serum pyruvate
def: "An increased concentration of pyruvate in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Hypotriglyceridemia
def: "An decrease in the level of triglycerides in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypocholesterolemia
def: "An decreased concentration of cholesterol in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Hypercholesterolemia
def: "An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Elevated 7-dehydrocholesterol
def: "Elevated 7-dehydrocholesterol levels." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased circulating very long-chain fatty acid concentration
def: "Increased concentation of very long-chain fatty acids in the blood circulation. Very long-chain fatty acids are fatty acids (FAs) with a chain-length of 22 or more carbons." [PMID:9345094]

name: Hypoamylasemia
def: "Decreased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands." []

name: Hyperamylasemia
def: "Increased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands." []

name: Reduced insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level in the blood circulation." []

name: Increased insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit concentration
def: "An abnormally elevated concentration of insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level in the blood circulation." []

name: Increased circulating beta-C-terminal telopeptide concentration
def: "A abnormal elevation above the normal concentration of beta-C-terminal telopeptide of type I collagen in the blood circulation." [RGD:sjwang]

name: Reduced circulating C-reactive protein concecntration
def: "An abnormal decrease of the C-reactive protein level in serum." [PMID:17852082, UCDenver:tjcallahan]

name: Reduced haptoglobin level
def: "An abnormally low concentration of haptoglobin in the blood circulation. Decreased haptoglobin in conjunction with increased reticulocyte count and anemia may indicate hemolysis. Decreased haptoglobin levels can also occur in the absence of hemolysis, due to cirrhosis of the liver, disseminated ovarian carcinomatosis, pulmonary sarcoidosis, and elevated estrogen state." [PMID:24809098]

name: Decreased circulating ceruloplasmin concentration
def: "Decreased concentration of ceruloplasmin in the blood." [HPO:probinson, PMID:32119309]

name: Decreased circulating ferritin concentration
def: "Abnormally reduced concentration of ferritin, a ubiquitous intracellular protein that stores iron, in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced C-peptide level
def: "A decreased concentration of C-peptide in the circulation. Since C-peptide is secreted in equimolar amounts to insulin, this feature correlates with reduced insulin secretion." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased C-peptide level
def: "An elevated concentration of C-peptide in the circulation. Since C-peptide is secreted in equimolar amounts to insulin, this feature correlates with increased insulin secretion." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoalbuminemia
def: "Reduction in the concentration of albumin in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased levels of alpha-fetoprotein
def: "A decrease in the concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation." []

name: Increased circulating brain natriuretic peptide concentration
def: "An increased concentration of brain natriuretic peptide in the blood circulation." [ORCID:0000-0002-4095-8489, PMID:16698841]

name: Increased circulating NT-proBNP concentration
def: "An elevated level of circulating N-terminal part of the prohormone of B-type natriuretic peptide (BNP)." []

name: Increased circulating thyroglobulin level
def: "An abnormal elevation of the concentration of thyroglobulin, a protein produced in the thyroid gland that acts as a precursor to thyrroid hormones." []

name: Elevated circulating methylsuccinic acid concentration
def: "Increased concentration of methylsuccinic acid in the blood circulation." [PMID:29909962]

name: Elevated circulating sebacic acid concentration
def: "Increased concentration of sebacic acid in the blood circulation." []

name: Elevated circulating alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde concentration
def: "Increased concentration of alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde in the blood circulation." [PMID:17560822]

name: Elevated circulating suberic acid concentration
def: "An increased concentration of suberic acid in the blood circulation. Suberic acid is an alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is the 1,6-dicarboxy derivative of hexane." []

name: Elevated circulating glutaric acid concentration
def: "An increased concentration of glutaric acid in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Elevated circulating biliverdin concentration
def: "Increased concentration of biliverdin, a green tetrapyrrolic bile pigment, in the blood circulation." [PMID:19580635]

name: Methylmalonic acidemia
def: "Increased concentration of methylmalonic acid in the blood." [HPO:probinson, PMID:26101005]

name: Elevated circulating fumarate concentration
def: "An increased concentration of fumarate, an intermediate in the citric acid cycle, in the blood circulation." [PMID:31290619]

name: Decreased serum bicarbonate concentration
def: "An abnormal reduction of the concentration of bicarbonate, HCO3[-], in the circulation." []

name: Elevated serum anion gap
def: "An abnormally high value of the serum anion gap (the sum of serum chloride and bicarbonate concentrations subtracted from the serum sodium concentration)." [PMID:17699401]

name: Respiratory alkalosis
def: "Alkalosis due to excess loss of carbon dioxide from the body." [HPO:probinson]

name: Gluten intolerance
def: "A detrimental reaction to the presence of gluten in food, which may include abdominal pain, fatigue, headaches and paresthesia, or celiac disease." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia
def: "An increased concentration of insulin combined with a decreased concentration of glucose in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fasting hyperinsulinemia
def: "An increased concentration of insulin in the blood in the fasting state, i.e., not as the response to food intake." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intermittent hypothermia
def: "Episodes of reduced body termperature." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperpyrexia
def: "An extreme elevation of core body temperature above normal defined as a rectal temperature of 41.1 degrees Celsius (106 degrees Fahrenheit)." [HPO:nvasilevsky, PMID:16818546]

name: Unexplained fevers
def: "Episodes of fever for which no infectious cause can be identified." [HPO:curators]

name: Low-grade fever
def: "Mild fever that does not exceed 38.5 degrees centigrade." [HPO:probinson]

name: Persistent fever
def: "Fever that persists longer than expected for an acute infectious disease. No precise threshold exists, and the clinical interpretation of fever is context-dependent, but as a rule of thumb, this term refers to fever that persists longer than 2-3 weeks." [PMID:14677667]

name: Tongue edema
def: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling in the tongue." []

name: Edema of the dorsum of hands
def: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin on the back of the hands." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased nuchal translucency
def: "Nuchal translucency is the sonographic appearance of subcutaneous accumulation of liquid in the back of the fetal neck in the first trimester of pregnancy (11-14 gestational weeks of pregnancy)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12751779, PMID:15846173, PMID:28511453]

name: Cerebral edema
def: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid in the brain." [HPO:probinson]

name: Peripheral edema
def: "An abnormal accumulation of interstitial fluid in the soft tissues of the limbs." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pharyngeal edema
def: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid leading to swelling of the pharynx." [HPO:probinson]

name: Laryngeal edema
def: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling in the tissues of the larynx." [HPO:probinson]

name: Corneal stromal edema
def: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling of the stroma of cornea." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoproteinemic edema
def: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body because of decreased osmotic pressure of plasma (hypoproteinemia)." [HPO:curators]

name: Genital edema
def: "A buildup of fluid that causes swelling in the soft tissues of the genital area." []

name: Low neutrophil alkaline phosphatase
def: "An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase in neutrophils, which could be due to absence of enzyme or the production of defective enzyme." [PMID:46759]

name: Elevated leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
def: "Increased alkaline phosphatase measured within leukocytes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased beta-galactosidase activity
def: "Abnormally decreased rate of beta-galactosidase activity. Beta-galactosidase activity can be measured in leukocyte, fibroblast, or plasma." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Chromosomal breakage induced by crosslinking agents
def: "Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with DNA cross-linking agents such as diepoxybutane and mitomycin C." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Chromosomal breakage induced by ionizing radiation
def: "Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with ionizing radiation." [HPO:sdoelken, PMID:16814619]

name: Folate-dependent fragile site at Xq28
def: "The presence of a folate sensitive fragile site at chromosome Xq28." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal B cell proliferation
def: "Any abnormality in the multiplication or reproduction of B cells, which results in the expansion of a cell population." []

name: Mitochondrial depletion
def: "An abnormal reduction in mitochondrial DNA content of cells." [PMID:23385875]

name: Electron transfer flavoprotein-ubiquinone oxidoreductase defect
def: "A deficiency of the electron transfer flavoprotein-ubiquinone oxidoreductase." [PMID:2989828]

name: Deficiency or absence of cytochrome b(-245)
Decreased activity of the pyruvate dehydrogenase complex
Intraaxonal accumulation of curvilinear autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
def: "Curvilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material within axons." [HPO:probinson]

name: Impaired memory B cell generation
def: "Impaired production of memory cells, the B cells that persist for years or an entire lifetime and which confer rapid and enhanced response to secondary challenge." [HPO:probinson]

name: Impaired Ig class switch recombination
def: "An impairment of the class-switch recombination process that normally leads B lymphocytes to produce IgG, IgA, or IgE." [HPO:probinson, PMID:11544001]

name: Lack of T cell function
def: "Complete inability of T cells to perform their functions in cell-mediated immunity." []

name: Reduced natural killer cell activity
def: "Reduced ability of the natural killer cell to function in the adaptive immune response." [HPO:probinson]

name: Persistent CMV viremia
def: "Lasting (uncontrolled) presence of cytomegalovirus in the blood circulation." [PMID:28130404]

name: Persistent EBV viremia
def: "Persistent presence of Epstein-Barr virus in the blood." []

name: Decreased muscle glycogen content
def: "A decreased amount of glycogen in muscle tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased intramyocellular lipid droplets
def: "An abnormal increase in intracellular lipid droplets In a muscle. The number and size of these drops can increase with somd disorders of lipid metabolism affecting muscle. See PMID 20691590 for histological images." [HPO:probinson, PMID:20691590]

name: Elevated circulating globotriaosylceramide concentration
def: "Increased concentration of globotriaosylceramide (Gb3) in the blood circulation. Globotriaosylceramide, also named ceramidetrihexoside, is the primary lipid storage in Fabry disease." [PMID:17073606]

name: Reduced granulocyte CD59 level
def: "Reduced level of CD59 on the granulocyte surface as assessed by flow cytometry." []

name: Short telomere length
def: "An abnormal reduction in telomere length. Telomeres are non-coding, repetitive sequences of DNA at the ends of the chromosomes of eukaryotic cells which become shorter as cells divide, and when telomere attrition reaches its limit, cell proliferation arrest, senescence, and apoptosis can occur." []

name: Thin zona pellucida
def: "Reduced thickness of the zona pellucida." [PMID:7657763]

name: White eyelashes
def: "White color (lack of pigmentation) of the eyelashes." [DDD:cmoss]

name: White eyebrow
def: "White color (lack of pigmentation) of the eyebrow." [HPO:probinson]

name: Medial flaring of the eyebrow
def: "An abnormal distribution of eyebrow hair growth in the medial direction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Synophrys
def: "Meeting of the medial eyebrows in the midline." [PMID:19125427]

name: Thick eyebrow
def: "Increased density/number and/or increased diameter of eyebrow hairs." [PMID:19125427]

name: Horizontal eyebrow
def: "An eyebrow that extends straight across the brow, without curve." [PMID:19125427]

name: Abnormal location of the eyebrow
def: "Anomalous anatomical placement of the eyebrow." []

name: Highly arched eyebrow
def: "Increased height of the central portion of the eyebrow, forming a crescent, semicircular, or inverted U shape." [PMID:19125427]

name: Laterally extended eyebrow
def: "An eyebrow that extends laterally beyond the orbital rim rather than turning gently downward at that location." [PMID:19125427]

name: Long eyebrows
def: "Increased length of the hairs of the eyebrows." [HPO:probinson]

name: Uncombable hair
def: "Hair that is disorderly, stands out from the scalp, and cannot be combed flat." []

name: Dry hair
def: "Hair that lacks the lustre (shine or gleam) of normal hair." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Fine hair
def: "Hair that is fine or thin to the touch." [HPO:probinson]

name: Coarse hair
def: "Hair shafts are rough in texture." [HPO:probinson]

name: Loss of eyelashes
def: "This term refers to the loss of eyelashes that were previously present." [HPO:probinson]

name: Prominent eyelashes
def: "Eyelashes that draw the attention of the viewer due to increased density and/or length and/or curl without meeting the criteria of trichomegaly." [PMID:19125427]

name: Curly eyelashes
def: "Abnormally curly or curved eyelashes." [HPO:curators]

name: Trichiasis
def: "Inversion and rubbing of the eyelashes against the globe of the eye." [HPO:curators]

name: Slow-growing scalp hair
def: "Scalp hair whose growth is slower than normal." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Thick hair
def: "Increased density of hairs, i.e., and elevated number of hairs per unit area." [HPO:probinson]

name: Atrichia
def: "The most dramatic and severe form of hair loss characterized by an absence of hair follicles." [PMID:14676077]

name: Trichorrhexis nodosa
def: "Trichorrhexis nodosa is the formation of nodes along the hair shaft through which breakage readily occurs. It is thus a focal defect in the hair fiber that is characterized by thickening or weak points (nodes) that cause the hair to break off easily. The result is defective, abnormally fragile hair." [HPO:curators]

name: Pili canaliculi
def: "Uncombable hair." [HPO:probinson]

name: Tiger tail banding
def: "An abnormal appearance of hair under polarizing microscopy (using crossed polarizers), whereby hair shafts show striking alternating bright and dark bands, often referred to as tiger tail banding." [PMID:15692466]

name: Pili torti
def: "Pili (from Latin pilus, hair) torti (from Latin tortus, twisted) refers to short and brittle hairs that appear flattened and twisted when viewed through a microscope." [HPO:probinson]

name: Trichoschisis
def: "Transverse fractures through the hair shafts (trichoschisis). Trichoschisis is characterized by a sharp transverse fracture of the hair shaft." [PMID:23180925]

name: Hair shafts flattened at irregular intervals and twisted through 180 degrees about their axes
Axillary apocrine gland hypoplasia
def: "Developmental hypoplasia of the apocrine sweat glands in the region of the axilla." [HPO:probinson]

name: Periungual erythema
def: "Erythema (redness of the skin caused by hyperemia in superficial capillaries) in the region surrounding a fingernail or toe nail." []

name: Paronychia
def: "The nail disease paronychia is an often-tender bacterial or fungal hand infection or foot infection where the nail and skin meet at the side or the base of a finger or toenail. The infection can start suddenly (acute paronychia) or gradually (chronic paronychia)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Subungual hyperkeratosis
def: "A thickening of the stratum corneum in the region beneath the nails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Subungual fibromas
def: "The presence of fibromata beneath finger or toenails." [HPO:curators]

name: Melanonychia
def: "Brown or black discoloration of the nails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Leukonychia
def: "White discoloration of the nails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Yellow nails
def: "Yellowish discoloration of the nails." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Slow-growing nails
def: "Nails whose growth is slower than normal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short nail
def: "Decreased length of nail." [PMID:19125433]

name: Thin fingernail
def: "Fingernail that appears thin when viewed on end." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Fingernail dysplasia
def: "An abnormality of the development of the fingernails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dystrophic fingernails
def: "The presence of misshapen or partially destroyed nail plates, often with accumulation of soft, yellow keratin between the dystrophic nail plate and nail bed, resulting in elevation of the nail plate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ridged fingernail
def: "Longitudinal, linear prominences in the fingernail plate." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Narrow nail
def: "Decreased width of nail." [PMID:19125433]

name: Trachyonychia
def: "Excessive longitudinal ridging that gives the surface of the nail plate a rough appearance. It results from multiple foci of defective keratinization of the proximal nail matrix." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22016269, PMID:26273150]

name: Split nail
def: "A nail plate that has a longitudinal separation and the two sections of the nail share the same lateral radius of curvature." [PMID:19125433]

name: Broad nail
def: "Increased width of nail." [HPO:probinson]

name: Toenail dysplasia
def: "An abnormality of the development of the toenails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nail pits
def: "Small (typically about 1 mm or less in size) depressions on the dorsal nail surface." [PMID:19125433]

name: Ridged nail
def: "Longitudinal, linear prominences in the nail plate." [PMID:19125433]

name: Deep-set nails
def: "Deeply placed nails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Concave nail
def: "The natural longitudinal (posterodistal) convex arch is not present or is inverted." [PMID:19125433]

name: Thin toenail
def: "Toenail that appears thin when viewed on end." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Malalignment of the great toenail
def: "A lateral deviation of the nail plate of the great toe along the longitudinal axis due to the lateral rotation of the nail matrix. The nail plate grows out in ridges." [PMID:27171597]

name: Upslanting toenail
def: "Upturned concavity of toenails." []

name: Dystrophic toenail
def: "Toenail changes apart from changes of the color of the toenail (nail dyschromia) that involve partial or complete disruption of the various keratinous layers of the nail plate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Onychogryposis of toenails
def: "Thickened toenails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Onychauxis
def: "Thickened nails without deformity." [HPO:probinson]

name: Onychogryposis of fingernail
def: "Thickened fingernails." []

name: Beau's lines
def: "A nail dystrophy that is preseents as grooved lines that run from side to side on the fingernail or the toenail that may look like indentations or ridges on the nail plate. They are caused by temporary disruption in the growth of proximal nail matrix. Trauma is usually the initiating factor such as infections, severe medical illnesses, major surgery/anesthesia, medication side effects, and autoimmune disease." [ISBN:0-07-138076-0, PMID:26475537, PMID:29593008, PMID:32900765]

name: Recurrent loss of toenails and fingernails
def: "Repeated loss, or shedding, of the nails of the fingers and toes." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Onychomadesis
def: "Complete shedding (separation) of the nail from the proximal matrix. Onychomadesis is the proximal separation of the nail plate from the nail matrix due to a temporary cessation of nail growth." [PMID:24882996, PMID:25473242, PMID:28207011]

name: Episodic hyperhidrosis
def: "Intermittent episodes of abnormally increased perspiration." [HPO:probinson]

name: Palmoplantar hypohidrosis
def: "Decreased sweating on the palms and soles." [PMID:24664640]

name: Decreased sweating due to autonomic dysfunction
Linear IgG deposits along the epidermal basement membrane zone
def: "Presence of IgG antibodies in the dermoepidermal junction that are distributed in a linear pattern. This feature can be appreciated by immunofluorescence microscopy." [PMID:24160488]

name: Poor wound healing
def: "A reduced ability to heal cutaneous wounds." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chronic cutaneous wound
def: "A cutaneous wound that has failed to proceed through the orderly and timely process to produce an atomic and functional integrity, or proceeded through the repair process without establishing a sustained anatomic and functional result." [PMID:8166487]

name: Periorbital hyperpigmentation
def: "Increased pigmentation of the skin in the region surrounding the orbit of the eye." [HPO:probinson]

name: Milia
def: "Presence of multiple small cysts containing keratin (skin protein) and presenting as tiny pearly-white bumps just under the surface of the skin." [HPO:probinson]

name: Skin detachment
def: "Loss of sections of skin either spontaneously or after gentle handling." [PMID:27656858, RGD:gthayman]

name: Molluscoid pseudotumors
def: "Bluish-grey, spongy nodules associated with scars over pressure points and easily traumatized areas like the elbows and knees." [HPO:probinson]

name: Skin erosion
def: "A discontinuity of the skin exhibiting incomplete loss of the epidermis, a lesion that is moist, circumscribed, and usually depressed." [HPO:skoehler]

name: Skin fissure
def: "A clearly-defined and roughly linear cleavage in the skin that usually extends to the dermis." []

name: Annular cutaneous lesion
def: "A lesion of the skin with a ring-like distribution." []

name: Lichenoid skin lesion
def: "Mutliple skin lesions resembling those characteristic of the disease lichen planus. These lesions are violaceous (reddish-purple), shiny, isolated, flat-topped papules and plaques." [PMID:22356325]

name: Caseous vernix-like desquamation
def: "Vernix caseosa is a physiological, viscous biofilm that is produced by desquamated fetal skin and sebaceous glands covering the fetus at the third trimester in-utero. The substance's gross morphology in post-partum is described by the etymology, as vernix means varnish, and caseosa means cheesy-like matter. This finding refers to an abnormally thick and greasy vernix caseosa-like scale present at birth." [PMID:21856041]

name: Absent lanugo
def: "Lack of development of lanugo, the fine, soft, unpigmented hair on the body of a fetus or newborn baby." [PMID:26119818, PMID:30252348]

name: Desquamation of skin soon after birth
Knuckle pad
def: "Knuckle pads are benign fibrofatty subcutaneous pads located over the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joints that can be mistaken for arthritis. Rarely they affect the dorsal aspect of the metacarpophalangeal (MCP) joints. Clinically they are painless and often affect both hands in an asymmetrical pattern." [PMID:26672439]

name: Pretibial myxedema
def: "A diffuse, non-pitting edema and thickening of the skin usually on the anterior aspect of the lower legs spreading to the dorsum of the feet." [HPO:skoehler]

name: Fragmented elastic fibers in the dermis
def: "Elastic fibers in the dermis exhibit an increased number of breaks associated with disorganization of the structure of the elastic fibers." []

name: Civatte bodies
def: "Eosinophilic hyaline ovoid bodies which are often found in the subepidermal papillary regions or sometimes in the epidermis. Civatte bodies (CBs) are seen as rounded, homogenous, eosinophilic masses on routine H and E staining lying in the deeper parts of epidermis/epithelium and more frequently in dermis/connective tissue. They are known as CBs (in epithelium/epidermis), colloid bodies, or hyaline bodies (in connective tissue). They are 10-25 micrometers in diameter and situated mostly within or above the inflammatory cell infiltrate. In lichen planus, the number of necrotic keratinocytes may be so large that they are seen lying in clusters in the uppermost dermis. These bodies show a positive periodic acid Schiff reaction and are diastase resistant" [PMID:23919028]

name: Acantholysis
def: "The loss of intercellular connections, such as desmosomes, resulting in loss of cohesion between keratinocytes." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Anemic pallor
def: "A type of pallor that is secondary to the presence of anemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sclerodactyly
def: "Localized thickening and tightness of the skin of the fingers or toes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Erythema nodosum
def: "An erythematous eruption commonly associated with drug reactions or infection and characterized by inflammatory nodules that are usually tender, multiple, and bilateral." [HPO:probinson]

name: Psoriasiform dermatitis
def: "A skin abnormality characterized by redness and irritation, with thick, red skin that displays flaky, silver-white patches (scales)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perifolliculitis
def: "Inflammation surrounding hair follicles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Erysipelas
def: "Increased susceptibility to erysipelas, as manifested by a medical history of repeated episodes of erysipelas, which is a superficial infection of the skin, typically involving the lymphatic system." [HPO:probinson]

name: Superficial dermal perivascular inflammatory infiltrate
def: "Numerous lymphocytes surrounding blood vessels in the superfical part of the dermis." []

name: Chilblains
def: "Chilblains, also called perniosis, are an inflammatory skin condition related to an abnormal vascular response to the cold. We are unaware of a reliable estimate of incidence. It typically presents as tender, pruritic red or bluish lesions located symmetrically on the dorsal aspect of the fingers, toes, ears and nose. Less commonly, reports describe involvement of the thighs and buttocks. The lesions present hours after exposure to cold and usually resolve spontaneously in one to three weeks." [HPO:probinson, PMID:1832531, PMID:22025653]

name: Pruritus on foot
def: "Pruritus is an itch or a sensation that makes a person want to scratch. This term refers to an abnormally increased sensation of itching over the skin of the foot." []

name: Choroid plexus papilloma
def: "Choroid plexus papilloma is a histologically benign neoplasm located in the ventricular system of the choroid plexus." [HPO:skoehler]

name: Oropharyngeal squamous cell carcinoma
def: "A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the oropharnyx." [HPO:probinson]

name: Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin
def: "Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin is a malignant tumor of squamous epithelium." [HPO:curators]

name: Occasional neurofibromas
def: "Neurofibromas present in a smaller number than usually seen in neurofibromatosis type 1." [HPO:curators]

name: Subcutaneous neurofibromas
def: "The presence of Neurofibromas in the subcutis." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Plexiform neurofibroma
def: "A neurofibroma in which Schwann cells proliferate inside the nerve sheath, producing an irregularly thickened, distorted, tortuous structure." [HPO:curators]

name: Acral lentiginous melanoma
def: "A type of cutaneous melanoma localized to the palm, sole, or beneath the nail (subungual melanoma). Acral lentiginous melanoma starts as a slowly-enlarging flat patch of discoloured skin and usually displays a size above 6 mm and often several centimetres or more in diameter upon diagnosis and variable pigmentation with a mixutre of colors including brown, and blue-grey, black and red. The surface of the lesion is initially smooth but later in the course may become thicker and irregular, and may ulcerate or bleed." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lentigo maligna melanoma
def: "A subtype of melanoma in situ that typically develops on sun-damaged skin. The lesion is typically a large, irregularly pigmented macule that has developed from an ordinary lentigo (a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly-defined edge). Change to a malignant lentigo typically takes place over 20 years or more, and many patients accept the change as a consequence of aging." [HPO:7734995, HPO:probinson]

name: Bilateral vocal cord paresis
def: "Decreased strength of the vocal fold on both sides." [HPO:probinson]

name: Unilateral vocal cord paresis
def: "Decreased strength of the vocal fold on one side." [HPO:probinson]

name: Volvulus
def: "Abnormal twisting of a portion of intestine around itself or around a stalk of mesentery tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intestinal pseudo-obstruction
def: "A functional rather than mechanical obstruction of the intestines, associated with manifestations that resemble those caused by an intestinal obstruction, including distension, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, constipation or diarrhea, in an individual in whom a mechanical blockage has been excluded." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intestinal lymphangiectasia
def: "Angiectasia of lymph vessels (i.e., dilatation of lymphatic vessels) in the intestines." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ileal ulcer
def: "An erosion of the mucous membrane in a portion of the ileum." [PMID:28670609]

name: Duodenal ulcer
def: "An erosion of the mucous membrane in a portion of the duodenum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Esophageal ulceration
def: "Defect in the epithelium of the esophagus, essentially an open sore in the lining of the esophagus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Esophageal varix
def: "Extreme dilation of the submucusoal veins in the lower portion of the esophagus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Tracheoesophageal fistula
def: "An abnormal connection (fistula) between the esophagus and the trachea." [HPO:probinson]

name: Esophageal diverticulum
def: "The presence of a diverticulum of the esophagus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Spontaneous esophageal perforation
def: "The occurrence of the full-thickness tear (perforation) of the wall of the esophagus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Malposition of the stomach
def: "Abnormal anatomical location of the stomach. This feature may be due to intestinal malrotation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16465538]

name: Gastric diverticulum
def: "An outpouching of the gastric wall." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22257431]

name: Absence of intrinsic factor
def: "Absence of gastric intrinsic factor, which is normally produced by the parietal cells of the stomach, and is required for the absorption of vitamin B12." [HPO:probinson]

name: Gastric varix
def: "Extreme dilation of the submucusoal veins in the stomach." [HPO:probinson, PMID:24891929]

name: Colonic eosinophilia
def: "An excess of eosinophilic cells in colonic tissue, i.e., eosinophilic infiltration in the colon." [PMID:21922029]

name: Eosinophilic liver infiltration
def: "Cellular infiltration of the liver parenchyma with a preponderance of eosinophils." [HPO:probinson, PMID:20457690, PMID:7835024]

name: Eosinophilic infiltration of the esophagus
def: "Infiltration of numerous eosinophils (usually greater than 15 per high power field) into the squamous epithelium of the esophagus, and layering of eosinophils on the surface layer of the esophagus." [PMID:27158535]

name: Gastroesophageal reflux
def: "A condition in which the stomach contents leak backwards from the stomach into the esophagus through the lower esophageal sphincter." [HPO:probinson]

name: Esophageal spasms
def: "Involuntary contractions of the esophagus that are irregular, uncoordinated, and painful." []

name: Hematemesis
def: "The vomiting of blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hematochezia
def: "The passage of fresh (red) blood per anus, usually in or with stools. Most rectal bleeding comes from the colon, rectum, or anus." [DDD:hfirth]

name: Melena
def: "The passage of blackish, tarry feces associated with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Melena occurs if the blood remains in the colon long enough for it to be broken down by colonic bacteria. One degradation product, hematin, imbues the stool with a blackish color. Thus, melena generally occurs with bleeding from the upper gastrointestinal tract (e.g., stomach ulcers or duodenal ulcers), since the blood usually remains in the gut for a longer period of time than with lower gastrointestinal bleeding." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intestinal inflammation
def: "A reaction characterizeds by capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, pain, swelling localized to the in the intestinal tract." [PMID:9897960]

name: Crohn's disease
def: "A chronic granulomatous inflammatory disease of the intestines that may affect any part of the gastrointestinal tract from mouth to anus, causing a wide variety of symptoms. It primarily causes abdominal pain, diarrhea which may be bloody, vomiting, or weight loss, but may also cause complications outside of the gastrointestinal tract such as skin rashes, arthritis, inflammation of the eye, tiredness, and lack of concentration. Crohn's disease is thought to be an autoimmune disease, in which the body's immune system attacks the gastrointestinal tract, causing inflammation." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Frequent Giardia lamblia infestation
def: "Increased susceptibility to Giardia lamblia infection of the intestine, as manifested by a medical history of multiple episodes of Giardia lamblia intestinal infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent gastroenteritis
def: "Increased susceptibility to gastroenteritis, an infectious inflammationof the stomach and small intestines manifested by signs and symptoms such as diarheas and abdominal pain, as manifested by recurrent episodes of gastroenteritis." []

name: Helicobacter pylori infection
def: "A recurrent infection of the GI tract with helicobacter pylori, a gram-negative, microaerophilic bacterium usually found in the stomach." [PMID:23652324]

name: Neoplasm of the gallbladder
def: "The presence of a neoplasm of the gallbladder." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cholangiocarcinoma
def: "Cholangiocarcinoma is a primary cancer originating in the biliary epithelium i.e., the cholangiocytes, of the extrahepatic and intrahepatic biliary ducts. It is extremely invasive, develops rapidly, often metastasizes, and has a very poor prognosis. They are slow growing tumors which spread longitudinally along the bile ducts with neural, perineural and subepithelial extension." [HPO:probinson, PMID:18536057, PMID:8268770]

name: Fundic gland polyposis
def: "Multiple polyps in the acid-secreting mucosa of the gastric body and fundus. Fundic gland polyps (FGP) are usually 1 to 5 mm in size, though larger polyps have been found. FGPs are typically sessile, shiny, translucent, pale to pinkish in color (resembling the surrounding mucosa), and often exhibit tiny surface blood vessels. These polyps have characteristically been observed to chunk off or detach entirely at the base when removed with cold forceps, in contrast to other types of gastric polyps." [PMID:20567540]

name: Stomach cancer
def: "A cancer arising in any part of the stomach." [HPO:probinson]

name: Gastric adenocarcinoma
def: "An adenocarcinoma arising from the stomach glandular epithelium. Gastric carcinoma often produces no specific symptoms when it is superficial and potentially surgically curable, although up to 50% of patients may have nonspecific gastrointestinal complaints such as dyspepsia." [NCIT:C4004, PMID:15621988, PMID:28569272]

name: Hamartomatous stomach polyps
def: "Polyp-like protrusions which are histologically hamartomas located in the stomach." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anal margin squamous cell carcinoma
def: "A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the skin of the anal margin." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22379406]

name: Barrett esophagus
def: "An abnormal change (metaplasia) in the cells of the inferior portion of the esophagus. The normal squamous epithelium lining of the esophagus is replaced by metaplastic columnar epithelium. Columnar epithelium refers to a cell type that is typically found in more distal parts of the gastrointestinal system." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Esophageal carcinoma
def: "The presence of a carcinoma of the esophagus." [DDD:hfirth, NCIT:C3513]

name: Hepatocellular adenoma
def: "A benign tumor of the liver of presumably epithelial origin." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hepatic hemangioma
def: "A congenital vascular malformation in the liver composed of masses of blood vessels that are atypical or irregular in arrangement and size." [NCIT:C3869, PMID:21191518]

name: Hepatocellular carcinoma
def: "A kind of neoplasm of the liver that originates in hepatocytes and presents macroscopically as a soft and hemorrhagic tan mass in the liver." [HPO:probinson]

name: Partial abdominal muscle agenesis
def: "Failure to form of portions of the abdominal musculature." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the abdominal wall musculature
def: "Absence of the abdominal musculature." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the abdominal wall musculature
def: "Underdevelopment of the abdominal musculature." [HPO:probinson]

name: Protuberant abdomen
def: "A thrusting or bulging out of the abdomen." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nausea
def: "A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit." [HPO:probinson, PMID:26770271]

name: Chronic constipation
def: "Constipation for longer than three months with fewer than 3 bowel movements per week, straining, lumpy or hard stools, and a sensation of anorectal obstruction or incomplete defecation." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Dependency on parenteral nutrition
def: "Inability to ingest sufficient quantities of nutrition by mouth or by tube-feeding with the corresponding requirement for intravenous administration of nutrition." []

name: Intermittent diarrhea
def: "Repeated episodes of diarrhea separated by periods without diarrhea." []

name: Chronic diarrhea
def: "The presence of chronic diarrhea, which is usually taken to mean diarrhea that has persisted for over 4 weeks." [HPO:probinson]

name: Secretory diarrhea
def: "Watery voluminous diarrhea resulting from an imbalance between ion and water secretion and absorption." [HPO:probinson]

name: Mucoid diarrhea
def: "Passage of an increased number of stools containing mucus, a thick fluid substance secreted by mucous membranes." [PMID:31869107]

name: Hyperactive bowel sounds
def: "Abnormally increased gurgling/rumbling sounds made by the movement of fluid and gas in the intestines." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22767621]

name: Lack of bowel sounds
def: "Complete lack of abdominal sounds as assayed by examination of the abdomen with a stethoscope." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fluctuating splenomegaly
def: "Intermittently increased size of the spleen." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hepatosplenomegaly
def: "Simultaneous enlargement of the liver and spleen." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fluctuating hepatomegaly
def: "Intermittently increased size of the liver." [HPO:probinson]

name: Meconium peritonitis
def: "Peritonitis caused by intrauterine intestinal rupture and spillage of fetal meconium into the fetal peritoneal cavity. Intra-peritoneal meconium usually calcifies, sometimes within 24 hours. Ultrasound findings may include intraabdominal calcifications." [PMID:3317498, UToronto:chum]

name: Portal fibrosis
def: "Fibroblast proliferation and fiber expansion from the portal areas to the lobule." [HPO:probinson]

name: Portal inflammation
def: "Infiltration of portal fields by inflammatory cells." [PMID:16939061, PMID:19142989]

name: Malformation of the hepatic ductal plate
Hepatopulmonary fusion
def: "Fusion of the liver with the lung." [PMID:28196822]

name: Depletion of mitochondrial DNA in liver
def: "An abnormal reduction in the number of mitochondria in hepatocytes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nodular regenerative hyperplasia of liver
def: "Diffuse benign transformation of the hepatic parenchyma into small regenerative nodules with minimal or no fibrosis." [PMID:21472097]

name: Midline liver
def: "Position of the liver across the middle of the body instead of being in its normal position to the right of the stomach." [PMID:12432114]

name: Splenopancreatic fusion
def: "Fusion of the pancreatic tail and spleen." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:18398855]

name: Annular pancreas
def: "A congenital anomaly in which the pancreas completely (or sometimes incompletely) encircles the second portion of duodenum and occasionally obstructs the more proximal duodenum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nesidioblastosis
def: "An abnormality of pancreatic beta cells characterized by a proliferation of abnormal beta cells throughout the entire pancreas, with enlarged islet size and number (hypertrophic islets), increased periductular islets, enlarged beta-cell nuclei and abundant clear cytoplasm. Occasionally beta cells with pleomorphic nuclei, ductuloinsular complexes, and neoformation of islets from ducts are observed." [PMID:15517495, PMID:24645840]

name: Pancreatic cysts
def: "A cyst of the pancreas that possess a lining of mucous epithelium." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pancreatic pseudocyst
def: "Cyst-like space not lined by epithelium and contained within the pancreas. Pancreatic pseudocysts are often associated with pancreatitis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ectopia of the spleen
def: "An abnormal (non-anatomic) location of the spleen." [HPO:curators]

name: Splenic rupture
def: "A breach of the capsule of the spleen." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multilobulated spleen
def: "The fetal spleen is lobulated, and these lobules normally disappear before the birth. Lobulation of the spleen may persist into adult life and be typically seen along the medial part of the spleen. A persisting lobule results in a variation in shape of the spleen." [PMID:23710135]

name: Splenic cyst
def: "A closed sac located in the spleen." [HPO:probinson, PMID:24794024]

name: Splenic infarction
def: "Ischemia and necrosis of part or all of the spleen resulting from compromise of blood supply resulting from arterial or venous occlusion." [PMID:23281181, PMID:28613652]

name: Hypersplenism
def: "A malfunctioning of the spleen in which it prematurely destroys red blood cells." [HPO:probinson]

name: Epididymitis
def: "The presence of inflammation of the epididymis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Prostatitis
def: "The presence of inflammation of the prostate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Urinary bladder inflammation
def: "Inflammation of the urinary bladder." [HPO:probinson]

name: Smooth muscle antibody positivity
def: "The presence in serum of antibodies against smooth muscle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anti-glutamic acid decarboxylase antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against glutamic acid decarboxylase." [PMID:27356651]

name: Anti-thyroglobulin antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react to thyroglobulin." [ORCID:0000-0002-3387-1836, PMID:21196203, PMID:33144894, PMID:33999913, PMID:34634575]

name: Platelet antibody positive
def: "The presence in the serum of autoantibodies directed against thrombocytes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anti-liver cytosolic antigen type 1 antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a 60-kd peptide contained in the liver cytosolic fraction." [PMID:7806169]

name: Anti-citrullinated protein antibody positivity
def: "The presence autoantibodies in the serum that react do different citrullinated antigens, including filaggrin, fibrinogen, vimentin and collagen." [LMU:mgriese, PMID:21713412, PMID:27824549]

name: Anti-thyroid peroxidase antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against thyroid peroxidase." [ORCID:0000-0002-3387-1836, PMID:33144894, PMID:33796145]

name: Rheumatoid factor positive
def: "The presence in the serum of an autoantibody directed against the Fc portion of IgG." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lupus anticoagulant
def: "Presence of lupus anticoagulant (LA) autoantibodies. LA represent a heterogeneous group of autoantibodies, IgG, IgM, or a mixture of both classes, that interfere with standard phospholipid-based coagulant tests (this is only an in vitro phenomenon, LA do not cause reduction of coagulation in vivo). The antibodies are directed against plasma proteins which also bind to phospholipid surfaces." [PMID:27331311]

name: Anti-aquaporin 4 antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against aquaporin-4." [ORCID:0000-0002-3387-1836, PMID:24260168, PMID:24415568, PMID:25889963, PMID:31312230]

name: Antimitochondrial antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against mitochondria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Insulin receptor antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against the insulin receptor." [PMID:3280181]

name: Positive direct antiglobulin test
def: "A positive result of the direct antiglobulin test (DAT), a method of demonstrating the presence of antibody or complement bound to red blood cell (RBC) membranes by the use of anti-human globulin to form a visible agglutination reaction." [PMID:28134589]

name: Anti-thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against thyroid-stimulating hormone." [ORCID:0000-0002-3387-1836, PMID:10874533, PMID:26293122, PMID:3018097, PMID:30224035]

name: Drug allergy
def: "Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against drugs." []

name: Allergic rhinitis
def: "It is characterized by one or more symptoms including sneezing, itching, nasal congestion, and rhinorrhea." [PMID:11449200]

name: Decreased specific anti-polysaccharide antibody level
def: "The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against bacterial polysaccharides." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent specific antibody response
def: "Absence of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism." [PMID:17100769]

name: Decreased specific pneumococcal antibody level
def: "The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against pneumococci." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased circulating C1-esterase inhibitor concentration
def: "Decreased concentration of C1-esterase inhibitor (C1INH) in the blood circulation." [PMID:30844193]

name: Reduced hemolytic complement activity
def: "A diminished activity of the classical complement pathway as measured by the assay for 50% haemolytic complement (CH50) activity of serum." [PMID:20351687]

name: Post-vaccination measles
def: "Infection with the measles virus of the live-attenuated vaccine. This is an extremely rare event and may indicate immunocompromise in some cases." [PMID:29152266]

name: BCGosis
def: "Distant, or disseminated infection with Bacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination associated with failure to contain thebacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination leading to spread of BCG to many sites in the body. The tuberculosis vaccine BCG contains live attenuated Mycobacterium bovis." [PMID:21412596, PMID:24722620]

name: BCGitis
def: "Local or regional infection with Bacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination." [PMID:24722620]

name: Post-vaccination yellow fever
def: "Infection with the yellow fever virus of the live-attenuated vaccine." [PMID:31270247]

name: Post-vaccination polio
def: "Infection with live attenuated polio vaccine following vaccination. This is an extreemely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise." [PMID:25285130]

name: Severe toxoplasmosis
def: "Toxoplasmosis is a widespread parasitic infection that is frequently asymptomatic in immunocompetent patients. However, this obligate intracellular protozoan parasite can evade the immune system and persist for the life of its host in cyst form, predominantly in the brain, retina, and muscles. Reactivation of latent cysts may occur when the immune system fails to maintain cytokine pressure, which mainly relies on gamma interferon (IFN-gamma). Toxoplasmosis is a life-threatening infection in immunocompromised patients (ICPs)." [PMID:25762774]

name: Disseminated cryptosporidium infection
def: "Failure to contain infection by a protozoan of the genus Cryptosporidium, leading to spread to many parts of the body." []

name: Recurrent opportunistic infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to opportunistic infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection by opportunistic agents, i.e., by microorganisms that do not usually cause disease in a healthy host, but are able to infect a host with a compromised immune system." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chronic active Epstein-Barr virus infection
def: "Chronic active Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) infection is an uncommon outcome of EBV infection and may present as a waxing and waning or fulminant syndrome. Unlike acute infectious mononucleosis, wherein EBV establishes lifelong infection and survives by maintaining a delicate balance with the host as a latent infection, in chronic active EBV infection the host-virus balance is disturbed." []

name: Chronic tinea infection
def: "The term tinea means fungal infection, whereas dermatophyte refers to the fungal organisms that cause tinea. This term refers to a tinea infection that is chronic or recalcitrant to treatment and may be reflective of an immune defect." [PMID:25403034]

name: Recurrent infections in infancy and early childhood
def: "Recurrent infections at an early age with improvement in later childhood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent gingivitis
def: "Repeated occurrences of inflammatory condition of the gums (gingival tissue), most commonly caused by bacterial infection." [PMID:32491354]

name: Recurrent ear infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to ear infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of ear infections." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Recurrent otitis media
def: "Increased susceptibility to otitis media, as manifested by recurrent episodes of otitis media." [HPO:probinson]

name: Persistent human papillomavirus infection
def: "Human papillomaviruses (HPVs) are small oncogenic viruses. HPV has been shown to cause a variety of lesions and malignancies, which predominantly affect the anogenital region. Low-risk, non-oncogenic HPV types are associated with anogenital warts and recurrent respiratory papillomatosis while high-risk, oncogenic types are associated with cervical, penile, anal, vaginal, vulvar, and oropharyngeal cancers. Infection with anogenital HPV is usually asymptomatic and resolves spontaneously without consequences in the immunocompetent host. When disease does occur, the most common manifestation is genital warts, which may be small papules, or flat, smooth or pedunculated lesions. This resolution of HPV lesions is not generally seen in the immunosuppressed, resulting in severe, persistent and extensive manifestations of HPV disease." [PMID:24643184, PMID:26239127]

name: Defective production of NFKB1-dependent cytokines
def: "An impairment in the production by leukocytes of NFKB1-dependent cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interferon-alpha." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormality of tumor necrosis factor secretion
def: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of tumor necrosis factor." []

name: Severe combined immunodeficiency
def: "A type of primary immune deficiency that is characterized by a more severe defect in both the T- and B-lymphocyte systems." [HPO:curators]

name: Severe T-cell immunodeficiency
def: "A primary immune deficiency that is characterized by defects or deficiencies of T-lymphocytes that causes specific susceptibility to intracellular micro-organisms." [PMID:18755723]

name: Enlarged mesenteric lymph node
def: "Increase in size of one or more mesenteric lymph nodes." []

name: Chronic noninfectious lymphadenopathy
def: "A chronic form of lymphadenopathy that is not related to infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Generalized lymphadenopathy
def: "A generalized form of lymphadenopathy." [HPO:probinson]

name: Submandibular lymph node enlargement
def: "Increased size of the lymph nodes that are located beneath the mandible (lower jaw)." []

name: Follicular hyperplasia
def: "Lymphadenopathy (enlargement of lymph nodes) owing to hyperplasia of follicular (germinal) centers." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23281438]

name: Paratracheal lymphadenopathy
def: "Enlargement of lymph nodes surrounding the trachea." [PMID:4023240]

name: Cervical lymphadenopathy
def: "Enlarged lymph nodes in the neck." []

name: Recurrent cutaneous abscess formation
def: "An increased susceptibility to cutaneous abscess formation, as manifested by a medical history of recurrent cutaneous abscesses." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perianal abscess
def: "The presence of an abscess located around the anus." [HPO:curators]

name: Periapical tooth abscess
def: "A tooth abscess that occurs at the tip of the root (apex) of a tooth." []

name: Branchial cyst
def: "A branchial cyst is a remnant of embryonic development resulting from a failure of obliteration of a branchial cleft and consists of a subcutaneous cystic mass. Cysts are located anterior or posterior to the ear or in the submandibular region." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Branchial fistula
def: "A congenital fistula in the neck resulting from incomplete closure of a branchial cleft." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Fetal nuchal edema
def: "Nuchal edema is considered present in a fetus at gestational week 14 or more if in the midsagittal plane of the neck, there is subcutaneous edema that produces a characteristic tremor on ballotment of the fetal head. This constitutes the severe end of the spectrum of increased nuchal fold thickness, which is defined as soft-tissue thickening of 6 mm or more, seen in the suboccipitobregmatic view of the fetal head. Nuchal edema may be confined to the neck or it may be generalized, as part of hydrops fetalis." [PMID:16507941, PMID:9880279]

name: Thickened nuchal skin fold
def: "A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16100637, PMID:30431620]

name: Limited neck flexion
def: "Reduced abilty to lower the chin towards the chest by bending the neck." []

name: Nuchal rigidity
def: "Resistance of the extensor muscles of the neck to being bent forwards (i.e., impaired neck flexion) as a result of muscle spasm of the extensor muscles of the neck. Nuchal rigidity is not a fixed rigidity. Nuchal rigidity has been used as a bedside test for meningism, although its sensitivity for this purpose has been debated." [PMID:12060874]

name: Limited head rotation
def: "Reduced range of motion turning the head side to side." []

name: Stiff neck
def: "A sensation of tightness in the neck when attempting to move it, especially after a period of inactivity. Neck stiffness often involves soreness and difficulty moving the neck, especially when trying to turn the head to the side." []

name: Small sella turcica
def: "An abnormally small sella turcica." [HPO:curators]

name: Large sella turcica
def: "An abnormal enlargement of the sella turcica." [HPO:probinson]

name: Craniofacial asymmetry
def: "Asymmetry of the bones of the skull and the face." [HPO:curators]

name: Biparietal narrowing
def: "A narrowing of the biparietal diameter (i.e., of the transverse distance between the protuberances of the two parietal bones of the skull)." [HPO:curators]

name: Broad skull
def: "Increased width of the skull." [HPO:probinson]

name: Obliteration of the calvarial diploe
def: "Absence of the spongy bone structure (or tissue) of the internal part of the skull cap (i.e., of the calvarial diploe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Platystencephaly
def: "Extreme width of the skull in the occipital region, with anterior narrowing and prognathism." [PMID:31839203]

name: Trigonocephaly
def: "Wedge-shaped, or triangular head, with the apex of the triangle at the midline of the forehead and the base of the triangle at the occiput." [PMID:19125436]

name: Acrania
def: "Partial or complete absence of the flat bones of the cranial vault. The condition is frequently, though not always, associated with anencephaly." [UToronto:chum]

name: Thickened calvaria
def: "The presence of an abnormally thick calvaria." [HPO:curators]

name: Calvarial skull defect
def: "A localized defect in the bone of the skull resulting from abnormal embryological development. The defect is covered by normal skin. In some cases, skull x-rays have shown underlying lytic bone lesions which have closed before the age of one year." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dense calvaria
def: "An abnormal increase of density of the bones making up the calvaria." [HPO:curators]

name: Thin calvarium
def: "The presence of an abnormally thin calvarium." [HPO:probinson]

name: Copper beaten skull
def: "Diffuse prominent gyral impressions on the inner table of skull vault said to resemble beaten copper." [PMID:31466955]

name: Platybasia
def: "A developmental malformation of the occipital bone and upper end of the cervical spine, in which the latter appears to have pushed the floor of the occipital bone upward such that there is an abnormal flattening of the skull base." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cloverleaf skull
def: "Trilobar skull configuration when viewed from the front or behind." [PMID:19125436, PMID:29089832]

name: Cleft in skull base
def: "A bony defect in the skull base." [HPO:curators]

name: Large foramen magnum
def: "An abnormal increase in the size of the foramen magnum." [HPO:curators]

name: Small foramen magnum
def: "An abnormal narrowing of the foramen magnum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Advanced pneumatization of the mastoid process
def: "An abnormally advanced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms." [HPO:probinson]

name: Delayed pneumatization of the mastoid process
def: "An abnormally reduced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms." [HPO:probinson]

name: Mandibulofacial dysostosis
def: "A type of craniofacial dysostosis associated with abnormalities of the external ears, mirognathia, macrostomia, coloboma of the lower eyelid, and cleft palate. This is a bundled term that is left in the HPO now for convenience with legacy annotations but should not be used for new annotations." [HPO:probinson]

name: Midface retrusion
def: "Posterior positions and/or vertical shortening of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased concavity of the face and/or reduced nasolabial angle." [DDD:jclayton-smith, PMID:19125436]

name: Hyperplasia of midface
def: "Abnormally anterior positioning of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased convexity of the face, or increased nasolabial angle. The midface includes the maxilla, the cheeks, the zygomas, and the infraorbital and perialar regions of the face" [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125436]

name: Nasal congestion
def: "Reduced ability to pass air through the nasal cavity often leading to mouth breathing." [HPO:probinson]

name: Round face
def: "The facial appearance is more circular than usual as viewed from the front." [PMID:19125436]

name: Doll-like facies
def: "A characteristic facial appearance with a round facial form, full cheeks, a short nose, and a relatively small chin." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elfin facies
def: "This is a description previously used to describe a facial form characterized by a short, upturned nose, wide mouth, widely spaced eyes, and full cheeks. Because of the imprecision in this definition it is preferable to describe these features precisely. This term is retained because it was often used in the past, but it should not be used for new annotations." [HPO:probinson]

name: Oval face
def: "A face with a rounded and slightly elongated outline." [HPO:probinson]

name: Triangular face
def: "Facial contour, as viewed from the front, triangular in shape, with breadth at the temples and tapering to a narrow chin." [DDD:jclayton-smith, PMID:19125436]

name: Square face
def: "Facial contours, as viewed from the front, show a broad upper face/cranium and lower face/mandible, creating a square appearance." [PMID:19125436]

name: Flat face
def: "Absence of concavity or convexity of the face when viewed in profile." [PMID:19125436]

name: Moon facies
def: "A rounded, puffy face with fat deposits in the temporal fossa and cheeks, a double chin." [HPO:probinson]

name: High forehead
def: "An abnormally increased height of the forehead." [HPO:probinson]

name: Frontal bossing
def: "Bilateral bulging of the lateral frontal bone prominences with relative sparing of the midline." [PMID:19125436]

name: Flat forehead
def: "A forehead with abnormal flatness." [HPO:probinson]

name: Vertical forehead creases
def: "Vertical soft tissue creases in the midline of the forehead, often extending from the hairline to the brow, and seen with facial expression or when the face is at rest." [PMID:19125436]

name: Narrow forehead
def: "Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations below the mean (objective); or apparently narrow intertemporal region (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

name: Sloping forehead
def: "Inclination of the anterior surface of the forehead from the vertical more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently excessive posterior sloping of the forehead in a lateral view." [PMID:19125436]

name: Broad forehead
def: "Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently increased distance between the two sides of the forehead." [PMID:19125436]

name: Frontal hirsutism
def: "Excessive amount of hair growth on forehead." [DDD:jclayton-smith]

name: Prominent forehead
def: "Forward prominence of the entire forehead, due to protrusion of the frontal bone." [PMID:19125436]

name: Small forehead
def: "The presence of a forehead that is abnormally small." [HPO:curators]

name: Mandibular prognathia
def: "Abnormal prominence of the chin related to increased length of the mandible." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pointed chin
def: "A marked tapering of the lower face to the chin." [PMID:19125436]

name: Chin with H-shaped crease
def: "H-shaped crease in the fat pad of the chin." [PMID:19125436]

name: Cleft of chin
def: "Incomplete fusion of the chin, resulting from a developmental defect and manifesting as a midline cleft or fissure of the chin." [DDD:jclayton-smith]

name: Dimple chin
def: "A persistent midline depression of the skin over the fat pad of the chin." [PMID:19125436]

name: Tall chin
def: "Increased vertical distance from the vermillion border of the lower lip to the inferior-most point of the chin." [eom:96d8ca16a3c80216, PMID:19125436]

name: Broad chin
def: "Increased width of the midpoint of the mandible (mental protuberance) and overlying soft tissue." [PMID:19125436]

name: Chin with horizontal crease
def: "Horizontal crease or fold situated below the vermilion border of the lower lip and above the fatty pad of the chin, with the face at rest." [PMID:19125436]

name: Short chin
def: "Decreased vertical distance from the vermilion border of the lower lip to the inferior-most point of the chin." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125436]

name: Infra-orbital crease
def: "Skin crease extending from below the inner canthus laterally along the malar process of the maxilla and zygoma." [PMID:19125427]

name: Periorbital fullness
def: "Increase in periorbital soft tissue." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Infra-orbital fold
def: "Elevated ridge(s) of skin starting well below the medial aspect of the lower lid that curves gradually upward toward and/or across the nasal bridge." [PMID:19125427]

name: Bitemporal forceps marks
def: "Bilateral temporal scarlike defects, which are said to resemble forceps marks." [DDD:jclayton-smith, PMID:1401310]

name: Bitemporal hollowing
def: "Depression of profile in both temporal regions." []

name: Retinal arteriolar constriction
def: "Decreased retinal arteriolar diameters, which may decrease blood flow and slow oxygen delivery to regions of the retina." [HPO:probinson]

name: Retinal arteriolar tortuosity
def: "The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal arterioles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cherry red spot of the macula
def: "Pallor of the perifoveal macula of the retina with appearance of a small circular reddish choroid shape as seen through the fovea centralis due to relative transparancy of the macula." [HPO:probinson]

name: Retinal arteriolar occlusion
def: "Blockage of retinal arteriole, generally associated with interruption of blood flow and oxygen delivery to affected regions of the retina." [HPO:probinson]

name: Retinal arterial macroaneurysms
