def: "Movement-based tics affecting discrete muscle groups." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Stereotypical hand wringing
def: "Habitual clasping and squeezing of the hands." [HPO:probinson]

name: Punding
def: "Punding is a stereotypical motor behavior characterized by an intense fascination with repetitive, excessive and non-goal oriented handling, and examining of objects." [ICM:PCaroppo, PMID:15077237, PMID:25452726]

name: Stereotypical body rocking
def: "Habitual repetitive movement of the body." [HPO:probinson]

name: Eye poking
def: "Repetitive pressing, poking, and/or rubbing in the eyes." [HPO:probinson, PMID:8881355]

name: Recurrent hand flapping
def: "A type of stereotypic behavior in which the affected individual repeatedly waves the hands up and down." [HPO:probinson]

name: Poor gross motor coordination
def: "An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of large muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Gross motor skills are required to mediate movements of the arms, legs, and other large body parts." []

name: Poor fine motor coordination
def: "An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of small muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Fine motor skills are required to mediate movements of the wrists, hands, fingers, feet, and toes." []

name: Simultanapraxia
def: "A subset of motor impersistence, defined as the inability to perform more than two of the simple voluntary acts simultaneously, such as closing the eyes and protruding the tongue." [DOI:10.1007/978-0-387-79948-3_2046, PhenoTips:CHum]

name: Limb ataxia
def: "A kind of ataxia that affects movements of the extremities." [HPO:probinson]

name: Episodic ataxia
def: "Periodic spells of incoordination and imbalance, that is, episodes of ataxia typically lasting from 10 minutes to several hours or days." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dysdiadochokinesis
def: "A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to perform rapidly alternating movements, such as pronating and supinating his or her hand on the dorsum of the other hand as rapidly as possible." [HPO:probinson, HPO:zaferyueksel, UKB:tklockgether]

name: Clumsiness
def: "Lack of physical coordination resulting in an abnormal tendency to drop items or bump into objects." [HPO:probinson]

name: Progressive extrapyramidal muscular rigidity
def: "A progressive degree of muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Parkinsonism with favorable response to dopaminergic medication
def: "Parkinsonism is a clinical syndrome that is a feature of a number of different diseases, including Parkinson disease itself, other neurodegenerative diseases such as progressive supranuclear palsy, and as a side-effect of some neuroleptic medications. Some but not all individuals with Parkinsonism show responsiveness to dopaminergic medication defined as a substantial reduction of amelioration of the component signs of Parkinsonism (including mainly tremor, bradykinesia, rigidity, and postural instability) upon administration of dopaminergic medication." []

name: Photosensitive tonic-clonic seizure
def: "Generalized-onset tonic-clonic seizures that are provoked by flashing or flickering light." [HPO:probinson, PMID:28276060]

name: Photosensitive myoclonic seizure
def: "Generalised myoclonic seizure provoked by flashing or flickering light." [PMID:28276060]

name: Absence seizure with eyelid myoclonia
def: "An absence with eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by forced upward jerking of the eyelids during an absence seizure." [HPO:jalbers, PMID:19469840, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

name: Atypical absence seizure
def: "An atypical absence seizure is a type of generalised non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by interruption of ongoing activities and reduced responsiveness. In comparison to a typical absence seizure, changes in tone may be more pronounced, onset and/or cessation may be less abrupt, and the duration of the ictus and post-ictal recovery may be longer. Although not always available, an EEG often demonstrates slow (<3 Hz), irregular, generalized spike-wave activity." [HPO:probinson, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064, PMID:6790275]

name: Myoclonic absence seizure
def: "Myoclonic absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by an interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare and rhythmic three-per-second myoclonic movements, causing ratcheting abduction of the upper limbs leading to progressive arm elevation, and associated with 3 Hz generalized spike-wave discharges on the electroencephalogram. Duration is typically 10-60 s. Whilst impairment of consciousness may not be obvious the ILAE classified this seizure as a generalized non-motor seizure in 2017." [HPO:ihelbig, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064, PMID:9637609]

name: Febrile seizure outside the age of 3 months to 6 years
def: "Any type of seizure (most often a generalized tonic-clonic seizure) occurring with fever (at least 38.0 degrees Celsius) but in the absence of central nervous system infection, severe metabolic disturbance or other alternative precipitant in people beyond the typical arrange of 3 months-6 years with no prior history of afebrile seizure." [PMID:30078767, PMID:9126059]

name: Tonic status epilepticus
def: "Tonic status epilepticus is a type of status epilepticus characterized by focal or bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, which may be electrographically generalized or focal." [ORCID:0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:26336950]

name: Generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure
def: "A generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by a myoclonic jerk followed by an atonic motor component." [HPO:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

name: Generalized clonic seizure
def: "Generalized clonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterised by sustained bilateral jerking, either symmetric or asymmetric, that is regularly repetitive and involves the same muscle groups." [HPO:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

name: Generalized tonic seizure
def: "A generalized tonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterised by bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, often with neck stiffening without a subsequent clonic phase. The tonic activity can be a sustained abnormal posture, either in extension or flexion, sometimes accompanied by tremor of the extremities." [HPO:jalbers, HPO:probinson, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

name: Infantile spasms
def: "Infantile spasms represent a subset of \"epileptic spasms\". Infantile Spasms are epileptic spasms starting in the first year of life (infancy)." [HPO:ihelbig]

name: Dysesthesia
def: "Painful sensations elicited by a nonpainful cutaneous stimulus such as a light touch or gentle stroking over affected areas of the body. Sometimes referred to as hyperpathia or hyperalgesia. Often perceived as an intense burning, dyesthesias may outlast the stimulus by several seconds." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Spontaneous pain sensation
def: "Spontaneous pain is a kind of neuropathic pain which occurs without an identifiable trigger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abolished vibration sense
def: "A complete loss of the ability to perceive vibration." [HPO:curators]

name: Delirium
def: "A state of sudden and severe confusion." []

name: Paroxysmal drowsiness
def: "Attacks of disabling daytime drowsiness and low alertness." [HPO:probinson]

name: Paroxysmal lethargy
def: "Repeated episodes of sudden-onset and transient lethargy." [HPO:probinson]

name: Expressive aphasia
def: "Impairment of expressive language and relative preservation of receptive language abilities. That is, the patient understands language (speech, writing) but cannot express it." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anomic aphasia
def: "An inability to name people and objects that are correctly perceived. The individual is able to describe the object in question, but cannot provide the name." [HPO:probinson, PMID:18348092]

name: Transient global amnesia
def: "A paroxysmal, transient loss of memory function with preservation of immediate recall and remote memory but with a severe impairment of memory for recent events and ability to retain new information." [HPO:probinson]

name: Motor deterioration
def: "Loss of previously present motor (i.e., movement) abilities." [HPO:probinson]

name: Psychomotor deterioration
def: "Loss of previously present mental and motor abilities." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal lower-limb motor evoked potentials
def: "An anomaly identified by motor evoked potentials (MEPs) in the leg." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Glabellar reflex
def: "A type of primitive reflex that is elicited by repetitive tapping on the forehead. Normal subjects usually blink in response to the first several taps, but if blinking persists, the response is abnormal and considered to be a sign of frontal release. Persistent blinking is also known as Myerson's sign." [HPO:probinson]

name: Palmomental reflex
def: "A type of primitive reflex characterized by an involuntary contraction of the mentalis muscle of the chin caused by stimulation of the thenar eminence of the palm." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12122165, PMID:21250236]

name: Grasp reflex
def: "A type of primitive reflex that can be elicated when the hand of the examiner is gently inserted into the palm of the patient's hand. The palmar surface is stroked or simply touched. The flexor surfaces of the fingers may be stimulated also by the examiner's fingers. The stimulus should be in a distal direction. With a positive response, the patient grasps the examiner's hand with variable strength and continues to grasp as the examiner's hand is moved. Ability to release the grip voluntarily depends on the activity of the reflex; some patients can do so readily, while others can even be lifted off the bed, since the grasp has such power [NCBI Books:NBK395]." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12700289]

name: Suck reflex
def: "A type of primitive reflex that is elicited by lightly touching or tapping on the lips with an object such as a tongue blade, reflex hammer, or the examiner's finger. At times the reflex is obtained merely by approaching the lips with an object. A positive suck reflex consists of sucking movements by the lips when they are stroked or touched." [PMID:21250236]

name: Brisk reflexes
def: "Tendon reflexes that are noticeably more active than usual (conventionally denoted 3+ on clinical examination). Brisk reflexes may or may not indicate a neurological lesion. They are distinguished from hyperreflexia by the fact that hyerreflexia is characterized by hyperactive repeating (clonic) reflexes, which are considered to be always abnormal." []

name: Jaw hyperreflexia
def: "Increased intensity of muscle tendon reflexes in jaw." []

name: Progressive gait ataxia
def: "A type of gait ataxia displaying progression of clinical severity." [HPO:probinson]

name: Gait instability, worse in the dark
Writer's cramp
def: "A focal dystonia of the fingers, hand, and/or forearm that appears when the affected person attempts to do a task that requires fine motor movements such as writing or playing a musical instrument." [HPO:probinson]

name: Arm dystonia
def: "A type of dystonia (abnormally increased muscular tone causing fixed abnormal postures) that affects muscles of the arms." []

name: Leg dystonia
def: "A type of dystonia (abnormally increased muscular tone causing fixed abnormal postures) that affects muscles of the legs." []

name: Parietal hypometabolism in FDG PET
def: "Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the parietal cortex as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan." [HPO:probinson, PMID:15073255]

name: Reduced brain creatine level by MRS
def: "A decrease in the level of creatine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." [PMID:12557293, PMID:15625559]

name: Reduced brain glutamine level by MRS
def: "An decrease in the level of glutamine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." [ORCID:0000-0003-0169-8159, PMID:24123328]

name: Elevated brain lactate level by MRS
def: "An increase in the level of lactate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Reduced brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS
def: "A decrease in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Elevated brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS
def: "An increase in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

name: Elevated brain choline level by MRS
def: "An increase in the level of choline-containing compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Peripheral visual field loss
def: "Loss of peripheral vision with retention of central vision, resulting in a constricted circular tunnel-like field of vision." [HPO:probinson]

name: Centrocecal scotoma
def: "A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) located between the central point of fixation and the blind spot with a roughly horizontal oval shape." [HPO:probinson]

name: Central scotoma
def: "An area of depressed vision located at the point of fixation and that interferes with central vision." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pericentral scotoma
def: "A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) that surrounds the central fixation point." [HPO:probinson]

name: Visual acuity light perception with projection
Ultra-low vision with retained light perception
def: "Ultra-low vision but with retained ability to perceive the difference between light and dark." [UManchester:psergouniotis]

name: Ultra-low vision with no light perception
def: "Ultra-low vision with complete lack of light and form perception." [UManchester:psergouniotis]

name: Ultra-low vision with retained motion projection
def: "Ultra-low vision but with retained ability to identify a moving object (typically hand motion at distance of 30 cm)." [UManchester:psergouniotis]

name: Congenital blindness
def: "Blindness with onset at birth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Protanomaly
def: "A type of anomalous trichromacy associated with defective long-wavelength-sensitive (L) cones, causing the sensitivity spectrum to be shifted toward medium wavelengths. This leads to difficulties especially in distinguishing red and green." [HPO:probinson]

name: Deuteranomaly
def: "A type of anomalous trichromacy associated with abnormal M photopigment, such that the absorption spectrum is shifted toward L wavelengths. Affected individuals have difficulties distinguishing between red and green." [HPO:probinson]

name: Tritanomaly
def: "Difficulty distinguishing between yellow and blue, possible related to dysfunction of the S photopigment." [HPO:probinson]

name: Blue cone monochromacy
def: "A form of monochromacy in which vision is derived from the remaining preserved blue (S) cones and rod photoreceptors." [HPO:probinson]

name: Esophoria
def: "A form of strabismus with both eyes turned inward to a relatively mild degree, usually defined as less than 10 prism diopters." []

name: Exophoria
def: "A form of strabismus with one or both eyes deviated outward to a milder degree than with exotropia." []

name: Duane anomaly
def: "A condition associated with a limitation of the horizontal ocular movement with retraction of the globe and narrowing of the palpebral fissure on adduction" [HPO:probinson]

name: Upgaze palsy
def: "A limitation of the ability to direct one's gaze above the horizontal meridian." []

name: Downgaze palsy
def: "A limitation of the ability to direct one's gaze below the horizontal meridian." [PMID:8913186]

name: Congenital horizontal nystagmus
def: "Horizontal nystagmus dating from or present at birth." [HPO:curators]

name: Gaze-evoked horizontal nystagmus
def: "Horizontal nystagmus made apparent by looking to the right or to the left." [HPO:curators]

name: Horizontal pendular nystagmus
def: "Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements of equal velocity." [HPO:probinson]

name: Spasmus nutans
def: "The combination of pendular nystagmus, head nodding, and torticollis." [HPO:probinson, PMID:7499100]

name: Seesaw nystagmus
def: "Seesaw nystagmus is a type of pendular nystagmus where a half cycle consists of the elevation and intorsion of one eye, concurrently with the depression and extortion of the fellow eye. In the other half cycle, there is an inversion of the ocular movements." [HPO:probinson]

name: Downbeat nystagmus
def: "Downbeat nystagmus is a type of fixation nystagmus with the fast phase beating in a downward direction. It generally increases when looking to the side and down and when lying prone." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21505601]

name: Upbeat nystagmus
def: "In primary position, the eyes drift slowly downward and then spontaneously beat upward. Upward gaze accentuates the nystagmus. The associated oscillopsias are often very irritating, but the symptoms are usually transient." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21505601]

name: Progressive external ophthalmoplegia
def: "Initial bilateral ptosis followed by limitation of eye movements in all directions and slowing of saccades." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nonprogressive restrictive external ophthalmoplegia
def: "Nonprogressive restriction of movement of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position. Residual eye movements are significantly limited." [HPO:probinson]

name: Undetectable light-adapted electroretinogram
def: "No detectable response to the light-adapted 3.0 ERG (single-flash cone response). This type of ERG measures responses of the cone system; a-waves arise from cone photoreceptors and cone off-bipolar cells; the b-wave comes from On- and Off-cone bipolar cells." [PMID:25502644]

name: Undetectable light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram
def: "Absence of the combined rod-and-cone response on electroretinogram." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram amplitude
def: "Descreased amplitude of eletrical response upon electroretinography." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal amplitude of pattern reversal visual evoked potentials
Polymorphous posterior corneal dystrophy
def: "This corneal dystrophy affects the posterior limiting membrane of the cornea and is characterized by polymorphous plaques of calcium deposits in the deep stromal layers of the cornea, and occasionally by vesicular lesions of the endothelium and edema of the deep corneal stroma." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thinning of Descemet membrane
def: "A reduction in the thickness of Descemet's membrane." []

name: Descemet Membrane Folds
def: "Presence of folds in the Descemet membrane, which is the basement membrane of the endothelial (inner) cell layer of the cornea. Descemet membrane folds are generally a manifestation of inflammation or edema of the cornea." [HPO:probinson]

name: Corneal guttata
def: "Corneal guttata are droplet-like accumulations of non-banded collagen on the posterior surface of Descemet's membrane. The presence of focal thickenings of Descemet's membrane histologically named guttae. Cornea guttata can be easily diagnosed in vivo and ex vivo by means of specular microscopy as it gives dark areas where no endothelial cells are visible." [HPO:probinson, PMID:10611102, PMID:11222329]

name: Keratoconus
def: "A cone-shaped deformity of the cornea characterized by the presence of corneal distortion secondary to thinning of the apex." [HPO:probinson, PMID:7767020]

name: Recurrent corneal erosions
def: "The presence of recurrent corneal epithelial erosions. Although most corneal epithelial defects heal quickly, some may show recurrent ulcerations." [HPO:curators]

name: Herpetiform corneal ulceration
def: "The presence of one or more dendritic corneal epithelial ulcers characterized by a treelike branching linear pattern with feathery edges and terminal bulbs. Herpetiform corneal ulcers can be identified by fluorescein staining." [HPO:probinson]

name: Rieger anomaly
def: "A congenital malformation of the anterior segment characterized by iridicorneal malformation, glaucoma, iris stroma hypoplasia, posterior embryotoxon, and corneal opacities." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic iris stroma
def: "Underdevelopment of the stroma of iris." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior lenticonus
def: "A conical projection of the anterior surface of the lens, occurring as a developmental anomaly." [DDD:gblack]

name: Posterior lenticonus
def: "A conical projection of the posterior surface of the lens, occurring as a developmental anomaly." [DDD:gblack]

name: Inferior lens subluxation
def: "Partial displacement of the lens in the inferior direction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior polar cataract
def: "A polar cataract that affects the posterior pole of the lens." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior capsular cataract
def: "A cataract which is found in the back outer layer of the lens. This type often develops more rapidly." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Anterior subcapsular cataract
def: "A type of cataract affecting the anterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the lens capsule." [HPO:probinson]

name: Macular hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the macula lutea." [HPO:probinson]

name: Macular agenesis
def: "A congenital defect characterized by lack of development of the macula." []

name: Perifoveal hypoautofluorescence
def: "Decreased amount of autofluorescence (emission of fluorescent light from ocular structures in the absence of sodium fluorescein) in the retina in the region surrounding the fovea." [PMID:34800980]

name: Hypoautofluorescent macular lesion
def: "Decreased amount of autofluorescence in the macula as ascertained by fundus autofluorescence imaging." [PMID:27847630]

name: Hyperautofluorescent macular lesion
def: "Increased amount of autofluorescence in the macula as ascertained by fundus autofluorescence imaging." [PMID:27847630]

name: Photoreceptor layer loss on macular OCT
def: "Loss of the outer nuclear layer (photoreceptor layer) as assessed by ocular coherence tomography." [HPO:probinson]

name: Inner retinal layer loss on macular OCT
Falciform retinal fold
def: "An area of the retina that is buckled so that a sector-shaped sheet of retina lies in front of the normal retina. This feature is of congenital onset." [HPO:probinson]

name: Retinal dots
def: "Yellow, white or greyish lesions in the retina that are well-defined/distinct, individual and mostly uniform in size." [UManchester:psergouniotis]

name: Retinal crystals
def: "Crystalline deposits in the retina." [PMID:12498506]

name: Retinitis pigmentosa inversa
def: "Retinitis pigmentosa inversa is form of retinal degeneration characterized by areas of retinal/chorioretinal degeneration with pigment migration in the macular area (in contrast to retinitis pigmentosa which, at early disease stages, predominantly affects the retinal periphery)." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:9734800]

name: Foveoschisis
def: "Splitting of the retinal layers in the macula." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multifocal subretinal deposits
def: "Deposits accumulating between the outer retina and the retinal pigment epithelium and that are distributed with multiple foci." []

name: Retinal hole
def: "A small break in the retina." [HPO:probinson]

name: Retinal nerve fiber edema
def: "Swelling (edema) of the retinal nerve fibers." []

name: Retinal nonattachment
def: "Failure of attachment of the retina during development." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21441919]

name: Exudative retinal detachment
def: "A type of retinal detachment arising from damage to the outer blood-retinal barrier that allows fluid to access the subretinal space and separate the neurosensory retina from the retinal pigment epithelium." [HPO:probinson, ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Rhegmatogenous retinal detachment
def: "A type of retinal detachment associated with a retinal tear, that is, with a break in the retina that allows fluid to pass from the vitreous space into the subretinal space between the sensory retina and the retinal pigment epithelium." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
def: "An acute condition characterized by sudden visual loss (usually discovered in the morning), optic disc edema at onset, optic disc-related visual field defects. Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy can be associated with flame hemorrhages on the swollen disc or nearby neuroretinal layer, and sometimes with nearby cotton-wool exudates." [HPO:probinson, PMID:17698200]

name: Retrobulbar optic neuritis
def: "Optic neuritis that occurs in the section of the optic nerve located behind the eyeball." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Hypoplastic optic chiasm
def: "Developmental defect characterized by undergrowth of the optic chiasm." [PMID:23312594, PMID:23591992]

name: Opto-chiasmatic atrophy
def: "Wasting (atrophy) of the optic chiasm." [PMID:34161705]

name: Pseudopapilledema
def: "Apparent optic disc swelling in the absence of increased intracranial pressure." [HPO:probinson]

name: Optic disc drusen
def: "Optic disc drusen are acellular, calcified deposits within the optic nerve head. Optic disc drusen are congenital and developmental anomalies of the optic nerve head, representing hyaline-containing bodies that, over time, appear as elevated, lumpy irregularities on the anterior portion of the optic nerve." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22787500, PMID:23658477, PMID:30524490]

name: Papilledema
def: "Papilledema refers to edema (swelling) of the optic disc secondary to any factor which increases cerebral spinal fluid pressure." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reticular pigmentary degeneration
def: "A type of retinal reticular pigmentation that forms a polygonal, netlike arrangement of hyperpigmented lines forming geometric patterns in the fundus." [HPO:fprobst, PMID:28114409]

name: Achromatic retinal patches
def: "Areas of the retina lacking pigmentation. Punched out areas of chorioretinal hypopigmentation less than 1 disc diameter in size and tending to be located in the midperiphery of the retina." [HPO:probinson, PMID:11264130]

name: Hypoplasia of deltoid muscle
def: "Underdevelopment of the deltoid muscle." [Neuromics:vstraub]

name: Triceps aplasia
def: "Absence of the triceps muscle." [HPO:curators]

name: Biceps aplasia
def: "Absence of the biceps muscle." [HPO:curators]

name: Clinodactyly of the 4th toe
def: "Bending or curvature of a fourth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Clinodactyly of the 3rd toe
def: "Bending or curvature of a third toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Clinodactyly of the 5th toe
def: "Bending or curvature of a fifth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Clinodactyly of the 2nd toe
def: "Bending or curvature of a second toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ectopic accessory finger-like appendage
def: "In contrast to forms of polydactyly where the supernumerary digit (this can either be a rudimentary or a completely 'normal' digit) is either located postaxial (on the ulnar side of the hand, next to the little finger), preaxial (on the radial side of the hand, next to the thumb) or mesoaxial (somewhere central, between thumb and little finger), a supernumerary digit may also be placed ectopically, meaning anywhere else except post-,meso- or preaxial. In the literature this is sometimes referred to as Disorganisation-like Syndrome (OMIM223200)." [HPO:probinson]

name: 3-4 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers three and four." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 2-4 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of the fingers two to four." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 4-5 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers four and five." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 2-3 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers two and three." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 2-5 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers two to five." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 1-4 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one to four." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: 1-5 finger syndactyly
def: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one to five (complete syndactyly of all fingers of the hand)." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Brachytelomesophalangy
def: "Disproportionately short middle and distal phalanges compared to the hand/foot." [HPO:probinson]

name: Type D brachydactyly
def: "This type of brachydactyly is characterized by short and broad terminal phalanges of the thumbs and big toes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Type E brachydactyly
def: "In type E brachydactyly, shortening of the fingers is mainly in the metacarpals and metatarsals." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 3rd toe
def: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the third toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 2nd toe
def: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the second toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 5th toe
def: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the fifth toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 4th toe
def: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the fourth toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Progressive leg bowing
def: "Progressive bending or abnormal curvature of the leg." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fibular metaphyseal irregularity
def: "Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of a metaphysis of a fibula." [HPO:probinson]

name: Distal femoral metaphyseal irregularity
def: "Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the distal metaphysis of the femur." []

name: Tibial metaphyseal irregularity
def: "Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of a metaphysis of a tibia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 3rd finger
def: "Chronic loss of joint motion of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 3rd finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue." [HPO:curators]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 2nd finger
def: "Chronic loss of joint motion of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 2nd finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contractures of the interphalangeal joint of the thumb
def: "Chronic loss of joint motion of the interphalangeal joint of the thumb due to structural changes in non-bony tissue. This joint is also called Articulatio interphalangealis pollicis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 5th finger
def: "Proximal interphalangeal (PIP) flexion deformity of the little finger. That is, the PIP joint of a little finger is bent (flexed) and cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 4th finger
def: "Chronic loss of joint motion of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 4th finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue. That is, the PIP joint of a fourth finger is bent (flexed) and cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contracture of the distal interphalangeal joint of the 4th finger
def: "Chronic loss of joint motion of the distal interphalangeal joint of the 4th finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ulnar deviation of the 3rd finger
def: "Displacement of the 3rd finger towards the ulnar side (i.e., towards the ring finger)." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Ulnar deviation of the 2nd finger
def: "Displacement of the 2nd (index) finger towards the ulnar side." [HPO:curators]

name: Hitchhiker thumb
def: "With the hand relaxed and the thumb in the plane of the palm, the axis of the thumb forms an angle of at least 90 degrees with the long axis of the hand." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Radial deviation of the 4th finger
def: "Displacement of the 4th finger towards the radial side (i.e., towards the thumb)." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Radial deviation of the 2nd finger
def: "Displacement of the 2nd finger towards the radial side." [HPO:curators]

name: Radial deviation of the 3rd finger
def: "Displacement of the 3rd finger towards the radial side (i.e., towards the thumb)." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Proximal placement of thumb
def: "Proximal mislocalization of the thumb." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Absent proximal finger flexion creases
def: "Absence of the proximal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fingers." [HPO:probinson]

name: Single interphalangeal crease of fifth finger
def: "Presence of only one (instead of two, as normal) interphalangeal crease of the fifth finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thimble-shaped middle phalanges of hand
def: "The middle phalanx of finger resembles a thimble, a small metal cap to protect the finger while sewing that has a broad (proximal) base and narrower top, whereby both base and top are flat." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperphalangy of the 2nd finger
def: "An accessory phalanx of the index (second) finger that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges. Hyperphalangy of the index finger results from an accessory ossification center at the metacarpophalangeal joint, resulting in radial deviation of the index finger. Note that this term refers only to this type of hyperphalangy." [HPO:probinson, PMID:25480037, PMID:6540680]

name: Long distal phalanx of finger
def: "Increased length of the distal phalanx of finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Drumstick terminal phalanges
def: "Rounding and broadening of the tufts of the distal phalanges." [HPO:probinson]

name: Slender distal phalanx of finger
def: "Reduced diameter of the distal phalanx of finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Long proximal phalanx of finger
def: "Increased length of the proximal phalanx of finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Slender proximal phalanx of finger
def: "Reduced diameter of the proximal phalanx of finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Limited mobility of proximal interphalangeal joint
Narrow small joints of the hand
Soft tissue swelling of interphalangeal joints
Absent thumb
def: "Absent thumb, i.e., the absence of both phalanges of a thumb and the associated soft tissues." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Postaxial polydactyly type A
def: "Supernumerary digits located at the ulnar side of the hand with a complete extra finger and extra metacarpal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Advanced ossification of carpal bones
def: "Ossification of carpal bones at an abnormally early age." [HPO:probinson]

name: Two carpal ossification centers present at birth
Multiple carpal ossification centers
def: "A delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more long bones." [HPO:probinson]

name: Irregular carpal bones
def: "Carpal bones with irregular or fragmented margins." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Aplasia of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
def: "Absence of the distal phalanx of the middle (3rd) finger." [HPO:curators]

name: Absent proximal phalanx of thumb
def: "Absence of the proximal phalanx of the thumb. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent middle phalanx of 2nd finger
def: "Absence of the middle phalanx of the index (2nd) finger." [HPO:curators]

name: Absent middle phalanx of 3rd finger
def: "Absence of the middle phalanx of the middle (3rd) finger." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Absent middle phalanx of 5th finger
def: "Absence of the middle phalanx of the little (5th) finger." [HPO:curators]

name: Aplasia of the 1st metacarpal
def: "Absent first metacarpal (long bone) of the hand." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
def: "Absence of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger." [HPO:curators]

name: Short 5th metacarpal
def: "Short fifth metacarpal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 4th metacarpal
def: "Short fourth metacarpal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 2nd metacarpal
def: "Short second metacarpal bone because of developmental hypoplasia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short 1st metacarpal
def: "A developmental defect characterized by reduced length of the first metacarpal (long bone) of the hand." [HPO:probinson]

name: Shortening of all metacarpals
def: "Abnormal reduction in length of all metacarpal bones." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cuboidal metacarpal
def: "Severely shortened metacarpal with a cuboidal appearance." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short metacarpals with rounded proximal ends
Short 3rd metacarpal
def: "Short third metacarpal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the 3rd metacarpal
def: "Absence of the third long bone of the hand." [HPO:curators]

name: Aplasia of the 4th metacarpal
def: "Absence of the fourth long bone of the hand." [HPO:curator]

name: Aplasia of the 2nd metacarpal
def: "Absence of the second long bone of the hand." [HPO:curators]

name: Aplasia of the 5th metacarpal
def: "Absence of the fifth long bone of the hand." [HPO:curators]

name: Absent scaphoid
def: "Congenital absence of the scaphoid.." [DDD:jcampbell]

name: Hypoplasia of proximal radius
def: "Proximal radial shortening owing to a congenital defect of development." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bilateral ulnar hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the ulna on both sides." [HPO:probinson]

name: Distal ulnar hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the distal portion of the ulna." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bilateral radial aplasia
def: "Missing radius bone on both sides associated with congenital failure of development." [HPO:probinson]

name: Unilateral radial aplasia
def: "Missing radius bone on one side only associated with congenital failure of development." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior radial head dislocation
def: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterior direction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterolateral radial head dislocation
def: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterolateral direction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ulnar radial head dislocation
def: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an ulnar direction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Synostosis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb with the 1st metacarpal
def: "Fusion of the proximal phalanx of the thumb with the 1st metacarpal." [HPO:probinson, PMID:26571461]

name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
def: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pseudoepiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
def: "The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone although an accessory epiphysis may be located at the distal end of the metacarpal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bifid first metacarpal
def: "Partial duplication of the first metacarpal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the femoral head
def: "Underdevelopment of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short femoral neck
def: "An abnormally short femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of proximal fibula
def: "Underdevelopment or shortening of the end of the fibula (calf bone) nearest the knee." [PMID:880750]

name: Rudimentary fibula
def: "Absent or nearly absent fibula. (Does not include aplastic)" []

name: Broad femoral head
def: "Increased width of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Flattened femoral head
def: "An abnormally flattened femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lateral displacement of the femoral head
def: "A developmental anomaly with lateral displacement of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dysplasia of the femoral head
def: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Delayed femoral head ossification
def: "Delayed ossification of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dislocation of the femoral head
def: "Joint dislocation of the femoral head." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multicentric femoral head ossification
def: "There is normally one ossification center in the head of the femur. This term applies if there are multiple such centers." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elongated femoral neck
def: "Increased length of the neck of the femur." [PMID:33252156]

name: Broad femoral neck
def: "An abnormally wide femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Coxa vara
def: "Coxa vara includes all forms of decrease of the femoral neck shaft angle (the angle between the neck and the shaft of the femur) to less than 120 degrees." [HPO:probinson]

name: Narrow femoral neck
def: "An abnormally reduced diameter of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Monkey wrench femoral neck
def: "The femoral neck region shows medial metaphyseal beaking and a significant enlargement of the lesser trochanter (with some enlargement also of the greater trochanter), producing a monkey wrench (Swedish key) configuration of the proximal femur. A monkey wrench refers to a type of adjustable wrench with one fixed and one adjustable jaw at right angles to a straight handle." [PMID:7977470]

name: Postaxial polysyndactyly of foot
def: "Combined syndactyly and polydactyly of the foot on the lateral side (i.e., on the side of the little toe)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Polysyndactyly of hallux
def: "Combined syndactyly and polydactyly of the great toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent first metatarsal
def: "A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the first metatarsal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the capital femoral epiphysis
def: "Underdevelopment of the proximal epiphysis of the femur." [HPO:probinson]

name: Trident acetabulum
def: "Abnormal appearance of the acetabulum characterized by spurs at the medial and lateral acetabular margin and in the center of the acetabulum, giving rise to shape resembling a three-pronged spear sadi to resemble a trident." [PMID:28744080]

name: Recurrent patellar dislocation
def: "Patellar dislocation occurring repeated times." [HPO:curators]

name: Congenital palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles that is present at birth." []

name: Patchy palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "A focal type of palmoplantar keratoderma in which only certain areas of the palms and soles are affected." [HPO:probinson]

name: Palmoplantar keratoderma
def: "Abnormal thickening of the skin of the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet." [HPO:probinson]

name: Honeycomb palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles with an honeycomb pattern." [PMID:9326323]

name: Nonepidermolytic palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles charactersized by hyperkeratosis of the stratum corneum with no evidence of epidermolysis characteristic of epidermolytic hyperkeratosis." [PMID:7528239]

name: Focal friction-related palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "Hyperkeratosis affecting the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot in areas exposed to friction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Diffuse palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
def: "Diffuse abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles." [PMID:17298101]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 3rd toe
def: "The proximal interphalangeal joint of the 3rd toe cannot be straightened actively or passively." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 2nd toe
def: "The proximal interphalangeal joint of the 2nd toe cannot be straightened actively or passively." [HPO:probinson]

name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 4th toe
def: "The proximal interphalangeal joint of the 4th toe cannot be straightened actively or passively." [HPO:probinson]

name: 2-4 toe cutaneous syndactyly
def: "A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 2, 3, and 4." [HPO:probinson]

name: Medially deviated second toe
def: "Medial deviation of the second toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hallux valgus
def: "Lateral deviation of the great toe (i.e., in the direction of the little toe)." [HPO:curators]

name: Hallux varus
def: "Medial deviation of the great toe owing to a deformity of the great toe joint causing the hallux to deviate medially." [HPO:curators]

name: Absent hallux
def: "Aplasia of the hallux, that is, a development defect such that the big toe does not develop." [HPO:probinson]

name: Triphalangeal hallux
def: "A hallux (big toe) with three phalanges in a single, proximo-distal axis." [PMID:19760621, PMID:22486404]

name: Partial absence of toe
def: "The absence of a phalangeal segment of a toe or hallux." [PMID:19125433]

name: Proximal/middle symphalangism of 5th toe
def: "Bony fusion of the middle and proximal phalanges of the 5th toe." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Proximal/middle symphalangism of 4th toe
def: "Bony fusion of the middle and proximal phalanges of the 4th toe." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Bilateral talipes equinovarus
def: "Bilateral clubfoot deformity (see HP:0001762)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Loss of subcutaneous adipose tissue from upper limbs
Absent muscle dystrophin expression
def: "Lack of dystrophin in muscle tissue. Immunohistochemistry reveals absent dystrophin protein in the muscle biopsy." [PMID:11917091, UToronto:htrang]

name: Absent muscle fiber emerin
def: "Immunohistochemistry shows complete lack of emerin protein in the muscle biopsy." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Reduced muscle fiber merosin
def: "A reduced amount of merosin in muscle fibers. This feature is usually assessed by immunohistochemical examination of muscle biopsy tissue." [HPO:Probinson]

name: Absent muscle fiber merosin
def: "Lack of merosin protein in the muscle biopsy." []

name: Reduced muscle fiber alpha dystroglycan
def: "Immunohistochemistry reveals reduced alpha dystroglycan protein in the muscle biopsy. Alpha-dystroglycan is a heavily glycosylated peripheral-membrane component of the dystrophin-associated glycoprotein complex (DAPC), which, in addition to laminin alpha2, binds perlecan and agrin in the extracellular matrix, whereas beta-dystroglycan, derived from the same gene, is a transmembrane protein that links to dystrophin intracellularly." [HPO:probinson, PMID:11592034, UToronto:htrang]

name: Hypoglycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan
def: "A reduction in the degree of glycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan in muscle tissue." [PMID:18691338]

name: Accumulation of muscle fiber desmin
def: "Immunohistochemistry shows accumulation of desmin protein in the muscle biopsy." [Neuromics:vstraub]

name: Absent muscle fiber dysferlin
def: "Immunohistochemistry shows complete lack of dysferlin protein in the muscle biopsy." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Increased Z-disc width
def: "Abnormally increased width of the Z-disk of the sarcomere, resulting from splitting or opening of the Z-disc (c.f., Figure 2 of PMID:28732005)." []

name: Z-band streaming
def: "Streaming or smearing of the Z band, which is then no longer confined to a narrow zone which bisects the I band. The Z disc may extend across the I band or the entire sarcomere in a zigzag manner. Focal thickening, smudging, and blurring of the Z band takes place concurrently. Myofibrillar disorganization is a frequent but not invariable accompanying change." [PMID:1180479, PMID:22028589]

name: Muscle fiber intracytoplasmic reducing inclusion bodies
def: "Intracytoplasmic inclusions in myofibers that reduce nitro-blue tetrazolium (NBT) and thus stain strongly with the menadione-NBT stain." [PMID:18274675]

name: Nemaline bodies
def: "Nemaline rods are abnormal bodies that can occur in skeletal muscle fibers. The rods can be observed on histological analysis of muscle biopsy tissue or upon electron microscopy, where they appear either as extensions of sarcomeric Z-lines, in random array without obvious attachment to Z-lines (often in areas devoid of sarcomeres) or in large clusters localized at the sarcolemma or intermyofibrillar spaces." [HPO:curators, PMID:11333380]

name: Muscle fiber tubular inclusions
def: "Unusual regions of densely packed membranous tubules known as tubular aggregates which present as membranous inclusions, derived from membranes of sarcoplasmic reticulum and mitochondria, containing miscellaneous proteins with a variety of enzymatic activities." [HPO:sdoelken, PMID:15113116]

name: Generalized limb muscle atrophy
def: "Generalized (unlocalized) atrophy affecting muscles of the limbs in both proximal and distal locations." [HPO:probinson]

name: Progressive distal muscular atrophy
def: "Progressive muscular atrophy affecting muscles in the distal portions of the extremities." [HPO:curators]

name: Triangular tongue
def: "A form of macrogloassia (increased size of the tongue) characterized by a broad based root of the tongue but a small tongue tip, giving the appearance of a triangle." [UToronto:bgallinger]

name: Amyoplasia
def: "Congenital lack of development of the muscles, which are then replaced by a mixture of dense fat and fibrous tissue." [HPO:probinson, Neuromics:vstraub]

name: Generalized neonatal hypotonia
def: "Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) manifesting in the neonatal period and affecting the entire musculature." [HPO:probinson]

name: Infantile axial hypotonia
def: "Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) affecting the musculature of the trunk and with onset in infancy." [HPO:curators]

name: Episodic generalized hypotonia
def: "The occurrence of repeated episodes of generalized muscular hypotonia." [HPO:curators]

name: Cogwheel rigidity
def: "A type of rigidity in which a muscle responds with cogwheellike jerks to the use of constant force in bending the limb (i.e., it gives way in little, repeated jerks when the muscle is passively stretched)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decerebrate rigidity
def: "A type of rigidity that is manifested by an exaggerated extensor posture of all extremities." [UToronto:chum]

name: Fatigable weakness of swallowing muscles
def: "A type of weakness of the muscles involved in swallowing that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [PMID:17986328, UK:rheller]

name: Fatigable weakness of speech muscles
def: "A type of weakness of the muscles involved in speech that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [PMID:17986328, UNCL:hlochmueller]

name: Fatigable weakness of distal limb muscles
def: "A type of weakness of a skeletal muscle of distal part of a limb that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [UK:rheller]

name: Fatigable weakness of neck muscles
def: "A type of weakness of a skeletal muscle in the neck that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [UK:rheller]

name: Fatiguable weakness of proximal limb muscles
def: "A type of weakness of a skeletal muscle of proximal part of a limb that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [UK:rheller]

name: Congenital facial diplegia
def: "Facial diplegia (that is, bilateral facial palsy) with congenital onset." [HPO:curators]

name: Hypoplasia of the odontoid process
def: "Developmental hypoplasia of the dens of the axis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the nasal bone
def: "Absence of the nasal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the nasal bone
def: "Underdevelopment of the nasal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent crus of helix
def: "Continuum between the tragus and ascending helix, without any evidence of a posterior extension (crus) towards the concha." [PMID:19152421]

name: Horizontal crus of helix
def: "An abnormal horizontal axis orientation of the crus of the helix. That is, the main axis of the crus of the helix is perpendicular to the medial longitudinal axis of the ear, instead of sloping inferoposteriorly." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152421]

name: Prominent crus of helix
def: "The presence of an abnormally prominent of the crus of the helix. That is, development of the crus helix to the same degree as an average antihelix stem or helix." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152421]

name: Calcific stippling of infantile cartilaginous skeleton
Subcutaneous ossification
def: "Formation of abnormal, extraskeletal bony tissue in the soft tissue beneath the skin. Subcutaneous ossifications may be observed by radiography or by palpation." [PMID:29059381]

name: Ectopic ossification in ligament tissue
def: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within ligament tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ectopic ossification in muscle tissue
def: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within muscle tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ectopic ossification in tendon tissue
def: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within tendon tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Caudal appendage
def: "The presence of a tail-like skin appendage located adjacent to the sacrum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Widened greater sciatic notch
def: "The sacroiliac joint in the bony pelvis connects the sacrum and the ilium of the pelvis, which are joined by strong ligaments. The notch is located directly superior to the joint. This term refers to a increase in the lateral dimension of the notch." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short greater sciatic notch
def: "The sacroiliac joint in the bony pelvis connects the sacrum and the ilium of the pelvis, which are joined by strong ligaments. The notch is located directly superior to the joint. This term refers to a reduction in the height of the notch." [HPO:probinson]

name: Narrow greater sciatic notch
def: "A narrowing of the sacrosciatic notch, i.e., the deep indentation in the posterior border of the hip bone at the point of union of the ilium and ischium." [HPO:pnrobinson]

name: Narrow pelvis bone
def: "Reduced side to side width of the pelvis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Halberd-shaped pelvis
def: "An anomalous radiographic appearance of the developing pelvis, in which the greater ischiadic noth (incisura ischiadica major) is shallow and the pelvis takes on the appearance said to resemble a halberd (a weapon especially of the 15th and 16th centuries consisting typically of a battle-ax and pike mounted on a handle)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19232556]

name: Square pelvis bone
def: "An abnormally squared appearance of the bony pelvis, a normally rounded or basin-shaped structure." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic pelvis
def: "Underdevelopment of the bony pelvis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Coxa magna
def: "Widening of the femoral head and neck." [HPO:probinson]

name: Arthralgia of the hip
def: "Joint pain affecting the hip." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hip dysplasia
def: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the hip." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cortically dense long tubular bones
def: "Increased density of the compact bone of long bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Congenital pseudoarthrosis of the clavicle
def: "The two portions of the clavicle (corresponding to the two primary ossification centers of the clavicle) are connected by a fibrous bridge that is contiguous with the periosteum, and a synovial membrane develops, resulting in a clavicle with a bipartite appearance radiographically. Congenital pseudarthrosis of the clavicle generally presents as a painless mass or swelling over the clavicle." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22295044]

name: Abnormality of vertebral epiphysis morphology
def: "An anomaly of one or more epiphyses of one or more vertebrae." []

name: Splayed epiphyses
def: "Flaring (widening) of the epiphysis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent shoulder dislocation
def: "Shoulder dislocation occurring repeated times." [PMID:29197942, Sanford:krageth]

name: Flat glenoid fossa
def: "Abnormally flat configuration of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus." [HPO:probinson, PMID:15163819]

name: Absent glenoid fossa
def: "Lack of development of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Glenoid fossa hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the glenoid fossa, which is the cavity in the lateral part of the scapula which articulates with the head of the humerus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Spinal stenosis with reduced interpedicular distance
def: "An abnormal narrowing of the spinal canal related to a reduction in the interpedicular distance (i.e., the distance measured between the pedicles on frontal [coronal] imaging)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cervical spinal canal stenosis
def: "An abnormal narrowing of the cervical spinal canal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Atlantoaxial instability
def: "Abnormally increased movement at the junction between the first cervical (atlas) and the second cervical (axis) vertebrae as a result of either a bony or ligamentous anomaly." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cervical spine instability
def: "An abnormal lack of stability of the cervical spine." [HPO:curators]

name: Osteoporosis of vertebrae
def: "Osteoporosis affecting predominantly the vertebrae." [HPO:curators]

name: Punctate vertebral calcifications
def: "The presence of punctiform calcification of the bone of the vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sclerotic vertebral body
def: "Increase in bone density of the vertebral body." [HPO:probinson]

name: Schmorl's node
def: "A Schmorl's node is the herniation of nucleus pulposus through the cartilaginous and bony end plate into the body of the adjacent vertebra." [PMID:22544358]

name: Abnormally straight spine
def: "The absence of the normal curvature of the vertebral column." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Camptocormia
def: "An abnormal forward-flexed posture e.g. forward flexion of the spine, which is noticeable when standing or walking but disappears when lying down. It is becoming an increasingly recognized feature of Parkinson's disease and dystonic disorders." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Herniation of intervertebral nuclei
def: "The presence of one or more herniated nucleus pulposus of intervertebral disk." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intervertebral disc degeneration
def: "The presence of degenerative changes of intervertebral disk." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased intervertebral space
def: "An increase in the vertical distance between adjacent vertebral bodies, observed as an increase in the intervertebral disc space." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dysplastic sacrum
def: "A developmental defect of the sacrum characterized by partial or disordered development of the sacrum in which portions of the sacrum, which normally is formed by fusion of five sacral vertebrae S1-S5, fail to form or fail to form normally." []

name: Anteriorly placed odontoid process
def: "Anterior mislocalization of the dens of the axis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bifid sternum
def: "The sternal cleft is a rare congenital anomaly resulting from a fusion failure of the sternum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bulging of the costochondral junction
def: "Abnormal outward curving (protuberance) of the junction of ribs and costal cartilage." [HPO:probinson]

name: Supraumbilical raphe
def: "An abnormality of the sternum that presents at birth as a ventral sternal non-union defect, due to an abnormality of the fusion of the layers of the skin. It presents as a scar-like line that extends upward from the umbilicus (belly button)." [https://www.chw.org/medical-care/birthmarks-and-vascular-anomalies-center/conditions/phace-syndrome/phace-syndrome-handbook/ventral-or-midline-abnormalities, PMID:24075092]

name: Rachitic rosary
def: "A row of beadlike prominences at the junction of a rib and its cartilage (i.e., enlarged costochondral joints), resembling a rosary." [HPO:probinson, PMID:26745253]

name: Straight clavicles
def: "An abnormally straight configuration of the clavicle, a tubular bone which normally is doubly curved ." [HPO:probinson]

name: Undulate clavicles
def: "An abnormally wavy surface or edge of the clavicles." [HPO:curators]

name: Clavicular pseudarthrosis
def: "A developmental defect in a the clavicule leading to bending and pathologic fracture, with inability to form a normal bony callus with subsequent fibrous nonunion, leading to the pseudarthrosis (or false joint)." [PMID:19232556]

name: Lateral clavicle hook
def: "An excessive upward convexity of the lateral clavicle." [HPO:probinson, PMID:7322653]

name: Long clavicles
def: "Increased length of the clavicles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Clavicular sclerosis
def: "An increase in bone density within the clavicle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Broad clavicles
def: "Increased width (cross-sectional diameter) of the clavicles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sclerotic scapulae
def: "Increased density of the bony tissue of the scapula." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sprengel anomaly
def: "A congenital skeletal deformity characterized by the elevation of one scapula (thus, one scapula is located superior to the other)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thickening of the lateral border of the scapula
Horizontal inferior border of scapula
def: "A morphological abnormality of the scapula in which there is a flat (horizontal) inferior edge of the scapula. The entire scapula is said to resemble a square, leading to the designation sqaring of the scapula (in Figure 1 of PMID:24706940 the scapulae have a roughly rectangular shape)." [PMID:24706940]

name: Bell-shaped thorax
def: "The rib cage has the shape of a wide mouthed bell. That is, the superior portion of the rib cage is constricted, followed by a convex region, and the inferior portion of the rib cage expands again to have a large diameter." [HPO:probinson]

name: Asymmetry of the thorax
def: "Lack of symmetry between the left and right halves of the thorax." [HPO:probinson]

name: Deformed rib cage
def: "Malformation of the rib cage." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal facility in opposing the shoulders
def: "Increased range of shoulder movement related to aplasia or hypoplasia of the clavicles that results in the ability to approximate the shoulders in front of the chest." [PMID:23289840]

name: Narrow chest
def: "Reduced width of the chest from side to side, associated with a reduced distance from the sternal notch to the tip of the shoulder." [HPO:probinson]

name: C1-C2 subluxation
def: "A partial dislocation of the atlantoaxial joints." [HPO:curators]

name: C2-C3 subluxation
def: "A partial dislocation of the intervertebral joint between the second and third cervical vertebrae." [HPO:probinson]

name: Heberden's node
def: "Bony swelling of the distal interphalangeal joint (DIP) associated with the formation of osteophytes (calcific spurs) of the articular (joint) cartilage that are visible radiographically." [HPO:probinson, PMID:10531070, PMID:17488856, PMID:9709182]

name: Block vertebrae
def: "Congenital synostosis between two or more adjacent vertebrae (partial or complete fusion of adjacent vertabral bodies)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fused thoracic vertebrae
def: "A congenital anomaly characterized by a joining (fusion) of two or more thoracic vertebral bodies with one another." []

name: Distal joint laxity
def: "Lack of stability of a distal joint (e.g., finger)." []

name: Generalized joint laxity
def: "Joint hypermobility (ability of a joint to move beyond its normal range of motion) affecting many or all joints of the body." [HPO:curators]

name: Hyperextensibility at elbow
def: "The ability of the elbow joint to move beyond its normal range of motion." [HPO:curators]

name: Hyperextensibility at wrists
def: "The ability of the wrist joints to move beyond their normal range of motion." [HPO:curators]

name: Joint hyperflexibility
def: "Increased mobility and flexibility in the joint due to the tension in tissues such as ligaments and muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6548-5200]

name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
def: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb." [HPO:probinson]

name: Juvenile type ovarian granulosa cell tumor
def: "Juvenile granulosa cell ovarian tumor (JGCOT) is a rare sex cord stromal tumor, occuring most frequently in premenarchal girls or young women. In contrast to adult granulosa cell tumor, JGCOT has a high mitotic index and more aggressive tumor growth. Microscopically it is seen as diffuse and regularly distributed neoplastic cells with a wide cytoplasm and pleomorphic hyperchromatic nucleus. Follicle formation, in various sizes and shapes, is important in JGCOT. Call-Exner bodies are infrequently seen in JGCOT in contrast to the adult type." [NCIT:C7289, PMID:25788847]

name: Ovarian thecoma
def: "A sex cord-stromal tumor of the ovary. Thecomas range from small tumors to large solid or solid-cystic masses of up to 15 cm. They are unilateral in over 90 percent of cases and are rarely malignant. Thecomas are stromal tumors made up of cells that resemble theca cells, lutein cells and fibroblasts. They are traditionally classified within the sex cord-stromal tumor category of ovarian tumor types." [NCIT:C1882229, PMID:27284435]

name: Dysmenorrhea
def: "Pain during menstruation that interferes with daily activities." [PMID:15686299]

name: Reduced antral follicle count
def: "A count of antral follicles that is lower than normal for age." [PMID:30010909]

name: Oocyte arrest at metaphase I
def: "Failure of oocytes to proceed through the stages of meiosis with stoppage at the first metaphase stage." [PMID:27273344, PMID:32473092]

name: Priapism
def: "A painful and harmful medical condition in which the erect penis doesn't return to its flaccid state, despite the absence of both physical and psychological stimulation, within four hours." [HPO:skoehler]

name: Impotence
def: "Inability to develop or maintain an erection of the penis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced sperm motility
def: "An abnormal reduction in the mobility of ejaculated sperm." [HPO:probinson]

name: Immotile sperm
def: "A lack of mobility of ejaculated sperm." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced progressive sperm motility
def: "A reduced proportion of sperm that move in a straight line or large circles; alternatively, an increaed proportion of sperm that move in tight circles or in some other non-linear fashion." [PMID:8957699]

name: Small scrotum
def: "Apparently small scrotum for age." [PMID:23650202]

name: Decreased testicular size
def: "Reduced volume of the testicle (the male gonad)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Clitoral hypoplasia
def: "Developmental hypoplasia of the clitoris." [HPO:probinson]

name: Varicocele
def: "A varicocele is a widening of the veins along the spermatic cord, leading to enlarged, twisted veins in the scrotum, and manifested clinically by a painless testicle lump, scrotal swelling, or bulge in the scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Prominent scrotal raphe
def: "Increased size of the ridge of tissue that extends along the midline of the scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Shawl scrotum
def: "Superior margin of the scrotum superior to the base of the penis." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23650202]

name: Bifid scrotum
def: "Midline indentation or cleft of the scrotum." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23650202]

name: Scrotal hyperpigmentation
def: "Increased pigmentation (skin color) of the scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent scrotum
def: "Congenital absence of the scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chordee
def: "Ventral, lateral, or ventrolateral bowing of the shaft and glans penis of more than 30 degrees." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23650202]

name: Absent penis
def: "Lack of recognizable penile structures." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23650202]

name: Penile freckling
def: "Multiple pigmented macules located on the skin of the penis." []

name: Partial development of the penile shaft
Long penis
def: "Penile length more than 2 SD above the mean for age." []

name: Monorchism
def: "Having only one testis in the scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Testicular torsion
def: "Testicular torsion is when the spermatic cord to a testicle twists, cutting off the blood supply. The most common symptom is acute testicular pain." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Testicular microlithiasis
def: "The deposition of calcium phosphate microliths within the seminiferous tubules." [HPO:probinson]

name: Testicular fibrosis
def: "Formation of excess connective tissue in the testicle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Vanishing testis
def: "A condition which is considered to be due to the subsequent atrophy and disappearance in fetal life of an initially normal testis. In the presence of spermatic cord structures is evidence of the presence of the testis in early intrauterine life. When associated with a blind-ending spermatic cord, this entity is named as his absence of a testis in an otherwise normal 46XY male is usually unilateral and is assumed to be a consequence of intrauterine or perinatal torsion or infarction." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22985611]

name: Orchitis
def: "Testicular inflammation." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Retractile testis
def: "A testis that is located at the upper scrotum or lower inguinal canal and that can be made to descend completely into the scrotum without resistance by manual reduction but returns to its original position by the cremasteric reflex." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23061004, PMID:4380054]

name: Testicular atrophy
def: "Wasting (atrophy) of the testicle (the male gonad) manifested by a decrease in size and potentially by a loss of fertility." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sertoli cell-only phenotype
def: "A histological phenotype observed on testicular biopsy in which only Sertoli cells line the seminiferous tubules of the testis." [PMID:30484998]

name: Imperforate hymen
def: "A congenital disorder where the hymen (a membrane that surrounds or partially covers the external vaginal opening) does not have an opening and completely obstructs the vagina." [PMID:24822139]

name: Vaginal stricture
def: "A narrowing of the vagina owing to scar formation." []

name: Blind vagina
def: "The vagina ends in a blind pouch or sac rather than being connected to the internal genitalia." [HPO:skoehler, PMID:23730041, PMID:29768628]

name: Vaginal dryness
def: "Persistent vaginal dryness." [PMID:21702402]

name: Hematocolpos
def: "Accumulation of blood in the vagina usually due to vaginal obstruction." [PMID:29479403]

name: Hydrometrocolpos
def: "Hydrometrocolpos is an accumulation of uterine and vaginal secretions as well as menstrual blood in the uterus and vagina." [PMID:24046799]

name: Spermatocele
def: "A cystic structure arising from the epididymis, rete testis or efferent ductuli. These structures are filled with spermatozoa containing fluid that may be milky. These cysts are usually outside the tunica vaginalis and, as with hydrocele, transluminate easily." [PMID:21592287]

name: Epididymal cyst
def: "A smooth, extratesticular, spherical cyst in the head of the epididymis." [HPO:probinson, PMID:14767330]

name: Absent vas deferens
def: "Aplasia (congenital absence) of the vas deferens." [HPO:probinson]

name: Atretic vas deferens
def: "Abnormal closure or blockage of the vas deferens." []

name: Abnormal sperm mid-piece morphology
def: "A structural abnormality of the sperm mid-piece." [HPO:22198630, HPO:probinson]

name: Enuresis nocturna
def: "Enuresis occurring during sleeping hours." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Urachus fistula
def: "Persistence of the urachal canal with drainage of urine from the bladder through the persistent allantois canal to the umbilicus." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Patent urachus
def: "Persistence of the urachal canal resulting in a canal between the bladder and the umbilicus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Urachal cyst
def: "A cyst located along the allantois canal." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Fetal megacystis
def: "Fetal megacystis is an abnormally enlarged bladder identified at any gestational age." [HPO:probinson, PMID:20837325]

name: Megacystis
def: "Dilatation of the bladder postnatally." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multiple bladder diverticula
def: "Presence of a many diverticula (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urinary bladder." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Aplasia of the bladder
def: "Aplasia (absence) of the urinary bladder." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the bladder
def: "Underdevelopment of the urinary bladder." [HPO:probinson]

name: Congenital posterior urethral valve
def: "A developmental defect resulting in an obstructing membrane in the posterior male urethra." [eMedicine:1016086, HPO:probinson]

name: Penoscrotal hypospadias
def: "A severe form of hypospadias in which the urethral opening is located at the junction of the penis and scrotum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Penile hypospadias
def: "Location of the urethral opening on the inferior aspect of the penis." [HPO:curators]

name: Coronal hypospadias
def: "A mild form of hypospadias in which the urethra opens just under the corona glandis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perineal hypospadias
def: "Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the perineal region." [HPO:probinson, PMID:8097257]

name: Midshaft hypospadias
def: "Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the middle of the inferior shaft of the penis." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12371222]

name: Membranous nephropathy
def: "A type of glomerulonephropathy characterized by thickening of the basement membrane and deposition of immune complexes in the subepithelial space." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Minimal change glomerulonephritis
def: "The presence of minimal changes visible by light microscopy but flattened and fused podocyte foot processes on electron microscopy in a person with nephrotic range proteinuria." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Crescentic glomerulonephritis
def: "A type of extracapillary glomerulonephritis characterized by the formation of crescent-like cellular proliferation." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis
def: "A type of glomerulonephritis characterized by diffuse mesangial cell proliferation and the thickening of capillary walls due to subendothelial extension of the mesangium. The term membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis is often employed to denote a general pattern of glomerular injury seen in a variety of disease processes that share a common pathogenetic mechanism, rather than to describe a single disease entity" [PMID:19908070]

name: Polyuria
def: "An increased rate of urine production." [HPO:probinson]

name: Impaired renal ltubular reabsorption of chloride
def: "Any impairment of reabsorption of chloride by the kidney in order to not lose too much chloride in the urine." [PMID:25820368]

name: Renal Fanconi syndrome
def: "An inability of the tubules in the kidney to reabsorb small molecules, causing increased urinary loss of electrolytes (sodium, potassium, bicarbonate), minerals, glucose, amino acids, and water." [HPO:probinson]

name: Impaired renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate
def: "Decreased renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate." [ORCID:0000-0002-2234-4248, PMID:31474092]

name: Impaired renal concentrating ability
def: "A defect in the ability to concentrate the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Proximal renal tubular acidosis
def: "A type of renal tubular acidosis characterized by a failure of the proximal tubular cells to reabsorb bicarbonate, leading to urinary bicarbonate wasting and subsequent acidemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Non-acidotic proximal tubulopathy
def: "A type of proximal renal tubulopathy characterized by resorption defects leading to glycosuria, aminoaciduria, tubular proteinuria, renal hypophosphatemia, and urate tubular hyporeabsorption without bicarbonate loss." [HPO:probinson]

name: Stage 2 chronic kidney disease
def: "A type of chronic kidney disease with mildly reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 60-89 mL/min/1.73 m2)." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Stage 4 chronic kidney disease
def: "A type of chronic kidney disease with severely reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 15-29 mL/min/1.73 m2)." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Stage 5 chronic kidney disease
def: "A degree of kidney failure severe enough to require dialysis or kidney transplantation for survival characterized by a severe reduction in glomerular filtration rate (less than 15 ml/min/1.73 m2) and other manifestations including increased serum creatinine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Stage 1 chronic kidney disease
def: "A type of chronic kidney disease with normal or increased glomerular filtration rate (GFR at least 90 mL/min/1.73 m2)." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Stage 3 chronic kidney disease
def: "A type of chronic kidney disease with moderately reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 30-59 mL/min/1.73 m2)." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Renal cortical atrophy
def: "Atrophy of the cortex of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bilateral renal atrophy
def: "A two-sided form of atrophy of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Duplicated collecting system
def: "A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two (instead of, normally, one) pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice." [HPO:probinson]

name: Horseshoe kidney
def: "A connection of the right and left kidney by an isthmus of functioning renal parenchyma or fibrous tissue that crosses the midline." [HPO:probinson]

name: Axial malrotation of the kidney
def: "An abnormality of the normal developmental rotation of the kidney leading to an abnormal axial orientation of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Tubulointerstitial fibrosis
def: "A progressive detrimental connective tissue deposition (fibrosis) on the kidney parenchyma involving the tubules and interstitial tissue of the kidney. Tubulointerstitial injury in the kidney is complex, involving a number of independent and overlapping cellular and molecular pathways, with renal interstitial fibrosis and tubular atrophy (IF/TA) as the final common pathway. However, IF and TA are separable, as shown by the profound TA in renal artery stenosis, which characteristically has little or no fibrosis (or inflammation). For new annotations it is preferable to annotate to the specific HPO terms for Renal interstitial lfibrosis and/or Renal tubular atrophy." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19144691, PMID:22449945]

name: Unilateral renal dysplasia
def: "A unilateral form of developmental dysplasia of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bilateral renal dysplasia
