def: "A bilateral form of developmental dysplasia of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Renal tubular epithelial necrosis
def: "Coagulative necrosis of tubular epithelial cells, defined as cells with increased cytoplasmic eosinophilia and nucleus that has a condensed chromatin pattern with fuzzy nuclear contour or has barely visible nuclear basophilic staining. The extent of cortical tubular necrosis is scoredsemiquantitatively as none, mild (less than 25% tubules with necrosis), moderate (25-50 percent), and severe (over 50%)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Duplication of renal pelvis
def: "A duplication of the renal pelvis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cortical nephrocalcinosis
def: "The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal cortex (the outer portion of the kidney between the renal capsule and the renal medulla)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Medullary nephrocalcinosis
def: "The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal medulla (innermost part of the kidney)." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Renal corticomedullary cysts
def: "The presence of multiple cysts at the border between the renal cortex and medulla." [HPO:probinson]

name: Xanthine nephrolithiasis
def: "The presence of xanthine-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys." [HPO:probinson]

name: Renal interstitial fibrosis
def: "The accumulation of collagen and related extracellular matrix (ECM) molecules in the interstitium of the kidney. The interstitium is expanded by the presence of collagen that stain blue on trichrome. Tubules are not back to back, but rather separated by fibrosis and can be atrophic." [PMID:22449945]

name: Dilatation of renal calices
def: "An abnormal enlargement of the renal calices, the system of ducts of the kidney that collect urine." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Hyperechogenic kidneys
def: "An increase in amplitude of waves returned in ultrasonography of the kidney, which is generally displayed as increased brightness of the signal." [HPO:probinson, PMID:2259758, PMID:24235286]

name: Renal cortical hyperechogenicity
def: "Increased echogenecity of the kidney cortex." [PMID:24235286]

name: Polycystic kidney dysplasia
def: "The presence of multiple cysts in both kidneys." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multiple renal cysts
def: "The presence of many cysts in the kidney." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Multiple small medullary renal cysts
def: "The presence of many cysts in the medulla of the kidney." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Multicystic kidney dysplasia
def: "Multicystic dysplasia of the kidney is characterized by multiple cysts of varying size in the kidney and the absence of a normal pelvicaliceal system. The condition is associated with ureteral or ureteropelvic atresia, and the affected kidney is nonfunctional." [HPO:curators]

name: Partially duplicated kidney
def: "The presence of a partially duplicated kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased numbers of nephrons
def: "A reduction in the count of nephrons per kidney." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Nephronophthisis
def: "Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis." [Eurenomics:fschaefer]

name: Bifid ureter
def: "Incomplete duplication of the ureter." [PMID:23513084]

name: Congenital megaureter
def: "A developmental disturbance with extreme ureteral dilatation." [HPO:probinson]

name: Papillary renal cell carcinoma type 2
def: "A type of papillary renal cell carcinoma in which the papillae are covered by large eosinophilic cells with pleomorphic nuclei, prominent nucleoli, and nuclear pseudostratification." [DDD:rscott, PMID:12429790]

name: Dextrotransposition of the great arteries
def: "A type of transposition of the great arteries (TGA) in which aorta is in front of and primarily to the right of the pulmonary artery. This is the most common kind of TGA." [PMID:25082585]

name: Perimembranous ventricular septal defect
def: "A ventricular septal defect that is confluent with and involves the membranous septum and is bordered by an atrioventricular valve, not including the type 3 VSDs." [DDD:dbrown, PMID:10798413]

name: Inlet ventricular septal defect
def: "A ventricular septal defect that involves the inlet of the right ventricular septum immediately inferior to the AV valve apparatus." [DDD:dbrown, PMID:17101870]

name: Subarterial ventricular septal defect
def: "A ventricular septal defect that lies beneath the semilunar valve(s) in the conal or outlet septum." [DDD:dbrown, PMID:10798413]

name: Subaortic ventricular septal bulge
def: "A localized hypertrophy of the subaortic segment of the ventricular septum has been frequently described in elderly persons, and variously termed subaortic ventricular septal bulge (VSB), sigmoid-shaped septum, localized or discrete upper septal hypertrophy." [ORCID:0000-0001-5835-5515, PMID:25129067, PMID:9203495]

name: Left ventricular noncompaction
def: "Left ventricular noncompaction (LVNC) is defined by 3 markers: prominent left ventricular (LV) trabeculae, deep intertrabecular recesses, and the thin compacted layer." [PMID:16670098, PMID:25443708]

name: Left ventricular noncompaction cardiomyopathy
def: "Left ventricular non-compaction (LVNC) is characterized by prominent left ventricular trabeculae and deep inter-trabecular recesses. The myocardial wall is often thickened with a thin, compacted epicardial layer and a thickened endocardial layer. In some patients, LVNC is associated with left ventricular dilatation and systolic dysfunction, which can be transient in neonates." [PMID:17916581]

name: Concentric hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
def: "Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with an symmetrical and concentric pattern of hypertrophy." [HPO:probinson]

name: Asymmetric septal hypertrophy
def: "Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with an asymmetrical pattern of hypertrophy, with a predilection for the interventricular septum and myocyte disarray." [HPO:probinson, PMID:17916581]

name: Apical hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
def: "Apical hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (AHCM) is diastolic dysfunction due to abnormal stiffness of the left ventricle during diastole, with resultant impaired ventricular filling. In AHCM thickened apical segments produce a crowded, spade-shaped, small apical cavity." [ORCID:0000-0001-5835-5515, PMID:23109785, PMID:8685759]

name: Hypoplastic tricuspid valve
def: "Congenital defect characterized by underdevelopment of the tricuspid valve." [DDD:dbrown]

name: Dysplastic tricuspid valve
def: "A congenital malformation of the tricuspid valve characterized by leaflet deformation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:2007717, PMID:26059011, UToronto:chum]

name: Tricuspid valve prolapse
def: "One or more of the leaflets (cusps) of the tricuspid valve bulges back into the right atrium upon contraction of the right ventricle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ebstein anomaly of the tricuspid valve
def: "Ebstein's anomaly refers to an abnormally placed and deformed tricuspid valve characterized by apical displacement of the septal and posterior tricuspid valve leaflets, leading to atrialization of the right ventricle with a variable degree of malformation and displacement of the anterior leaflet." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:probinson]

name: Imperforate tricuspid valve
def: "A tricuspid valve that has failed to open." [DDD:dbrown, PMID:7066117]

name: Quadricuspid aortic valve
def: "The presence of an aortic valve with four instead of the normal three cusps (flaps)." [PMID:27390747]

name: Thickened aortic valve cusp
def: "An abnormally increased thickness of a leaflet of the aortic valve." [Fyler:1486, PMID:9360334]

name: Bicuspid pulmonary valve
def: "The presence of a bicuspid pulmonary valve." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aortic atherosclerotic lesion
def: "The presence of atheromas or atherosclerotic plaques in the aorta." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16818829]

name: Aortic tortuosity
def: "Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the aorta." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aortopulmonary collateral arteries
def: "Small ectopic arteries or arterial branches that connect the aorta, aortic branches and/or subclavian artery regions directly to the lung parenchyma, usually seen in conjunction with pulmonary atresia, ventricular septal defect (VSD) and/or closed ductus arteriosus." [MP:0010635, PMID:26467877]

name: Overriding aorta
def: "An overriding aorta is a congenital heart defect where the aorta is positioned directly over a ventricular septal defect, instead of over the left ventricle. The result is that the aorta receives some blood from the right ventricle, which reduces the amount of oxygen in the blood. It is one of the four conditions of the Tetralogy of Fallot. The aortic root can be displaced toward the front (anteriorly) or directly above the septal defect, but it is always abnormally located to the right of the root of the pulmonary artery. The degree of override is quite variable, with 5-95% of the valve being connected to the right ventricle." [HPO:curators]

name: Aortic rupture
def: "Tearing of the aortic wall generally associated with profuse internal bleeding." []

name: Aortopulmonary window
def: "A congenital anomaly with an abnormal connection between the aorta and the main pulmonary artery resulting in an aortopulmonary shunt." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:probinson]

name: Fusiform cerebral aneurysm
def: "A localized circumferential (i.e., bulges on all sides) dilatation or ballooning of a cerebral artery." []

name: Cerebral berry aneurysm
def: "A small, sac-like aneurysm (outpouching) of a cerebral blood vessel." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dilatation of celiac artery
def: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the celiac artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Generalized arterial tortuosity
def: "Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries affecting most or all arteries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Carotid artery tortuosity
def: "Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the carotid arteries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Vertebral artery tortuosity
def: "Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the vertebral arteries." []

name: Arteria lusoria
def: "Usually, three large arteries arise from the arch of the aorta: the brachiocephalic trunk (divided into the right common carotid artery and the right subclavian artery), the left common carotid artery, and the left subclavian artery. However, when aberrant right subclavian artery variant is present, the brachiocephalic trunk is absent and four large arteries arise from the arch of the aorta: the right common carotid artery, the left common carotid artery, the left subclavian artery, and the final one with the most distal left sided origin, the right subclavian artery, also called the arteria lusoria." [PMID:25105156]

name: Dilated left subclavian artery
def: "Abnormally increased caliber of the left subclavian artery." []

name: Premature arteriosclerosis
def: "Arteriosclerosis occurring at an age that is younger than usual." [HPO:probinson]

name: Iliac arterial calcification
def: "An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall of the iliac artery." []

name: Iliac artery aneurysm
def: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the iliac artery." [PMID:9685125]

name: Coronary artery stenosis
def: "Abnormal narrowing of the coronary artery." []

name: Intimal thickening in the coronary arteries
Coronary artery aneurysm
def: "Enlargement of the diameter (cross-section) of a coronary artery as defined by a focal dilation of a segment at least 1.5 times larger than the reference vessel." [HPO:probinson, PMID:28374180]

name: Coronary artery dissection
def: "Acute occurrence of a dissection (tear within the tunica intima and entry of blood into the tunica media) of a coronary artery." [HPO:probinson, PMID:20448134]

name: Carotid cavernous fistula
def: "An abnormal connection between a carotid artery and the cavernous sinus." [PMID:23571267]

name: Increased carotid artery intimal medial thickness
def: "An increase in the combined thickness of the intima and media of the carotid artery." [HPO:probinson, PMID:9878640]

name: Carotid artery stenosis
def: "Narrowing of the carotid arteries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Carotid artery dilatation
def: "A dilatation (balooning or bulging out of the vessel wall) of a carotid artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Carotid artery occlusion
def: "Complete obstruction of a carotid artery." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Celiac artery dissection
def: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the celiac artery wall." [PMID:32938213]

name: Radial artery aplasia
def: "Congenital absence of the radial artery." [PMID:24650137]

name: Vertebral artery aneurysm
def: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the vertebral artery ." []

name: Vertebrobasilar dolichoectasia
def: "Elongation, dilatation, and/or tortuosity of the vertebrobasilar segment. The definition of VBD includes: (i) diameter of basilar or vertebral artery over 4.5 mm; or (ii) deviation of any portion more than 10 mm from the shortest expected course; and (iii) length of basilar artery over 29.5 mm or length of intracranial vertebral artery over 23.5 mm." [PMID:24765483]

name: Renal artery atherosclerosis
def: "An atherosclerotic lesion located in the renal artery." []

name: Renal artery stenosis
def: "The presence of stenosis of the renal artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Renal artery aneurysm
def: "Increase in diameter of a segment of the renal artery that can be defined as a focal, isolated dilatation of all three layers of the arterial wall over 1.5 times the diameter of the disease-free proximal adjacent arterial segment." [PMID:25537277]

name: Anterior cerebral artery stenosis
def: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the anterior cerebral artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Middle cerebral artery stenosis
def: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the middle cerebral artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior cerebral artery stenosis
def: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the posterior cerebral artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abdominal aortic calcification
def: "An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in abdominal aorta." []

name: Medial calcification of medium-sized arteries
def: "Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of medium-sized (muscular or distributive) arteries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Medial calcification of large arteries
def: "Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of large (conduit) arteries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Severely reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
def: "A large reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle. The normal range in adults is at over 50 percent, and a severe reduction is defined as less than 30 percent." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16376782, PMID:27206819, PMID:29083812]

name: Moderately reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
def: "A medium reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle, defined as a left ventricular ejection fraction of 30-39 percent." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16376782, PMID:27206819, PMID:29083812]

name: Reduced left ventricular endsystolic diameter
def: "A lower than normal left ventricular endsystolic diameter." []

name: Ventricular preexcitation with multiple accessory pathways
def: "A form of ventricular preexcitation due to the presence of multiple accessory pathways for cardiac conduction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Wolff-Parkinson-White syndrome
def: "A disorder of the cardiac conduction system of the heart characterized by ventricular preexcitation due to the presence of an abnormal accessory atrioventricular electrical conduction pathway." [HPO:probinson]

name: Automatic atrial tachycardia
def: "Chronic supraventricular tachycardia predominantly seen in childhood." [PMID:4019927]

name: Multifocal atrial tachycardia
def: "Multifocal atrial tachycardia is a rare supraventricular arrhythmia in neonates and young infants that is characterized by multiple P waves with varying P wave morphology and is usually asymptomatic." [ORPHA:3282]

name: Prolonged QTc interval
def: "A longer than normal interval (corrected for heart rate) between the Q and T waves in the heart's cycle. Prolonged QTc can cause premature action potentials during late phase depolarizations thereby leading to ventricular arrhythmias and ventricular fibrillations." [PMID:24097136]

name: Increased QRS voltage
def: "Elevation of the voltage (height) of the QRS complex. There are several criteria in use, but the most common is the Sokolov-Lyon criterion (S wave depth in V1 + tallest R wave height in V5-V6 greater than 35 mm)." []

name: First degree atrioventricular block
def: "Delay of conduction through the atrioventricular node, which is manifested as prolongation of the PR interval in the electrocardiogram (EKG). All atrial impulses reach the ventricles." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:probinson]

name: Right bundle branch block
def: "A conduction block of the right branch of the bundle of His. This manifests as a prolongation of the QRS complex (greater than 0.12 s) with delayed activation of the right ventricle and terminal delay on the EKG." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:probinson]

name: Trifascicular block
def: "Abnormal conduction in all three divisions of the intraventricular conducting tissue." [DDD:dbrown]

name: Positive regitine blocking test
def: "A positive response to the regitine blocking test consisting of a substantial reduction in blood pressure following administration of regitine, indicative of the presence of increased levels of epinephrine and norepinephrine in the circulation, which is seen in pheochromocytoma-associated hypertension." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pulmonary artery aneurysm
def: "An aneurysm (severe localized balloon-like outward bulging) in the pulmonary artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Peripheral pulmonary artery stenosis
def: "Stenosis of a peripheral branch of the pulmonary artery." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lip telangiectasia
def: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the lips." [HPO:probinson]

name: Telangiectasia of the oral mucosa
def: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the oral mucosa." [HPO:probinson]

name: Palate telangiectasia
def: "The presence of small (ca. 0.5-1.0 mm) dilated blood vessels near the surface of the mucous membranes of the palate." [HPO:curators]

name: Tongue telangiectasia
def: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the tongue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Facial telangiectasia in butterfly midface distribution
def: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin in a butterfly midface distribution." [HPO:curators]

name: Telangiectases of the cheeks
def: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin of the cheeks." [HPO:curators]

name: Increased CSF glycine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of glycine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Decreased CSF glycine concentration
def: "Abnormally decreased levels of glycine in cerebrospinal fluid." []

name: Decreased CSF serine concentration
def: "Abnormally decreased levels of serine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Increased CSF alanine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of alanine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Decreased CSF glutamine concentration
def: "Abnormally decreased levels of glutamine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Decreased CSF arginine concentration
def: "Abnormally decreased levels of arginine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Increased CSF methionine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of methionine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Increased CSF lysine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of lysine in cerebrospinal fluid." []

name: Increased CSF valine concentration
def: "Any increased amount from normal of valine in the cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Increased CSF leucine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of leucine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Increased CSF isoleucine concentration
def: "Abnormally increased levels of isoleucine in cerebrospinal fluid." [PMID:715764]

name: Cystinuria
def: "An increased concentration of cystine in the urine." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Methioninuria
def: "Increased level of methionine in urine." [UCDenver:tjcallahan]

name: Homocystinuria
def: "An increased concentration of homocystine in the urine." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Aspartic aciduria
def: "A increased concentration of aspartic acid in the urine." [PMID:21123949, UCDenver:tjcallahan]

name: Hyperthreoninuria
def: "An increased concentration of threonine in the urine." [HPO:probinson, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

name: Hyperlysinuria
def: "An increased concentration of lysine in the urine." [HPO:probinson, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

name: Hyperglutaminuria
def: "An increased concentration of glutamine in the urine." [PMID:11283793]

name: Argininuria
def: "A increased concentration of arginine in the urine." [HPO:probinson, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

name: Hyperglycinuria
def: "An increased concentration of glycine in the urine." [HPO:gcarletti, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

name: Glutaric aciduria
def: "An increased concentration of glutaric acid in the urine." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Medium chain dicarboxylic aciduria
def: "An increase in the level of medium chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Ethylmalonic aciduria
def: "An increased concentration of ethylmalonic acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elevated urine suberic acid level
def: "An increased in the level of suberic acid in the urine above the normal range. Suberic acid is an alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is the 1,6-dicarboxy derivative of hexane." [PMID:6466694]

name: Long-chain dicarboxylic aciduria
def: "An increase in the level of long-chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Methylmalonic aciduria
def: "Increased concentration of methylmalonic acid in the urine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased level of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in urine
def: "An increase in the level of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in the urine." [PMID:15505778, PMID:23705938]

name: Increased level of methylsuccinic acid in urine
def: "An increase in the level of methylsuccinic acid in the urine." [PMID:16828325, PMID:19343532, PMID:3571488, PMID:6616873]

name: 3-hydroxydicarboxylic aciduria
def: "An increase in the level of 3-hydroxydicarboxylic acid in the urine." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Increased urine succinate level
def: "An increase in the level of succinate in the urine." [PMID:32942769]

name: Increased urinary porphobilinogen
def: "Increased concentration of porphobilinogen in the urine." [HPO:probinson, PMID:11861450]

name: Elevated urinary homogentisic acid
def: "An increased amount of homogentisic acid in the urine." [PMID:32809406]

name: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxybutyric acid
def: "An increased amount of 3-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine." []

name: Elevated urinary 4-hydroxybutyric acid
def: "An increased amount of 4-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine." []

name: Type I transferrin isoform profile
def: "Abnormal transferrin isoform profile consistent with a type I congenital disorder of glycosylation. In the traditional nomenclature for congenital disorders of glycosylation, absence of entire glycans was designated type I, and loss of one or more monosaccharides as type II." [HPO:probinson, PMID:15105360, PMID:22516080]

name: Type II transferrin isoform profile
def: "Abnormal transferrin isoform profile consistent with a type II congenital disorder of glycosylation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:15105360, PMID:22516080]

name: Decreased sialylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
def: "An reduced addition of sialic acids to O-linked glycans." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased methylcobalamin
def: "Decreased concentration of methylcobalamin. Methylcobalamin is a form of vitamin B12." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased adenosylcobalamin
def: "Decreased concentration of adenosylcobalamin. Adenosylcobalamin is one of the active forms of vitamin B12." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased blood folate concentration
def: "An elevated circulating concentration of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9." []

name: Reduced blood folate concentration
def: "A reduced circulating concentration of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased circulating guanosine concentration
def: "Increased concentration of guanosine in the blood circulation." []

name: Hyperxanthinemia
def: "An increased level of xanthine in the blood circulation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:9153281]

name: Increased circulating inosine concentration
def: "An increased concentration of inosine in the blood circulation." []

name: Increased circulating hypoxanthine concentration
def: "Elevated concentration of hypoxanthine in the blood circulation." []

name: Hypermagnesemia
def: "An abnormally increased magnesium concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypomagnesemia
def: "An abnormally decreased magnesium concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypomanganesemia
def: "A reduction below the normal concentration of manganese in the blood." []

name: Hypermanganesemia
def: "An elevation above the normal concentration of manganese in the blood." [PMID:29382362]

name: Decreased circulating copper concentration
def: "A reduced concentration of copper in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased circulating copper concentration
def: "An abnormally elevated concentration of copper in the blood circulation. This term refers to the total copper concentration." []

name: High nonceruloplasmin-bound serum copper
def: "An increased concentration of non ceruloplasmin bound copper in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased serum zinc
def: "A reduced concentration of zinc in the blood." [PMID:16518702, RGD:gthayman]

name: Increased serum zinc
def: "An increased consentration of zinc in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperkalemia
def: "An abnormally increased potassium concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyponatremia
def: "An abnormally decreased sodium concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypernatremia
def: "An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased circulating chylomicron concentration
def: "Increased plasma concentrations of chylomicrons, the large lipid droplet (up to 100 mm in diameter) of reprocessed lipid synthesized in epithelial cells of the small intestine and containing triacylglycerols, cholesterol esters, and several apolipoproteins." [HPO:probinson, MP:0009699]

name: Increased VLDL cholesterol concentration
def: "An increase in the amount of very-low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Decreased HDL cholesterol concentration
def: "An decreased concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Increased HDL cholesterol concentration
def: "An elevated concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL) in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased LDL cholesterol concentration
def: "An elevated concentration of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced circulating leukotriene C4 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of leukotriene C4 in the blood circulation." [PMID:9820300]

name: Elevated circulating phytanic acid concentration
def: "An abnormal elevation of phytanic acid." [HPO:curators]

name: Highly elevated creatine kinase
def: "An increased CPK level between 4X and 50X above the upper normal level." [Neuromics:vstraub]

name: Extremely elevated creatine kinase
def: "An increased creatine kinase level more than 50X above the upper normal level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961, Neuromics:vstraub]

name: Decreased circulating beta-2-microglobulin level
def: "Reduced concentration of beta-2-microglobulin in the blood." []

name: Atransferrinemia
def: "Absence of transferrin, a protein that transports iron, in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elevated circulating transferrin concentration
def: "An abnormally increased concentration of transferrin in the blood circulation." [PMID:19787826]

name: Hyperhistidinemia
def: "An increased concentration of histidine in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Elevated plasma branched chain amino acids
def: "An increased concentration of a branched chain amino acid in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Elevated plasma citrulline
def: "An increased concentration of citrulline in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Low plasma citrulline
def: "A decreased concentration of citrulline in the blood." [HPO:gcarletti]

name: Elevated circulating gamma-aminobutyric acid concentration
def: "An increase in the level of Gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the blood circulation." [PMID:1485027, PMID:25485164]

name: Decreased circulating GABA concentration
def: "A decrease in the level of GABA in the serum." [PMID:1485027]

name: Hypoornithinemia
def: "An abnormal decrease in ornithine in the blood." [http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

name: Hyperornithinemia
def: "Increased concentration of ornithine in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased serum bile acid concentration during pregnancy
Decreased circulating chenodeoxycholic acid concentration
def: "A reduced concentration of chenodeoxycholic acid in the blood circulation." []

name: Neonatal hyperbilirubinemia
def: "A type of hyperbilirubinemia with neonatal onset." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased total bilirubin
def: "Increased concentration of total (conjugated and unconjugated) bilirubin in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Unconjugated hyperbilirubinemia
def: "An increased amount of unconjugated (indirect) bilurubin in the blood." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent infantile hypoglycemia
def: "Recurrent episodes of decreased concentration of glucose in the blood occurring during the infantile period." [HPO:probinson]

name: Quotidian fever
def: "Fever that occurs at daily intervals." [PMID:28546530]

name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex III
def: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex IV
def: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex IV, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex II
def: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex II, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex I
def: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial ATP synthase complex
def: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial proton-transporting ATP synthase complex, which makes ATP via oxidative phosphorylation, and is sometimes described as Complex V of the electron transport chain." [HPO:probinson]

name: Secretory IgA deficiency
def: "Deficiency of secretory IgA (polymers of 2-4 IgA monomers are linked by two additional chains) and is the primary antibody response at the mucosal level, where it forms immune complexes with pathogens and allergens." [HPO:probinson, PMID:2251975]

name: Decreased CD69 upregulation upon TCR activation
def: "Reduced or impaired upregulation of CD69 on T cells after activation via the T cell receptor (TCR)." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Poliosis
def: "Circumscribed depigmentation of the hair of the head or the eyelashes." [HPO:probinson]

name: White forelock
def: "A triangular depigmented region of white hairs located in the anterior midline of the scalp." [DDD:probinson]

name: White hair
def: "Hypopigmented hair that appears white." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Fair hair
def: "A lesser degree of hair pigmentation than would otherwise be expected." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Silver-gray hair
def: "Hypopigmented hair that appears silver-gray." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sparse medial eyebrow
def: "Decreased density/number and/or decreased diameter of medial eyebrow hairs." []

name: Sparse lateral eyebrow
def: "Decreased density/number and/or decreased diameter of lateral eyebrow hairs." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal number of hair whorls
def: "More than two clockwise hair whorls." [PMID:19125436]

name: Abnormal position of hair whorl
def: "Hair growth from a single point on the scalp in any location other than lateral to the midline and close to the vertex of the skull." [PMID:19125436]

name: Frontal upsweep of hair
def: "Upward and/or sideward growth of anterior hair." [PMID:19125436]

name: Absent lower eyelashes
def: "Lack of eyelashes on the lower lid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lumbosacral hirsutism
def: "Abnormally increased hair growth in the lumbosacral region." [HPO:curators]

name: Dorsal hirsutism
def: "Abnormally increased hair growth in the lskin of the back." []

name: Frontotemporal hypertrichosis
def: "Excessive, increased hair growth located in the region of the forehead and temple." []

name: Congenital alopecia totalis
def: "Loss of all scalp hair with congenital onset." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic fifth toenail
def: "Underdeveloped nails of the fifth toes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent nail of hallux
def: "Absent nail of big toe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent fifth fingernail
def: "Absence of nail of little finger." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent thumbnail
def: "Absence of thumb nail." [HPO:probinson]

name: Excessive skin wrinkling on dorsum of hands and fingers
Intermittent jaundice
def: "Jaundice that is sometimes present, sometimes not." [HPO:curators]

name: Prolonged neonatal jaundice
def: "Neonatal jaundice refers to a yellowing of the skin and other tissues of a newborn infant as a result of increased concentrations of bilirubin in the blood. Neonatal jaundice affects over half of all newborns to some extent in the first week of life. Prolonged neonatal jaundice is said to be present if the jaundice persists for longer than 14 days in term infants and 21 days in preterm infants." [HPO:probinson]

name: Central cyanosis
def: "Generalized bluish discoloration of the body and the visible mucous membranes, which occurs due to inadequate oxygenation secondary to conditions that lead to an increase in deoxygenated hemoglobin or presence of abnormal hemoglobin." [ORCID:0000-0002-9578-0788, PMID:32644593]

name: Facial wrinkling
def: "Excessive wrinkling of the skin of the face." [HPO:curators]

name: Neonatal wrinkled skin of hands and feet
Areas of hypopigmentation and hyperpigmentation that do not follow Blaschko lines
Reticular hyperpigmentation
def: "Increased pigmentation of the skin with a netlike (reticular) pattern." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nevus flammeus of the forehead
def: "Naevus flammeus localised in the skin of the forehead." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Naevus flammeus of the eyelid
def: "Naevus flammeus localised in the skin of the eyelid." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Aplasia cutis congenita on trunk or limbs
def: "A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the trunk or the limbs." [HPO:curators]

name: Commissural lip pit
def: "A depression located at an oral commissure." [HPO:sdoelken, PMID:19125428]

name: Supraauricular pit
def: "Benign congenital lesion of the supraauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Postauricular pit
def: "Benign congenital lesion of the postauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Preauricular pit
def: "Small indentation anterior to the insertion of the ear." [HPO:sdoelken, PMID:19152421]

name: Subcutaneous spheroids
def: "Small, hard cyst-like nodules, freely moveable in the subcutis over the bony prominences of the legs and arms, which have an outer calcified layer with a translucent core on x-ray." [PMID:20847697]

name: Periarticular subcutaneous nodules
def: "Subcutaneous nodules that are located in the vicinity of joints." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nevus comedonicus
def: "A type of epidermal nevus characterized by closely arranged, dilated follicular openings with keratinous plugs resembling classical comedones." [PMID:23888253]

name: Discrete 2 to 5-mm hyper- and hypopigmented macules
Mongolian blue spot
def: "Congenital deep dermal melanosis in the sacral area." [DDD:cmoss]

name: Multiple lentigines
def: "Presence of an unusually high number of lentigines (singular: lentigo), which are flat, tan to brown oval spots." [HPO:probinson]

name: Large cafe-au-lait macules with irregular margins
def: "Large hypermelanotic macules with jagged borders." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hyperparakeratosis
def: "Abnormal keratinization of the epidermal stratum coreum (horny layer) with increased keratin formation, preservation of the nuclei in the superficial cells, and absence of the stratum granulosum." []

name: Linear arrays of macular hyperkeratoses in flexural areas
Follicular hyperkeratosis
def: "A skin condition characterized by excessive development of keratin in hair follicles, resulting in rough, cone-shaped, elevated papules resulting from closure of hair follicles with a white plug of sebum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perioral hyperkeratosis
def: "Increased thickness of the stratum corneum (the outer layer of the skin) in the skin surrounding the mouth." [PMID:32965877]

name: Streaks of hyperkeratosis along each finger onto the palm
Orthokeratotic hyperkeratosis
def: "A form of hyperkeratosis characterized by thickening of the cornified layer without retained nuclei." []

name: Gingival hyperkeratosis
def: "Hyperkeratosis of the gingiva." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Cobblestone-like hyperkeratosis
def: "The presence of verrucous, cobblestone-like papules and nodules in a region of skin that is said to have an appearance like that of cobblestones." [PMID:18809899]

name: Ichthyosis follicularis
def: "Ichthyosis follicularis is characterized by widespread non inflammatory thorn-like follicular projections. Dyskeratotic papules are most pronounced over the extensor extremities and scalp and are symmetrically distributed." [PMID:14708109, PMID:21600032]

name: Suprabasal cleavage
def: "Cleavage within the suprabasal cell layer of the epidermis, which lies directly above the basal layer and is composed of five to ten layers of cells." []

name: Stratum basale cleavage
def: "Cleavage within the epidermal keratinocytes, which is the innermost layer of the epidermis and consists of proliferating cells that give rise to the outer layers of the epidermis." []

name: Sub-lamina densa cleavage
def: "A type of blistering in which the cleavage plane of blisters is located below the lamina densa." []

name: Lamina lucida cleavage
def: "The formation of bullae (blisters) with cleavage in the lamina lucida layer of the skin." [HPO:probinson]

name: Maculopapular exanthema
def: "A skin rash that is characterized by diffuse cutaneous erythema with areas of skin elevation. It may evolve to vesicles or papules as part of a more severe clinical entity. Different degrees of angioedema with involvement of subcutaneous tissue may also appear." [PMID:19398898]

name: Morbilliform rash
def: "An exanthema consisting of widespread pink-to-red macules (flat spots of 2-10 mm in diameter) or papules (red bumps) that blanch with pressure. The macules and papules may cluster and merge to form sheets over several days." [HPO:probinson]

name: Generalized seborrheic dermatitis
def: "Seborrheic dermatitis that is not localized to any one particular region." []

name: Pyoderma
def: "Any manifestation of a skin disease associated with the production of pus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chronic furunculosis
def: "A furuncle (boil) is a skin infection involving an entire hair follicle and nearby skin tissue. Chronic furunculosis refers to recurrent episodes of furuncles, often caused by recurrent staphylococcus infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Microcolon
def: "A colon of abnormally small caliber." [PMID:3484569]

name: Lymphocytic infiltration of the colorectal mucosa
def: "Abnormally increased intraepithelial lymphocyte count. This finding may be appreciated as large numbers of surface intraepithelial lymphocytes as seen (for instance) with hematoxylin and eosin staining of a colonic biopsy sample taken during colonoscopy." [PMID:9824342]

name: Steatorrhea
def: "Greater than normal amounts of fat in the feces. This is a result of malabsorption of lipids in the small intestine and results in frothy foul-smelling fecal matter that floats." [HPO:probinson]

name: Megaduodenum
def: "Dilation and elongation of the duodenum with hypertrophy of all layers of the duodenum." []

name: Duodenitis
def: "Inflammation of the lining of the upper small intestine (duodenum)." [PMID:16679353]

name: Duodenal stenosis
def: "The narrowing or partial blockage of a portion of the duodenum." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Microvillar PAS-positive secretory granules
def: "The presenceaccumulationof periodic acid-Schiff (PAS) granules in the subapical region of small intenstinal microvilli, appearing as different kinds of vesicular/tubular structures." [PMID:26830108]

name: Microvillus inclusions
def: "The presence of vacuoles bearing centripetal microvilli in small gut villus enterocytes." [PMID:26830108]

name: Villous atrophy
def: "The enteric villi are atrophic or absent." [HPO:probinson]

name: Meckel diverticulum
def: "Meckel's diverticulum is a congenital diverticulum located in the distal ileum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Total intestinal aganglionosis
def: "A congenital defect characterized by the lack of ganglion cells in the entire intestine, i.e., the aganglionic segment comprises the entire large and small bowel." [HPO:probinson, PMID:596929]

name: Chronic gastritis
def: "A chronic form of gastritis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Atrophic gastritis
def: "Atrophic gastritis (AG) is a histopathological entity that is characterized by chronic inflammation of the gastric mucosa with loss of gastric glandular cells and replacement by intestinal-type epithelium, pyloric-type glands, and fibrous tissue." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21483628]

name: Posteriorly placed anus
def: "Posterior malposition of the anus." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Anteriorly placed anus
def: "Anterior malposition of the anus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal active colitis
def: "Focal active colitis (FAC) is characterized by focal crypt damage caused by neutrophils. FAC is characterized by an inflammatory infiltrate consisting of intraepithelial neutrophils and/or neutrophils invading the lumen of the criptae, with no other microscopic alteration of the colonic mucosa and, in particular, without the presence of signs of chronic inflammation." [PMID:21880133, PMID:29254324, PMID:9191008]

name: Pancolitis
def: "Inflammation of the entire colon." [PMID:16189424]

name: Hyperplastic colonic polyposis
def: "Presence of multiple hyperplastic polyps in the colon. Hyperplastic polyps are generally about 5 mm in size and show hyperplastic mucosal proliferation." [HPO:probinson]

name: Duodenal polyposis
def: "Presence of multiple polyps in the duodenum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cholecystitis
def: "The presence of inflammatory changes in the gallbladder." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ductal bile plugs
def: "Bile thrombi that form an obstruction (plug) in a dilated bile duct." [PMID:2028872, PMID:22152905]

name: Biliary cirrhosis
def: "Progressive destruction of the small-to-medium bile ducts of the intrahepatic biliary tree, which leads to progressive cholestasis and often end-stage liver disease." [HPO:probinson]

name: Biliary hyperplasia
def: "Hyperplasia of the biliary tree, as manifested by increased size of bile ducts, dilated lumen, and histologically by an increased number of epithelial cells or hyperplasia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bile duct polyp
def: "An elevated growth from the the mucosa of the bile duct." []

name: Bile duct proliferation
def: "Proliferative changes of the bile ducts." [HPO:probinson]

name: Biliary tract obstruction
def: "Obstruction affecting the biliary tree." [HPO:probinson]

name: Enteroviral hepatitis
def: "Inflammation of the liver due to infection with enterovirus." [PMID:15056237]

name: Chronic hepatitis due to cryptosporidium infection
def: "Chronic hepatitis associated with infection by cryptosporidia, as demonstrated (for example) by immunohistochemistry of liver tissue." [PMID:23440042]

name: Chronic active hepatitis
def: "Chronic hepatitis associated with recurrent clinical exacerbations, extrahepatic manifestations, and progression to cirrhosis." [PMID:7418593]

name: Increased hepatocellular lipid droplets
def: "An abnormal increase in the amount of intracellular lipid droplets in hepatocytes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased hepatic echogenicity
def: "Increased echogenicity of liver tissue on sonography, manifested as an increased amount of white on the screen of the sonography device." [PMID:21472065]

name: Pancreatic aplasia
def: "Aplasia of the pancreas." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Pancreatic hypoplasia
def: "Hypoplasia of the pancreas." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent aspiration pneumonia
def: "Increased susceptibility to aspiration pneumonia, defined as pneumonia due to breathing in foreign material, as manifested by a medical history of repeated episodes of aspiration pneumonia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anti-myeloperoxidase antibody positivity
def: "The presence of autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against myeloperoxidase." [ORCID:0000-0002-4095-8489, PMID:30767872]

name: Anti-U1 ribonucleoprotein antibody positivity
def: "The presence autoantibodies in the serum that react to proteins (70 Kd, A, C) that are associated with U1 RNA and form U1snRNP." [LMU:chrapp, PMID:15804705, PMID:29796907]

name: Cow milk allergy
def: "Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against cow milk protein." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
def: "The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
def: "A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
def: "The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
def: "A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
def: "A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
def: "The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination." []

name: Polyclonal elevation of IgM
def: "A heterogeneous increase in IgM immunoglobulins characterized by a diffuse band on serum electrophoresis." [PMID:11508831]

name: Decreased circulating total IgA
def: "Undetectable serum immunoglobulin A level at a value < 5 mg/dL (0.05 g/L)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Partial IgA deficiency
def: "Detectable but decreased IgA levels that are more than 2 standard deviations below normal age-adjusted means." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased serum complement C4b
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C4b in circulation." [https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/135478-overview]

name: Decreased serum complement C9
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C9 in circulation." [https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/135478-overview]

name: Decreased serum complement C8
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C8 in circulation." [PMID:8098723]

name: Decreased serum complement C6
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C6 in the blood circulation." [PMID:10632667]

name: Decreased serum complement C7
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C7 in the blood circulation." [PMID:17407100]

name: Decreased serum complement C5
def: "A reduced level of the complement component C5 in the blood circulation." [PMID:23371790]

name: Disseminated histoplasmosis
def: "Histoplasmosis infection involving multiple sites of the body. Disseminated histoplasmosis can involve various organs, including reticuloendothelial organs, gastrointestinal tract, adrenal glands, central nervous system, endovascular structures, kidney, and skin. It typically presents with systemic symptoms like fever, generalized fatigue, night sweats, weight loss, and the symptoms related to the specific organ involved. Severe disseminated disease can manifest as septic shock, multi organ failure, and ARDS." [PMID:30619685]

name: Recurrent oral herpes
def: "Recurrent episodes of oral herpes, typically characterized by blisters or ulcers on the gums, lips and/or tongue caused by herpes virus." []

name: Recurrent shingles
def: "Repeated episodes of a localized, painful cutaneous eruption related to reactivation of varicella zoster virus (VZV) and characterized by a characteristic rash in one or two adjacent dermatomes." [PMID:24113666]

name: Recurrent Staphylococcus aureus infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to Staphylococcus aureus infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Staphylococcus aureus infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent mycobacterium avium complex infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to mycobacterial avium complex infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of mycobacterial infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent Burkholderia cepacia infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to infections with Burkholderia cepacia, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection with this agent." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent Serratia marcescens infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to Serratia marcescens infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Serratia marcescens infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent Klebsiella infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to Klebsiella infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Klebsiella infection." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent E. coli infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to infections with Escherichia coli, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection with this agent." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent Haemophilus influenzae infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to Haemophilus influenzae infections as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection by Haemophilus influenzae." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent pharyngitis
def: "An increased susceptibility to pharyngitis as manifested by a history of recurrent pharyngitis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Recurrent upper and lower respiratory tract infections
def: "Increased susceptibility to upper and lower respiratory tract infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of upper and lower respiratory tract infections." []

name: Bronchiolitis
def: "Inflammation of the bronchioles." [DDD:tkuijpers]

name: Increased circulating interferon-gamma concentration
def: "An elevation in the concentration of interferon gamma measured in the blood circulation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:11335769]

name: Reduced circulating interferon gamma concentration
def: "A reduction in the concentration of interferon gamma measured in the blood circulation." []

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 21 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 21 in the blood circulation." []

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 22 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 22 in the blood circulation." []

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 17A concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 17A in the blood circulation." []

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 10 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 10 in the blood circulation." []

name: Increased circulating interleukin 10 concentration
def: "An elevation of the concentration of interleukin 10 in the blood circulation." [PMID:18424693]

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 27 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 27 in the blood circulation." []

name: Reduced circulating interleukin 23 concentration
def: "An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 23 in the blood circulation." []

name: Hyperplasia of the maxilla
def: "Abnormally increased dimension of the maxilla, especially relative to the mandible, resulting in a malocclusion or malalignment between the upper and lower teeth or in anterior positioning of the nasal base, increased convexity of the face, increased nasolabial angle, or increased width (transverse dimension of the maxilla." []

name: Aplasia of the maxilla
def: "A congenital defect characterized by absence of the Maxilla." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fibrous syngnathia
def: "Complete or nearly complete soft tissue fusion of the alveolar ridges." [PMID:19125428]

name: Narrow jaw
def: "Bigonial distance (lower facial width) more than 2 standard deviations below the mean (objective); or an apparently decreased width of the lower jaw (mandible) when viewed from the front (subjective)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125436]

name: Broad jaw
def: "Bigonial distance (lower facial width) more than 2 SD above the mean (objective); or an apparently increased width of the lower jaw (mandible) when viewed from the front (subjective)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125436]

name: Obtuse angle of mandible
def: "Abnormally flat (obtuse) angle of the mandible. The angle of the mandibular, located at the junction between the body and the ramus of the mandible, is normally close to being a right angle. This terms describes an abnormal increase of this angle such that the mandible appears flatter than normal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Trismus
def: "Limitation in the ability to open the mouth." [HPO:curators]

name: Aplastic zygomatic arch
def: "Developmental defect characterized by the absence of the zygomatic arch." [PMID:26119818]

name: Maxillozygomatic hypoplasia
def: "Hypoplasia of the maxillozygomatic complex." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the premaxilla
def: "Absence of the premaxilla, which is the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
def: "An abnormality of the premaxilla (the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla) causing it to appear relatively small in size compared to the other parts of the maxilla or other facial structures." [HPO:probinson, ORCID:0000-0001-5889-4463, PMID:19125436]

name: Hypoplasia of the frontal bone
def: "Underdevelopment of the frontal bone." [HPO:probinson]

name: Prominent occiput
def: "Increased convexity of the occiput (posterior part of the skull)." [PMID:19125436]

name: Flat occiput
def: "Reduced convexity of the occiput (posterior part of skull)." [PMID:19125436]

name: Pansynostosis
def: "Craniosynostosis of all calvarial sutures." [DDD:awilkie]

name: Bicoronal synostosis
def: "Synostosis affecting the right and the left coronal suture." [DDD:awilkie]

name: Dandy-Walker malformation
def: "A congenital brain malformation typically characterized by incomplete formation of the cerebellar vermis, dilation of the fourth ventricle, and enlargement of the posterior fossa. In layman's terms, Dandy Walker malformation is a cyst in the cerebellum (typically symmetrical) that is involved with the fourth ventricle. This may interfere with the ability to drain cerebrospinal fluid from the brain, resulting in hydrocephalus. Dandy Walker cysts are formed during early embryonic development, while the brain forms. The cyst in the cerebellum typically has several blood vessels running through it connecting to the brain, thereby prohibiting surgical removal." [HPO:probinson, PMID:26246090]

name: Enlarged cisterna magna
def: "Increase in size of the cisterna magna, one of three principal openings in the subarachnoid space between the arachnoid and pia mater, located between the cerebellum and the dorsal surface of the medulla oblongata." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cerebellopontine angle arachnoid cyst
def: "An arachnoid cyst located at the margin of the cerebellum and pons." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Vertical clivus
def: "An abnormal vertical orientation of the clivus (which normally forms a kind of slope from the sella turcica down to the region of the foramen magnum)." [HPO:curators]

name: Hypoplasia of mandible relative to maxilla
def: "Abnormally small dimension of the mandible (lower jaw) relative to the maxilla (upper jaw)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463]

name: Microretrognathia
def: "A form of developmental hypoplasia of the mandible in which the mandible is mislocalised posteriorly." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic frontal sinuses
def: "Underdevelopment of frontal sinus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent frontal sinuses
def: "Aplasia of frontal sinus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Paranasal sinus hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the paranasal sinuses." [HPO:probinson]

name: Progressive macrocephaly
def: "The progressive development of an abnormally large skull." [HPO:probinson]

name: Relative macrocephaly
def: "A relatively mild degree of macrocephaly in which the head circumference is not above two standard deviations from the mean, but appears dysproportionately large when other factors such as body stature are taken into account." [HPO:curators]

name: Postnatal macrocephaly
def: "The postnatal development of an abnormally large skull (macrocephaly)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Macrocephaly at birth
def: "The presence of an abnormally large skull with onset at birth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Primary microcephaly
def: "Head circumference below 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender at birth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Small anterior fontanelle
def: "Abnormally decreased size of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms." [HPO:probinson]

name: Premature anterior fontanel closure
def: "Early closure (ossification) of the anterior fontanelle, which generally undergoes closure around the 18th month of life." [HPO:probinson]

name: Midline skin dimples over anterior/posterior fontanelles
Wide anterior fontanel
def: "Enlargement of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms." [HPO:curators]

name: Large posterior fontanelle
def: "An enlargement of the posterior fontanelle relative to age-dependent norms." [HPO:probinson]

name: Widely patent fontanelles and sutures
def: "An abnormally increased width of the cranial fontanelles and sutures." [HPO:probinson]

name: Preauricular skin furrow
def: "A groove of the skin immediately in front of the ear." [HPO:probinson]

name: Postauricular skin tag
def: "A rudimentary tag of ear tissue often containing a core of cartilage and located just in back of the auricle (outer part of the ear)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chronic rhinitis due to narrow nasal airway
Purulent rhinitis
def: "Chronic rhinitis accompanied by pus formation." []

name: Absent nares
def: "The nostrils (the paired channels of the nose) are not present." [HPO:probinson]

name: Narrow naris
def: "Slender, slit-like aperture of the nostril." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anteverted nares
def: "Anteriorly-facing nostrils viewed with the head in the Frankfurt horizontal and the eyes of the observer level with the eyes of the subject. This gives the appearance of an upturned nose (upturned nasal tip)." [PMID:19152422]

name: Single naris
def: "The presence of only a single nostril." [PMID:19152422]

name: Enlarged naris
def: "Increased aperture of the nostril." [PMID:19152422]

name: Nasal polyposis
def: "Polypoidal masses arising mainly from the mucous membranes of the nose and paranasal sinuses. They are freely movable and nontender overgrowths of the mucosa that frequently accompany allergic rhinitis." [HPO:sdoelken, PMID:18728843]

name: Wide nasal bridge
def: "Increased breadth of the nasal bridge (and with it, the nasal root)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152422]

name: Prominent nasal bridge
def: "Anterior positioning of the nasal root in comparison to the usual positioning for age." [PMID:19152422]

name: Short nasal bridge
def: "Decreased superior-inferior length of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose." []

name: Depressed nasal bridge
def: "Posterior positioning of the nasal root in relation to the overall facial profile for age." [PMID:19152422]

name: Narrow nasal bridge
def: "Decreased width of the bony bridge of the nose." [PMID:19152422]

name: Long nasal bridge
def: "Increased superior-inferior length of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose." []

name: Aplasia of the nose
def: "Complete absence of all nasal structures." [HPO:probinson]

name: Underdeveloped nasal alae
def: "Thinned, deficient, or excessively arched ala nasi." [PMID:19152422]

name: Wide nasal base
def: "Increased distance between the attachments of the alae nasi to the face." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152422]

name: Narrow nasal base
def: "Decreased distance between the attachments of the alae nasi to the face." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152422]

name: Deviated nasal septum
def: "Positioning of the nasal septum to the right or left in contrast to the normal midline position of the nasal septum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short nasal septum
def: "Reduced superior to inferior length of the nasal septum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nasal septum perforation
def: "A full-thickness defect of the nasal septum." [PMID:30725893]

name: Thick nasal septum
def: "Abnormally increased thickness of the nasal septum." [HPO:curators]

name: Midline nasal groove
def: "An abnormal groove on the midline of the nose that may extend to the nasal tip." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Bifid nose
def: "Visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal bridge, ridge and tip." [PMID:19152422]

name: Widow's peak
def: "Frontal hairline with bilateral arcs to a low point in the midline of the forehead." [PMID:19125436]

name: Xerostomia
def: "Dryness of the mouth due to salivary gland dysfunction." [HPO:probinson]

name: Upper eyelid edema
def: "Edema in the region of the upper eyelid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Blepharochalasis
def: "Blepharochalasis is characterized by recurrent, non-painful, nonerythematous episodes of eyelid edema. It has been divided into hypertrophic and atrophic forms. In the hypertrophic form recurrent edema results in orbital fat herniation through a weakened orbital septum. Most patients who have blepharochalasis present in an atrophic condition with atrophy of redundant eyelid skin and superior nasal fat pads." [PMID:3207663]

name: Pyrimidine-responsive megaloblastic anemia
def: "A type of megaloblastic anemia that improves upon administration of pyrimidine supplements such as uridylic acid and cytidylic acid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thiamine-responsive megaloblastic anemia
def: "A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of thiamine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Folate-responsive megaloblastic anemia
def: "A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of folate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Folate-unresponsive megaloblastic anemia
def: "A type of megaloblastic anemia that does not improve upon administration of folate. Since vitamin B12 acts by promoting recycling of folate, administration of vitamin B12 also does not improve this type of anemia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chronic neutropenia
def: "Neutropenia with an absolute neutrophil count (ANC) less than 1,500,000,000/L lasting for more than 3 months." [PMID:23953336]

name: Congenital agranulocytosis
def: "Congenital onset of a marked decrease in the number of granulocytes." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased helper T cell proportion
def: "Reduced proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive helper T cells
def: "A decreased proportion of circulating CD4-positive helper T cells relative to total T cell count." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent circulating B cells
def: "Complete lack of mature B cells, that is, of B cells that have left the bone marrow." [HPO:probinson]

name: Severe B lymphocytopenia
def: "A severe form of B lymphocytopenia in which the count of B cells is very low or absent." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased proportion of CD3-positive T cells
def: "Any abnormality in the proportion of CD3-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells." []

name: Increased proportion of HLA DR+ T cells
def: "An elevated proportion of T cells that express human leukocyte antigen (HLA)-DR. HLA-DR is an MHC class II cell surface receptor that presents antigens (peptides of at least 9 amino acids), thereby constituting a ligand for the T-cell receptor. HLA-DR can be upregulated in response to immune stimulation." [PMID:11531958]

name: Reduced proportion of mucosal-associated invariant T cells
def: "A decreased proportion of circulating mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT) cells relative to total T cell count." [PMID:32161190]

name: Increased proportion autoreactive unresponsive CD21-/low B cells
def: "Increased proportion relative to B-lymphocytes of a subset of B lymphocytes characterized by dim/low levels of CD21, i.e., CD21-/low, in flow cytometry, and additionally enriched in autoreactive clones as determined for instance by clonse showing rheumatoid factor (anti-IgG) reactivity and antibodies recognizing cytoplasmic and to a lesser extent nuclear structures." [PMID:26119182]

name: Absent natural killer cells
def: "Lack of natural killer cells, a type of lymphocyte in the innate immune system that contains cytoplasmic granzymes, i.e., small granules with perforin and proteases that allow natural killer cells to form pores in the cell membrane of the target cell through which the granzymes and associated molecules can enter, inducing apoptosis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased neutrophil mitochondria
def: "An increased number of mitochondria detected in neutrophils." [PMID:6155073]

name: Hypersegmentation of neutrophil nuclei
def: "An excessive division of the lobes of the nucleus of a neutrophil." [HPO:probinson]

name: Giant neutrophil granules
def: "The presence of abnormally large granules in neutrophils. This finding can be appreciated on a peripheral blood smear. The finding is characteristic of Chediak Higashi syndrome. The giant granules are derived from azurophil granules, whereas peroxidase-negative granules are not involved in their formation." [PMID:9665278]

name: Increased neutrophil ribosomes
def: "An increased number of ribosomes detected in neutrophils." [PMID:6155073]

name: Hyposegmentation of neutrophil nuclei
def: "Hyposegmented (hypolobulated) or bilobed neutrophil nuclei." [DDD:probinson]

name: Absence of alpha granules
def: "A lack of platelet alpha granules. This typically results in the grey appearance of platelets in giemsa stained blood smears." [HPO:probinson, PMID:3877532]

name: Reduced platelet alpha granules
def: "A reduced number of platelet alpha granules." [PMID:31217188]

name: Reduced platelet dense granules
def: "Decreased number of platelet dense granules, a type of platelet organelle." [PMID:31217188]

name: Absent platelet dense granules
def: "Lack of platelet dense granules, a type of platelet organelles." [PMID:11809908]

name: Cerebellar hemangioblastoma
def: "A hemangioblastoma of the cerebellum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent earlobe
def: "Absence of fleshy non-cartilaginous tissue inferior to the tragus and incisura." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152421]

name: Small earlobe
def: "Reduced volume of the earlobe." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19152421]

name: Prominent stem of antihelix
def: "Increased protrusion of the antihelical ridge, proximal to its bifurcation, relative to the prominence of the helix." [PMID:19152421]

name: Stahl ear
def: "The presence of a supernumerary, i.e. third, crus of the helix in the helix, arising at or above the normal bifurcation of the antihelix." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Prominent inferior crus of antihelix
def: "Increased protrusion of the inferior crus relative to the prominence of the antihelix stem." [HPO:19152421]

name: Underdeveloped superior crus of antihelix
def: "Decreased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem." [PMID:19152421]

name: Prominent superior crus of antihelix
def: "Increased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem." [PMID:19152421]

name: Low-set, posteriorly rotated ears
def: "Ears that are low-set (HP:0000369) and posteriorly rotated (HP:0000358)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Increased incisura length
def: "The length of the incisura from the upper to lower border is greater than that observed in the average population." [PMID:20082456]

name: Cleft at the superior portion of the pinna
Underdeveloped tragus
def: "Decreased posterolateral protrusion of the tragus." [PMID:19152421]

name: Absent tragus
def: "Lack of convexity or prominence of the contour of the ridge between the bottom of the incisura and the confluence of the ascending helix and crus helix." [PMID:19152421]

name: Absence of acoustic reflex
def: "Absence of the acoustic reflex, an involuntary contraction of the stapedius muscle that occurs in response to high-intensity sound stimuli." [HPO:probinson]

name: Otosclerosis
def: "In otosclerosis, a callus of bone accumulates on the stapes creating a partial fixation. This limits the movement of the stapes bone, which results in hearing loss." [HPO:probinson, PMID:15931303]

name: Absent malleus
def: "Aplasia of the malleus." [DDD:dfitzpatrick]

name: Aplasia of the semicircular canal
def: "Absence of the semicircular canal." [DDD:dfitzpatrick]

name: Hypoplasia of the semicircular canal
def: "Underdevelopment of the semicircular canal." [DDD:dfitzpatrick]

name: Panhypopituitarism
def: "A pituitary functional deficit affecting all the anterior pituitary hormones (growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone, luteinizing hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, and prolactin)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12466332]

name: Adrenocorticotropic hormone deficiency
def: "A reduced ability to secrete adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), a hormone that stimulates the adrenal cortex to secrete of glucocorticoids such as cortisol." [DDD:spark]

name: Gonadotropin deficiency
def: "A reduced ability to secrete gonadotropins, which are protein hormones secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary gland, including the hormones follitropin (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH)." [DDD:spark]

name: Dexamethasone-suppressible primary hyperaldosteronism
def: "A form of primary hyperaldosteronism in which the overproduction of aldosterone can be suppressed by the administration of dexamethasone." [DDD:spark, HPO:probinson]

name: Glucocortocoid-insensitive primary hyperaldosteronism
def: "A form of primary hyperaldosteronism in which the overproduction of aldosterone cannot be suppressed by the administration of dexamethasone or similar glucocorticoids." [DDD:spark, HPO:probinson]

name: Spontaneous neonatal pneumothorax
def: "Pneumothorax occurring neonatally without traumatic injury to the chest or lung." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hemosiderin-laden macrophages in bronchoalveolar fluid
def: "Hemosiderin-laden macrophages (HLM) in bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) fluid were originally known as adiagnostic biomarker of alveolar hemorrhage, but have also been observed in idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) with histopathological pattern of usual interstitial pneumonia (UIP)." [LMU:mgriese, PMID:16871595, PMID:23678356, PMID:25515792, PMID:28166761]

name: Bifid epiglottis
def: "A midline anterior-posterior cleft of the epiglottis that involves at least two-thirds of the epiglottic leaf. It is a useful feature for clinical diagnosis because it appears to be very rare in syndromes other than Pallister-Hall-Syndrome and is also rare as an isolated malformation." [HPO:curators]

name: Bowing of the vocal cords
def: "Bowing (abnormal curvature) of the vocal folds." [HPO:probinson]

name: Pulmonary arterial hypertension with lack of acute response to NO challenge
def: "A form of pulmonary arterial hypertension with lack of adequate hemodynamic response to NO challenge (adequate response is defined as a reduction of mean pulmonary artery pressure (mPAP) of at least 10 mmHg to reach an absolute value of mPAP 40 mmHg or less with an increased or unchanged cardiac output (CO) in response to inhaled nitric oxide at 10-20 ppm)." [PMID:15939821]

name: Dermal sinus tract
def: "A dermal sinus tract is an abnormality present at birth over the dorsal midline where an abnormal epithelialized connection from the skin tracks inwards towards the spine, most commonly seen in the lumbosacral region." [PMID:31484633]

name: Aplasia of the falx cerebri
def: "A developmental defect characterized by aplasia of the Falx cerebri." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lipomyelomeningocele
def: "A type of spinal dysraphism presenting as a subcutaneous fatty mass, that is, a spinal defect associated with lipomatous tissue, and covered by skin. The most usual location for lipomyelomeningocele is at the gluteal cleft." []

name: Aplasia of the olfactory bulb
def: "Lack of formation (congenital absence) of the olfactory bulb." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:27863011]

name: Encephalomalacia
def: "Encephalomalacia is the softening or loss of brain tissue after cerebral infarction, cerebral ischemia, infection, craniocerebral trauma, or other injury." [PhenoTips:CHum]

name: Porencephalic cyst
def: "A cavity within the cerebral hemisphere, filled with cerebrospinal fluid, that communicates directly with the ventricular system." [HPO:probinson, PMID:9279052]

name: Abnormal diffusion weighted cerebral MRI morphology
def: "A diffusion abnormality observed in diffusion-weighted magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brain. Molecular diffusion refers to the notion that any type of molecule in a fluid (eg, water) is randomly displaced as the molecule is agitated by thermal energy. Restricted diffusion of water appears bright on diffusion-weighted images." [ORCID:0000-0002-7440-8864, PMID:11058626]

name: Pontocerebellar atrophy
def: "Atrophy affecting the pons and the cerebellum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal T2 hypointense brainstem lesion
def: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Focal T2 hyperintense brainstem lesion
def: "A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Hypoplasia of the midbrain
def: "A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of the mesencephalon." [PMID:25561519]

name: Thinning of the substantia nigra pars compacta
def: "Reduced volume of pars compacta of the substantia nigra." [PMID:26209139]

name: Substantia nigra hypointensity on susceptibility-weighted imaging
def: "Hypointence (dark) appearance of the substantia nigra inmagnetic resonance imaging using susceptibility weighted imaging (SWI)." []

name: Enlarged sylvian cistern
def: "An increase in size of the subarachnoid space associated with the lateral cerebral sulcus (Sylvian fissure)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dilated third ventricle
def: "An increase in size of the third ventricle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Colpocephaly
def: "Colpocephaly is an anatomic finding in the brain manifested by occipital horns that are disproportionately enlarged in comparison with other parts of the lateral ventricles." [PMID:4058748]

name: Choroid plexus cyst
def: "A cyst occurring within the choroid plexus within a cerebral ventricle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Periventricular ribbonlike heterotopia
def: "Heterotopia that forms a continuous wavy line along the ventricular wall." [COST:neuromig, PMID:22315185]

name: Periventricular nodular heterotopia
def: "Nodules of heterotopia along the ventricular walls. There can be a single nodule or a large number of nodules, they can exist on either or both sides of the brain at any point along the higher ventricle margins, they can be small or large, single or multiple." [COST:neuromig, PMID:22427329]

name: Focal polymicrogyria
def: "Polymicrogyria affecting one or multiple small areas of the cerebral cortex." [COST:neuromig, PMID:20198472, PMID:22427329]

name: Frontal polymicrogyria
def: "A type of polymicrogyria with a gradient of severity (anterior more severe than posterior) extending from frontal poles posteriorly to precentral gyrus and inferiorly to frontal operculum." [COST:neuromig, PMID:20301504]

name: Microlissencephaly
def: "Severe microcephaly and lissencephaly with granular surfaces with immature cortical plate, reduced in thickness, with focal polymicrogyria and immature small neurons with rare processes, intermingled with a considerable number of glial elements." [PMID:8779318]

name: Type II lissencephaly
def: "A form of lissencephaly characterized by an uneven cortical surface with a so called 'cobblestone' appearace. There are no distinguishable cortical layers." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal lissencephaly
def: "A congenital absence of the convolutions of the cerebral cortex and a poorly formed sylvian fissure that affects a particular part of the cortex." [KI:phemming]

name: 4-layered lissencephaly
def: "A form of lissencephaly in which the cortex is thickened and has four more or less disorganized layers rather than six normal layers resulting from incomplete neuronal migration during brain development. At neuropathological examination, a 4-layered cortex consists of an upper molecular layer, a second thin cellular layer containing pyramidal neurons usually observed in layer V, a third pale poorly cellular layer and a fourth thick deep layer made up of neurons which had failed to migrate.
