def: "Loss of elasticity of the upper and lower eyelids causing the skin to sag and bulge." [HPO:probinson]

name: Symblepharon
def: "A partial or complete adhesion of the palpebral conjunctiva of the eyelid to the bulbar conjunctiva of the eyeball." [GOC:MG, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symblepharon]

name: Conjunctival icterus
def: "Conjunctival icterus is a condition where there is yellowing of the whites of the eyes. This is most commonly seen in patients who have liver disease." []

name: Chemosis
def: "Edema (swelling) of the bulbar conjunctiva." [HPO:probinson]

name: Conjunctival whitish salt-like deposits
def: "The presence of whitish deposits in the conjunctiva resembling salt. May be related to calcinosis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Conjunctival dermolipoma
def: "A conjuctival lesion composed of adipose tissue and dense connective tissue. Such choristomas of dermal elements are normally found at the outer canthus, and have a gelatinous appearance. Classically, there is an indistinct posterior border (with the lesion frequently extending into the orbit) and a well-demarcated anterior border several millimetres posterior to the limbus." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Corneal pterygium
def: "Corneal pterygium is an ocular surface disease characterized mainly by a wing-shaped growth of limbal and conjunctival tissue over the adjacent cornea." [PMID:34104871]

name: Spontaneous conjunctival filtering bleb
def: "Avascular cystic elevations of the superior conjunctiva not related to ocular surgery or trauma." [PMID:24768550, PMID:8749053]

name: Dacryocystitis
def: "Inflammation of the nasolacrimal sac." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ankyloglossia
def: "Short or anteriorly attached lingual frenulum, associated with limited mobility of the tongue." [PMID:19125428]

name: Short lingual frenulum
def: "The presence of an abnormally short lingual frenulum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Accessory oral frenulum
def: "Extra fold of tissue extending from the alveolar ridge to the inner surface of the upper or lower lip." [PMID:19125428]

name: Midline notch of upper alveolar ridge
Alveolar process hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the alveolar process (also known as alveolar bone)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Fragile teeth
def: "A tendency of teeth to fracture as manifested by a history of repeated fracture of the dental enamel without adequate trauma." []

name: Periapical bone loss
def: "Radiolucency (reflecting a reduction in the bony substance) around the apex (the tip of the dental root)." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Cleft maxillary alveolus
def: "Alveolar cleft is a tornado-shaped bone defect in the maxillary arch. Alveolar cleft occurs in response to divergence from normal development during frontonasal prominence growth, contact, and fusion. The most common alveolar portion of the cleft is located between the lateral incisor and the canine." []

name: Oral mucosa nodule
def: "A palpable, solid lesion greater than 5mm in diameter. that is located in the mucosa of the mouth." []

name: Oral synechia
def: "Fibrous band between the mucosal surfaces of the upper and lower alveolar ridges." [PMID:19125428]

name: Oral ulcer
def: "Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Erosion of oral mucosa
def: "Loss of the superficial layer of the oral mucosa usually resulting in a shallow or crusted lesion." []

name: Downturned corners of mouth
def: "A morphological abnormality of the mouth in which the angle of the mouth is downturned. The oral commissures are positioned inferior to the midline labial fissure." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125428]

name: Asymmetry of the mouth
def: "The presence of an asymmetric mouth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Chapped lip
def: "Cracking, fissuring, and peeling of the skin of the lips." []

name: Lip fissure
def: "A severe crack in a lip. A lip fissure may be painful, may bleed and often is a recurring manifestation." []

name: Swollen lip
def: "Enlargement of the lip typically due to fluid buildup or inflammation." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Wide mouth
def: "Distance between the oral commissures more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased width of the oral aperture (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Narrow mouth
def: "Distance between the commissures of the mouth more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the oral aperture (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Prominent palatine ridges
def: "Increased size and/or number of soft tissue folds on the palatal side of the maxillary alveolar ridge." [PMID:19125428]

name: Prominent median palatal raphe
def: "Unusual prominence of the median palatal raphe, which is the ridge formed by the fusion of the two plates of the skull that form the hard palate." [HPO:curators]

name: Palate fistula
def: "A fistula which connects the oral cavity and the pharyngeal area via the aspects of the soft palate." [HPO:probinson]

name: Infection associated neutropenia
def: "Transient neutropenia caused by an infection, such as with a virus, bacteria or protozoan." [PMID:23953336]

name: Absence of CD8-positive T cells
def: "Lack of detectible CD8-positive T cells" []

name: Decreased CD4:CD8 ratio
def: "An abnormal reduction of the relative proportion of CD4+ to CD8+ T cells." [PMID:29095912]

name: Increased CD4:CD8 ratio
def: "An abnormal elevation of the relative proportion of CD4+ to CD8+ T cells." []

name: Decreased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells
def: "An abnormally decreased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells." []

name: Elevated proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative, alpha-beta regulatory T cells
def: "An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative (double negative or DN) alpha-beta regulatory T cells (Tregs) as compared to total number of T cells." []

name: Reduced proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative, alpha-beta regulatory T cells
def: "An abnormally decreased proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative (double negative or DN) alpha-beta regulatory T cells (Tregs) as compared to total number of T cells." []

name: Increased proportion of transitional B cells
def: "An elevation in the normal proportion of transitional B cells (CD19+/CD38high/IgMhigh) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. B cells originate from precursors in the bone marrow, and the first cells which migrate to the peripheral blood have been classified as transitional B cells." [HPO:probinson]

name: Leukocyte inclusion bodies
def: "The presence of intraceullar inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in leukocytes." []

name: Absent neutrophil lactoferrin
def: "The absence of lactoferrin in neutrophil granules, which could be caused by either an isolated failure of synthesis of this protein (or the production of an antigenically unrecognizable form of lactoferrin) or a complete deficiency of specific granule production." [PMID:6155073]

name: Impaired oxidative burst
def: "In the NBT test, neutrophils change the colorless compound NBT into a compound with a deep blue color. If this test is negative (i.e., no blue color is produced), then this indicates a defect in superoxide-generating NADPH oxidase activity with inability to efficiently kill phagocytized bacteria." [HPO:probinson]

name: Impaired neutrophil chemotaxis
def: "An impairment of the migration of neutrophils towards chemoattractants as part of the innate immune response" []

name: Medulloepithelioma
def: "A primitive neuroectodermal tumor that originates from the cells of the embryonic medullary canal." [PMID:17566306]

name: Overfolding of the superior helices
def: "A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a greater degree than normal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Underfolded superior helices
def: "A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a lesser degree than normal." [HPO:probinson]

name: Congenital stapes ankylosis
def: "A form of stapes ankylosis with congenital onset." [HPO:probinson]

name: Incomplete partition of the cochlea type II
def: "With incomplete partition II, the cochlea consists of 1.5 turns; the apical and middle cochlea turns are undifferentiated and form a cystic apex. The vestibule is normal while the vestibular aqueduct is always enlarged. Developmental arrest occurs at the seventh week of gestation." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21849370, PMID:34698066]

name: Reduced circulating prolactin concentration
def: "A reduced level of prolactin in the blood circulation. Prolactin is a protein hormone that is secreted by lactotrophs in the anterior pituitary and that stimulates mammary gland development and milk production." [DDD:spark, HPO:probinson, PMID:23378139]

name: Aplasia of the epiglottis
def: "Absence of the epiglottis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplasia of the epiglottis
def: "Hypoplasia of the epiglottis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent inner and outer dynein arms
def: "Complete absence of the dynein arms of respiratory motile cilia, that is, absence of the inner and the outer dynein arms, which normally are situated inside and outside of the peripheral microtubules of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19606528]

name: Interhypothalamic Adhesion
def: "An abnormal parenchymal band connecting the medial margins of the left and right hypothalami across the third ventricle." [PMID:24874532]

name: Hypothalamic atrophy
def: "Partial or complete wasting (loss) of hypothalamus tissue that was once present." []

name: Fusion of the left and right thalami
def: "A developmental defect characterized by fusion of the left and right halves of the thalamus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thalamic edema
def: "Swelling within the thalamus due to the accumulation of fluid." []

name: Dysgenesis of the thalamus
def: "Structural abnormality of the thalamus related to defective development." []

name: Thalamic calcification
def: "Calcium deposition in the thalamus." []

name: Ubiquitin-positive cerebral inclusion bodies
def: "Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates that show positive staining with antibodies against ubiquitin within cells of the brain." [HPO:probinson]

name: Rosenthal fibers
def: "Thick, elongated, worm-like or corkscrew eosinophilic bundle that are found on H&E staining of the brain in the presence of long standing gliosis, occasional tumors, and some metabolic disorders." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Neurofibrillary tangles
def: "Pathological protein aggregates formed by hyperphosphorylation of a microtubule-associated protein known as tau, causing it to aggregate in an insoluble form." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Lafora bodies
def: "An intraneuronal inclusion body composed of acid mucopolysaccharides." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Hemimegalencephaly
def: "Enlargement of all or parts of one cerebral hemisphere." [HPO:probinson, PMID:17416820]

name: Neuronal loss in the cerebral cortex
Progressive leukoencephalopathy
def: "Leukoencephalopathy that gets more severe with time." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cavum septum pellucidum
def: "If the two laminae of the septum pellucidum are not fused then a fluid-filled space or cavum is present. The cavum septum pellucidum is present at birth but usually obliterates by the age of 3 to 6 months. It is up to 1cm in width and the walls are parallel. It is an enclosed space and is not part of the ventricular system or connected with the subarachnoid space." [HPO:curators]

name: Absent hippocampal commissure
def: "Absence of the fibers that connect the contralateral hippocampi via the crura of the fornix and run beneath the posterior portion of the corpus callosum." [PMID:28250456]

name: Hypoplastic hippocampus
def: "Underdevelopment of the hippocampus." []

name: Dysgenesis of the hippocampus
def: "Structural abnormality of the hippocampus related to defective development." []

name: Hippocampal atrophy
def: "Partial or complete wasting (loss) of hippocampus tissue that was once present." []

name: Reduced amygdala volume
def: "A decrease in the volume (size) of the amygdyla." []

name: Thickened superior cerebellar peduncle
def: "Increased width of the superior cerebellar peduncle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Elongated superior cerebellar peduncle
def: "Increased length of the superior cerebellar peduncle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Rhombencephalosynapsis
def: "Rhombencephalosynapsis is a rare brain malformation defined by midline fusion of the cerebellar hemispheres with partial or complete loss of the intervening vermis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3194-8625, PMID:22451504]

name: Olivopontocerebellar atrophy
def: "Neuronal degeneration in the cerebellum, pontine nuclei, and inferior olivary nucleus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dysplastic gangliocytoma of the cerebellum
def: "It is a rare, slowly growing tumor of the cerebellum, a gangliocytoma sometimes considered to be a hamartoma, characterized by diffuse hypertrophy of the granular layer of the cerebellum." [PMID:11073535]

name: Cerebellar edema
def: "Swelling from fluid accumulation (serous fluid infiltration into the interstitial space) in the cerebellum." []

name: Enlarged cerebellum
def: "An abnormally increased size of the cerebellum compared to other brain structures." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior predominant subcortical band heterotopia
def: "Longitudinal bands of gray matter located deep to the cerebral cortex and separated from it by a thin layer of normal appearing white matter visible along the occipital cortex." [COST:neuromig]

name: Bilateral perisylvian polymicrogyria
def: "A type of perisylvian polymicrogyria that affects both sides of the brain." [COST:neuromig, PMID:20301504]

name: Partial agenesis of the corpus callosum
def: "A partial failure of the development of the corpus callosum." [HPO:curators]

name: Hypodysplasia of the corpus callosum
def: "Developmental defect characterized by a small and malformed corpus callosum." []

name: Inferior cerebellar vermis hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the inferior portion of the vermis of cerebellum." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16580298]

name: Occipital cortical atrophy
def: "Atrophy of the occipital cortex." [HPO:probinson]

name: Parietal cortical atrophy
def: "Atrophy of the parietal cortex." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cerebral cortical hemiatrophy
def: "Atrophy of one side of the brain, characterized by findings including thinning of the cerebral cortex, reduced volume of the cerebral white matter with abnormal myelination, and enlargement of the ispilateral fourth ventricle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Frontal cortical atrophy
def: "Atrophy of the frontal cortex." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased motor nerve conduction velocity
def: "A type of decreased nerve conduction velocity that affects the motor neuron." [HPO:probinson]

name: Motor conduction block
def: "Blockade of impulses at a focal site along the course of a motor axon." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased sensory nerve conduction velocity
def: "Reduced speed of conduction of the action potential along a sensory nerve." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased distal sensory nerve action potential
def: "A reduction in the amplitude of sensory nerve action potential in distal nerve segments. This feature is measured by nerve conduction studies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Nail-biting
def: "Habitual biting of one's own fingernails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Poor eye contact
def: "Difficulty in looking at another person in the eye." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced use of typical gestures
def: "A diminished use of typical non-verbal conversational gestures such as shaing the head to indicate no or nodding the head to indicate yes." [ORCID:0000-0002-4422-1708, PMID:21182208]

name: Hand-leading gestures
def: "Taking other people by the hand to places they wish them to move to or taking someone's hand to objects they want them to manipulate." [ORCID:0000-0002-4422-1708, PMID:25388062]

name: Episodic hemiplegia
def: "Transient episodes of weakness of the arm, leg, and in some cases the face on one side of the body." [HPO:probinson]

name: Episodic quadriplegia
def: "Intermittent episodes of paralysis of all four limbs." [HPO:probinson]

name: Upper limb postural tremor
def: "A type of tremors that is triggered by holding an arm in a fixed position." [HPO:probinson]

name: Truncal titubation
def: "Tremor of the trunk in an anterior-posterior plane at 3-4 Hz." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intention tremor
def: "A type of kinetic tremor that occurs during target directed movement is called intention tremor. That is, an oscillatory cerebellar ataxia that tends to be absent when the limbs are inactive and during the first part of voluntary movement but worsening as the movement continues and greater precision is required (e.g., in touching a target such as the patient's nose or a physician's finger)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16344298]

name: Upper limb dysmetria
def: "A lack of coordination of arm movement manifested by undershoot or overshoot of the intended position of the arm." [HPO:mtaboada, PMID:20301629]

name: Lower limb dysmetria
def: "A lack of coordination of leg movement manifested by undershoot or overshoot of the intended position of the leg." [HPO:mtaboada, PMID:25573808]

name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with forced thinking
def: "A focal cognitive seizure with forced thinking characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure." [PMID:28276060]

name: Focal aware sensory seizure with auditory features
def: "A type of focal sensory seizure with auditory features during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure." [PMID:28276060]

name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
def: "A focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation / nausea / vomiting / other gastrointestinal phenomena characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure." [PMID:28276060]

name: Deja vu aura
def: "A subjective feeling that an experience which is occurring for the first time has been experienced before." [HPO:probinson]

name: Atypical absence status epilepticus
def: "Atypical absence status epilepticus is a type of generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma that is semiologically a prolonged atypical absence seizure." [HPO:jalbers]

name: Semantic dementia
def: "A progressive loss of the ability to remember the meaning of words, faces and objects." [ICM:PCaroppo, PMID:24966676]

name: EEG with continuous slow activity
def: "EEG showing diffuse slowing without interruption." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with occipital slowing
def: "Slowing in occipital areas of the scalp EEG." [HPO:jalbers]

name: Triceps hyperreflexia
def: "Increased intensity of the triceps reflex." [PMID:30285397]

name: Convergence excess esotropia
def: "An intermittent esotropia with binocular single vision present at distance fixation but esotropia on accommodation for near fixation. Usually associated with hypermetropia but patients can be emmetropic and rarely myopic. Associated with a high accommodative convergence/accommodation (AC/A) ratio." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Infantile constant exotropia
def: "Constant exotropia occurring before 6 months of age.; often associated with a large angle of deviation and ocular/CNS abnormalities." [UManchester:psergouniotis]

name: Electronegative electroretinogram
def: "A dark-adapted bright flash electroretinogram in which the b-wave that is of markedly lower amplitude than the associated a-wave (source: Holder GE., Inherited Chorioretinal Dystrophies: A Textbook and Atlas; 2014; p.17; ISBN 978-3-540-69466-3)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Reduced amplitude of dark-adapted bright flash electroretinogram a-wave
def: "An abnormal reduction in the amplitude of the a-wave." []

name: Nuclear pulverulent cataract
def: "A type of nuclear cataract involving congenital dust-like (pulverulent) opacity of the embryonal and fetal nucleus." [HPO:probinson, PMID:10634616, PMID:14059288]

name: Dense posterior cortical cataract
def: "A type of posterior cortical cataract characterized by dense lenticular opacities." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cortical pulverulent cataract
def: "A type of cataract characterized by punctate, dust-like opacities within the cortical region of the lens." [HPO:probinson]

name: Patchy atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium
def: "Wasting (atrophy) of the retinal pigment epithelium present in small, isolated areas." []

name: Foveal hyperpigmentation
def: "Increased amount of pigmentation in the fovea centralis." [HPO:probinson]

name: Peripapillary atrophy
def: "Thinning in the layers of the retina and retinal pigment epithelium around the optic nerve." [PMID:20920826]

name: Bilateral single transverse palmar creases
def: "The distal and proximal transverse palmar creases are merged into a single transverse palmar crease on both hands." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent palmar crease
def: "The absence of the major creases of the palm (distal transverse crease, proximal transverse crease, or thenar crease)." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125433]

name: Decreased palmar creases
def: "Poorly defined or shallow palmar creases." [PMID:19125433]

name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of the hallux
Midclavicular hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the middle portion of the clavicle." [HPO:probinson]

name: 11 pairs of ribs
def: "Presence of only 11 pairs of ribs." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent vertebral body mineralization
def: "A lack of bone mineralization of the vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic ischiopubic rami
def: "Underdevelopment of the ischiopubic ramus, which is comprised of the inferior pubic ramus and the inferior ramus of the ischium." [HPO:probinson]

name: High iliac wing
def: "Increased height of the wing (or ala) of the ilium (which is the large expanded portion which bounds the greater pelvis laterally)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Large iliac wing
def: "Increased size of the ilium ala." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cortical sclerosis of the iliac wing
def: "Increased density related to increased bone mass in the outermost layer (edge) of the iliac wing." [PMID:17404618]

name: Hypoplastic iliac wing
def: "Underdevelopment of the ilium ala." [HPO:probinson]

name: Flared iliac wing
def: "Widening of the ilium ala, that is of the wing of the ilium, combined with external rotation, leading to a flared appearance of the iliac wing." [HPO:probinson, PMID:28744080]

name: Dysplastic iliac wing
def: "A general term that describes a congenital defect in the iliac wing resulting from abnormal development." []

name: Narrow iliac wing
def: "Decreased width of the wing (or ala) of the ilium (which is the large expanded portion which bounds the greater pelvis laterally)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Iliac crest serration
def: "Irregularities of the iliac crest that produce the appearance of a lace border around it." [HPO:probinson]

name: Iliac horns
def: "Horn-like malformations of the iliac crests with symmetrical bilateral central posterior iliac processes. A characteristic finding in the Nail-Patella syndrome. Iliac horns are visible on X-ray and may be palpable, but are asymptomatic." [HPO:curators]

name: Short iliac bones
def: "Underdevelopment of the iliac bones." [PMID:29019756]

name: Hypoplastic iliac body
def: "Underdevelopment of the body of ilium." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior beaking of thoracic vertebrae
def: "Anterior tongue-like protrusions of thoracic vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior beaking of lower thoracic vertebrae
def: "Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the lower thoracic vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Small cervical vertebral bodies
def: "Reduced size of cervical vertebrae." [HPO:probinson]

name: Sclerotic vertebral endplates
def: "Sclerosis (increased density) affecting vertebral end plates." [HPO:curators]

name: Anterior wedging of T12
def: "An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T12 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior wedging of vertebral bodies
def: "An abnormality of the shape of vertebrae, such that they are wedge-shaped (narrow towards the back)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior wedging of L1
def: "An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L1 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior wedging of T11
def: "An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T11 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior wedging of L2
def: "An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L2 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Facet joint arthrosis
def: "Osteoarthritis of facet joints in the spine. Degeneration of cartilage in the facet joints results in bone rubbing on bone and reactive new bone formation visible on X-ray." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thoracic hemivertebrae
def: "Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the thoracic spine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lumbar hemivertebrae
def: "Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the lumbar spine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cervical hemivertebrae
def: "Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the cervical spine." []

name: Posterior scalloping of vertebral bodies
def: "An excessive concavity of the posterior surface of one or more vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Butterfly vertebrae
def: "A butterfly vertebra (sagittal cleft vertebra or anterior rachischisis) is a sagittal defect in the vertebral body caused by failure of fusion of the two lateral chondrification centers during embryogenesis. The name is based on the appearance of the two hemivertebrae emerging as butterfly wings from the central cleft on x-ray." [HPO:probinson, PMID:31448202, PMID:3693103]

name: Coronal cleft vertebrae
def: "Frontal schisis (cleft or cleavage) of vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior clefting of vertebral bodies
def: "Anterior schisis (cleft or cleavage) of vertebral bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lumbar platyspondyly
def: "A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance beween the vertebral endplates affecting the lumbar spine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thoracic platyspondyly
def: "A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance beween the vertebral endplates affecting the thoracic spine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Butterfly vertebral arch
def: "Butterfly vertebrae have a cleft through the body of the vertebrae and a funnel shape at the ends." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cleft vertebral arch
def: "A discontinuity of the vertebral arch, i.e., of the posterior part of a vertebra." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior rib cupping
def: "Wide, concave posterior rib end." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anterior rib cupping
def: "Wide, concave anterior rib end." [HPO:probinson]

name: Posterior rib fusion
def: "Complete or partial merging of the posterior part of adjacent ribs." [HPO:probinson]

name: Spatulate ribs
def: "Ribs that are increased in width and taper to the posterior ends." [HPO:probinson, PMID:20504305]

name: Posterior rib gap
def: "Radiolucent focal defect of the posterior portion of a rib shaft. The 'gaps' may lead to flail chest." [UToronto:bgallinger]

name: Enlargement of the costochondral junction
def: "Abnormally increased size of the costochondral junctions, which are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent testis
def: "Testis not palpable in the scrotum or inguinal canal." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23650202]

name: Clitoral hypertrophy
def: "Hypertrophy of the clitoris." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the ovary
def: "Aplasia, that is failure to develop, of the ovary." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ovarian serous cystadenoma
def: "A cystic tumor of the ovary, containing thin, clear, yellow serous fluid and varying amounts of solid tissue." [HPO:probinson, PMID:23766763]

name: Hemorrhagic ovarian cyst
def: "An abdominal mass formed by bleeding into a follicular ovarian cyst or corpus luteum cyst." [HPO:probinson, PMID:12928726]

name: Cervix cancer
def: "A tumor of the uterine cervix." []

name: Glomerulopathy
def: "Inflammatory or noninflammatory diseases affecting the glomeruli of the nephron." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Multiple glomerular cysts
def: "The presence of many cysts in the glomerulus of the kidney related to dilatation of the Bowman's capsule." [Eurenomics:fschaefer, PMID:20091054, PMID:20367310]

name: Renal juxtaglomerular cell hypertrophy/hyperplasia
def: "Increased number and size of the juxtaglomerular cells." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Glomerulomegaly
def: "Abnormally large size of glomeruli." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21115671, PMID:9402101]

name: Periglomerular fibrosis
def: "Circumferential fibrosis in the interstitium surrounding Bowman's capsule" [PMID:21204717, PMID:32866505]

name: Chronic tubulointerstitial nephritis
def: "Chronic inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules." [HPO:probinson]

name: Multilamellation of medullary peritubular capillary basement membranes
def: "Duplicated basement membranes of the peritubular capillaries located in the medulla of the kidney and arranged in multiple concentric layers." [KPMP:arosenberg]

name: Thickening of the tubular basement membrane
def: "Increase in thickness of the basement membrane of the tubulus of the kidney." [PMID:20142905]

name: Tubular basement membrane disintegration
def: "DIsruption and breaking up of the basement membrane of the tubules of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]

name: Tubular luminal dilatation
def: "Dilatation (expansion beyond the normal dimension) of the cavity (lumen) of tubules of the kidney. The tubular cross section displays an attenuated brush border (apical PAS positivity greater than 10 percent of the normal expected height, but unequivocally less than normal expected height), resulting in an apparent increase in the size of lumen." [KPMP:arosenberg, PMID:29537990]

name: Preductal coarctation of the aorta
def: "Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized proximal to the ductus arteriosus, i.e., to the preductal region of aortic arch." [DDD:dbrown]

name: Aortic isthmus hypoplasia
def: "A type of aortic arch hypoplasia whereby the isthmus (arch between the left subclavian and insertion of the patent ductus arteriosus/ligamentum arteriosum) has a diameter of less than 40% of the diameter of the ascending aorta." [PMID:27860551]

name: Vascular ring
def: "A developmental defect of the aortic arch system in which the trachea and esophagus are completely encircled by connected segments of the aortic arch and its branches. This occurs if the normal process of regression and persistence of the bilateral embryonic aortic arches fails." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dilatation of the sinus of Valsalva
def: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation of one of the anatomic dilations of the ascending aorta, which occurs just above the aortic valve." [UBERON_0003707]

name: Type IV atherosclerotic lesion
def: "In type IV atherosclerotic lesions a dense accumulation of extracellular lipid occupies an extensive but well-defined region of the intima. This type of extracellular lipid accumulation is known as the lipid core. A fibrous tissue increase is not a feature, and complications such as defects of the lesion surface and thrombosis are not present. The type IV lesion is also known as atheroma. Type IV is the first lesion considered advanced in this classification because of the severe intimal disorganization caused by the lipid core. The characteristic core appears to develop from an increase and the consequent confluence of the small isolated pools of extracellular lipid that characterize type III lesions. The increase in lipid is believed to result from continued insudation from the plasma. Type IV lesions, when they first appear in younger people, are found in the same locations as adaptive intimal thickenings of the eccentric type. Thus, atheroma is, at least initially, an eccentric lesion." [PMID:7648691]

name: Hepatic foam cells
def: "The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, in the liver." []

name: Foam cells with lamellar inclusion bodies
def: "The presence of foam cells that contain lamellar inclusion bodies." [HPO:probinson]

name: CNS foam cells
def: "The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, in the central nervous system." []

name: Coronary-pulmonary artery fistula
def: "A congenital malformation with abnormal connection between one of the coronary arteries and the pulmonary artery." [PMID:24605242]

name: Anomalous origin of left coronary artery from the pulmonary artery
def: "Left main coronary artery begins (branches off from) the pulmonary artery rather than as normal from the root of the aorta, above the left cusp of the aortic valve." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:probinson, PMID:27358682]

name: Elevated circulating dodecanoylcarnitine concentration
def: "Increased concentration of dodecanoylcarnitine in the blood circulation." []

name: Elevated circulating palmitoleylcarnitine concentration
def: "An elevated level of propionylcarnitine in the circulation. Propionylcarnitine is present in high abundance in the urine of patients with Methylmalonyl-CoA mutase (MUT) deficiency." []

name: Elevated circulating butyrylcarnitine concentration
def: "Increased concentration of O-butyrylcarnitine in the blood circulation." []

name: Elevated circulating propionylcarnitine concentration
def: "Increased concentration of propionylcarnitine in the blood circulation." []

name: Elevated circulating tetradecanoylcarnitine concentration
def: "Elevated circulating tetradecanoyl concentration." []

name: Circumoral cyanosis
def: "Persistent blue color of the skin that surrounds the mouth." [PMID:2797223]

name: Aplasia cutis congenita over posterior parietal area
Lid lag on downgaze
def: "Delayed descent of the upper eyelid on downgaze. Also described by some authors as von Graefe sign." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Eversion of lateral third of lower eyelids
Cicatricial ectropion
def: "An outward turning (eversion) or rotation of the eyelid margin (i.e., ectropion) caused by shortening or contraction of the anterior or middle lamellae related to scarring." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Cicatricial lagophthalmos
def: "A type of lagophthalmos that occurs following trauma or surgery." []

name: Nocturnal lagophthalmos
def: "The inability to close the eyelids during sleep." [PMID:16671223]

name: Hooded upper eyelid
def: "Upper eyelid partly covered by skin when eyes are open." []

name: Epicanthus inversus
def: "A fold of skin starting at or just below the medial aspect of the lower lid and arching upward to cover, extend in front of and lateral to the medial canthus." [PMID:19125427]

name: Lower eyelid retraction
def: "Inferior malposition of the lower eyelid margin without eyelid eversion." [HPO:probinson, PMID:10946945]

name: Upper eyelid entropion
def: "An inward turning (inversion) of the margin of the upper eyelid." [ORCID:0000-0003-0986-4123]

name: Ablepharon
def: "Absent eyelids." [PMID:19125427]

name: Cryptophthalmos
def: "Cryptophthalmos is a condition of total absence of eyelids and the skin of forehead is continuous with that of cheek, in which the eyeball is completely concealed by the skin, which is stretched over the orbital cavity." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125427]

name: Lacrimal duct atresia
def: "A developmental disorder of the lacrimal drainage system that most often affects the lacrimal ostium and resulting in non-opening of the nasolacrimal duct. It usually results from a non-canalization of the nasolacrimal duct." [HPO:probinson]

name: Malformed lacrimal duct
def: "Congenital malformation of the lacrimal duct associated with incomplete development of the bony nasolacrimal canal or craniofacial anomalies." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lacrimal duct aplasia
def: "A congenital defect resulting in absence of the lacrimal duct." [HPO:probinson]

name: Ectopic lacrimal punctum
def: "Positioning of a lacrimal punctum other than at the medial margins of the eyelid." [PMID:19125427]

name: Absent lacrimal punctum
def: "No identifiable superior and/or inferior lacrimal punctum." [PMID:19125427]

name: Hypoplasia of the lacrimal punctum
def: "Underdevelopment of the lacrimal puncta." [HPO:probinson]

name: Duplicated lacrimal punctum
def: "A congenital developmental anomaly characterized by the presence of two (instead of the normal one) lacrimal punctum on one or both sides of the face." [PMID:19875171]

name: Punctal stenosis
def: "Punctal stenosis is a condition in which the external opening of the lacrimal canaliculus is narrowed or occluded." [PMID:22848141]

name: Enlarged lacrimal glands
def: "Abnormally big lacrimal glands." [HPO:probinson]

name: Glossitis
def: "Inflammation of the tongue." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Bifid tongue
def: "Tongue with a median apical indentation or fork." [PMID:19125428]

name: Smooth tongue
def: "Glossy appearance of the entire tongue surface." [PMID:19125428]

name: Glossoptosis
def: "Posterior displacement of the tongue into the pharynx, i.e., a tongue that is mislocalised posteriorly." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125428]

name: Tongue atrophy
def: "Wasting of the tongue." [ORCID:0000-0001-5208-3432]

name: Lobulated tongue
def: "Multiple indentations and/or elevations on the edge and/or surface of the tongue producing an irregular surface contour." [PMID:19125428]

name: Geographic tongue
def: "An anomaly of the tongue characterized by loss (atrophy) of filiform papillae of the tongue, leaving areas of erythema (redness), surrounded by a serpiginous, white, hyperkeratotic border. The name geographic tongue refers to an appearance that is said to be similar to a map." [PMID:32119353]

name: Protruding tongue
def: "Tongue extending beyond the alveolar ridges or teeth at rest." [PMID:19125428]

name: Persistence of primary teeth
def: "Persistence of the primary teeth beyond the age by which they normally are shed and replaced by the permanent teeth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Carious teeth
def: "Caries is a multifactorial bacterial infection affecting the structure of the tooth. This term has been used to describe the presence of more than expected dental caries." [HPO:probinson]

name: Agenesis of canine
def: "Agenesis of canine tooth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dental crowding
def: "Changes in alignment of teeth in the dental arch" [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

name: Overjet
def: "An abnormal anteroposterior extension of the maxillary teeth beyond the plane of the mandibular teeth upon jaw closure." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Increased overbite
def: "Maxillary teeth cover the mandibular teeth when biting to an increased degree. The feature is defined as a vertical overlap of the maxillary incisors over the mandibular incisors that exceeds 2 mm." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:31468724]

name: Irregularly spaced teeth
def: "Irregular distribution of the teeth along the dental arch, i.e., and irregular spatial pattern of teeth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Alveolar bone loss around teeth
def: "A decrease in the amount of alveolar bone around the root of a tooth." []

name: Premature loss of permanent teeth
def: "Premature loss of the permanent teeth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Premature loss of primary teeth
def: "Loss of the primary (also known as deciduous) teeth before the usual age." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Hypoplasia of the primary teeth
def: "Developmental hypoplasia of the primary teeth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Widely spaced primary teeth
def: "Increased space between the primary teeth. Note this phenotype should be distinguished from increased space due purely to microdontia." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Microdontia of primary teeth
def: "Decreased size of the primary teeth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Abnormality of primary molar morphology
def: "An abnormality of morphology of primary molar." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Delayed eruption of primary teeth
def: "Delayed tooth eruption affecting the primary dentition." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Gingival cleft
def: "A fissure in the gingiva (gums), i.e., the mucosal tissue that lies over the mandible and maxilla." []

name: Gingival overgrowth
def: "Hyperplasia of the gingiva (that is, a thickening of the soft tissue overlying the alveolar ridge. The degree of thickening ranges from involvement of the interdental papillae alone to gingival overgrowth covering the entire tooth crown." [PMID:19125428]

name: Gingivitis
def: "Inflammation of the gingiva." [HPO:probinson]

name: Gingival recession
def: "The loss of gum tissue. The result is that gum tissue is recessed and its position on the tooth is lowered, exposing the roots of the teeth." []

name: White oral mucosal macule
def: "A small circumscribed whitish change in the color of the oral mucosa that is neither elevated nor depressed." [PMID:23762643]

name: Reticulate pigmentation of oral mucosa
def: "A net-like pattern of increased pigmentation of the oral cavity." [HPO:probinson]

name: Intra-oral hyperpigmentation
def: "Increased pigmentation, either focal or generalized, of the mucosa of the mouth." [PMID:19125428]

name: Oral melanotic macule
def: "Flat, distinct, discolored area of oral mucosal membrane less than 1 cm wide not associated with a change in the thickness or texture of the affected mucosal membrane. The lesions are small, solitary, well-circumscribed and often uniformly pigmented." [PMID:24034073, PMID:26538887]

name: Oral leukoplakia
def: "A thickened white patch on the oral mucosa that cannot be rubbed off." [HPO:probinson, PMID:17944749]

name: Triangular-shaped open mouth
def: "A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth, in which the upper lip is tented in a way that the opened mouth has the appearance of a triangle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Whistling appearance
def: "An abnormality of facial morphology characterized by a small mouth opening and constant contraction of the lips as if the patient were whistling." [HPO:probinson, PMID:856233]

name: Enlargement of parotid gland
def: "Increased size of the parotid gland." [DDD:jclayton-smith]

name: Parotitis
def: "Inflammation of the parotid gland." [HPO:probinson]

name: Aplasia of the parotid gland
def: "Absence of the parotid gland." [HPO:curators]

name: Thick lower lip vermilion
def: "Increased thickness of the lower lip, leading to a prominent appearance of the lower lip. The height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the midline is more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [HPO:curators, PMID:19125428]

name: Thin lower lip vermilion
def: "Height of the vermilion of the medial part of the lower lip more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Curved linear dimple below the lower lip
Everted lower lip vermilion
def: "An abnormal configuration of the lower lip such that it is turned outward i.e., everted, with the Inner aspect of the lower lip vermilion (normally opposing the teeth) being visible in a frontal view." [PMID:19125428]

name: Labial melanotic macule
def: "Flat, distinct, discolored area on the lip less than 1 cm wide not associated with a change in the thickness or texture." [PMID:24034073, PMID:26538887]

name: Thick upper lip vermilion
def: "Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Thin upper lip vermilion
def: "Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Everted upper lip vermilion
def: "Inner aspect of the upper lip vermilion (normally apposing the teeth) visible in a frontal view, i.e., the presence of an everted upper lip." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19125428]

name: Capillary malformation of the lip
def: "A vascular malformation located in the lip that is characterized by\nectatic papillary dermal capillaries and postcapillary venules in the upper reticular dermis." []

name: Short upper lip
def: "Decreased width of the upper lip." [HPO:probinson]

name: Long upper lip
def: "Increased width of the upper lip." [DDD:jhurst]

name: Angular cheilitis
def: "A type of inflammation of the lips involving one or both of the corners of the mouth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Velopharyngeal insufficiency
def: "Inability of velopharyngeal sphincter to sufficiently separate the nasal cavity from the oral cavity during speech." [DDD:jhurst]

name: High, narrow palate
def: "The presence of a high and narrow palate." [HPO:curators]

name: Short hard palate
def: "Distance between the labial point of the incisive papilla to the midline junction of the hard and soft palate more than 2 SD below the mean (objective) or apparently decreased length of the hard palate (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Torus palatinus
def: "A bony protrusion present on the midline of the hard palate." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Decreased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
def: "An abnormally reduced proportion of naive CD4 T cells relative to the total number of T cells." [PMID:22474485]

name: Decreased proportion of naive CD8 T cells
def: "An abnormally reduced proportion of naive CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells." [PMID:26700072]

name: Decreased proportion of class-switched memory B cells
def: "A reduction in the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased proportion of marginal zone B cells
def: "A reduction in the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells." [PMID:9802980]

name: T2 hypointense thalamus
def: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a diffuse hypointensity affecting the entire thalamus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal T2 hypointense thalamic lesion
def: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the thalamus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal T2 hyperintense thalamic lesion
def: "A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the thalamus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Decreased thalamic volume
def: "A reduction in the quantity of space occupied by the thalamus." [UToronto:htrang]

name: Dysgenesis of the basal ganglia
def: "Structural abnormality of the basal ganglia related to defective development." []

name: Large basal ganglia
def: "Increased size of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Neuronal loss in basal ganglia
def: "A reduction in the number of nerve cells in the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson, PMID:13729575]

name: Small basal ganglia
def: "Decreased size of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Symmetric lesions of the basal ganglia
Status cribrosum
def: "Diffusely widened perivascular spaces in the basal ganglia, affecting especially the corpus striatum. Status cribrosum is usually symmetrical, with the perivascular spaces showing CSF signal and without diffusion restriction. The word cribriform means sievelike, with multiple perforations." [HPO:probinson]

name: Basal ganglia necrosis
def: "Death of cells in the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cavitation of the basal ganglia
def: "The formation of small cavities in the tissue of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson, PMID:8516046]

name: Diffuse swelling of cerebral white matter
Reduced cerebral white matter volume
def: "An abnormally low volume of the white matter of the brain." []

name: White mater abnormalities in the posterior periventricular region
Frontoparietal cortical dysplasia
def: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the cortex of frontal lobe and the cortex of parietal lobe." [HPO:probinson]

name: Mild malformation of cortical development
def: "A malformation of cortical development characterized by mild abnormalities of the cortex: excessive heterotopic neurons in Layer 1 or microscopic neuronal clusters or excess of single neurons of normal morphology in deep white matter." [COST:neuromig, PMID:21219302]

name: Periventricular leukomalacia
def: "Periventricular leukomalacia is characterized by diffuse injury of deep cerebral white matter, accompanied in its most severe form by focal necrosis. The neuropathologic hallmarks of PVL are microglial activation and focal and diffuse periventricular depletion of premyelinating oligodendroglia." [PMID:16808630, PMID:18852342, PMID:28406931]

name: Small cerebellar cortex
def: "Reduced size of the cerebellar cortex." [RGD:gth]

name: Atrophy of the dentate nucleus
def: "Partial or complete wasting (loss) of dentate nucleus." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cerebellar vermis atrophy
def: "Wasting (atrophy) of the vermis of cerebellum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Disorganization of the anterior cerebellar vermis
Loss of Purkinje cells in the cerebellar vermis
Dysgenesis of the cerebellar vermis
def: "Defective development of the vermis of cerebellum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Superior cerebellar dysplasia
def: "Abnormal morphological development of the superior part of the cerebellum." []

name: Diffuse cerebellar atrophy
def: "Diffuse unlocalised atrophy affecting the cerebellum." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Cerebellar cortical atrophy
def: "Atrophy (wasting) of the cerebellar cortex." [HPO:probinson]

name: Cerebellar Purkinje layer atrophy
def: "Atrophy of the cerebellum affecting primarily the Purkinje cell layer." [HPO:probinson]

name: Spinocerebellar atrophy
def: "Atrophy affecting the cerebellum and the spinocerebellar tracts of the spinal cord." [HPO:probinson]

name: Perisylvian predominant thick cortex pachygyria
def: "Pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm and a perisylvian predominant severity gradient. The severity gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Perisylvian predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe other the occipital lobes but also includes a rare perisylvian-predominant pachygyria and a temporal predominant pachygyria." [COST:neuromig, PMID:28440899]

name: Posterior predominant thick cortex pachygyria
def: "Pachygyria with cortical thickness above 10 mm with and a posterior predominant severety gradient. The severety gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Posterior predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe other the occipital lobes but also includes a rare perisylvian-predominant pachygyria and a temporal predominant pachygyria." [COST:neuromig, PMID:28440899]

name: Anterior predominant thick cortex pachygyria
def: "Pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm and an anterior predominant severity gradient. The severety gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Anterior predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe over the frontal and temporal lobes." [COST:neuromig]

name: Focal EEG discharges with secondary generalization
def: "Focal EEG discharges that secondarily spread to both hemispheres and can then be recorded over the entire scalp." [HPO:jalbers]

name: Hemihypsarrhythmia
def: "Hypsarrhythmia occurring in one hemisphere." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with generalized polyspikes
def: "EEG with repetitive generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with generalized sharp slow waves
def: "EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with burst suppression
def: "The burst suppression pattern in electroencephalography refers to a characteristic periodic pattern of low voltage (<10 microvolts) suppressed background and a relatively shorter pattern of higher amplitude slow, sharp, and spiking complexes." [HPO:probinson, PMID:22323592]

name: EEG with generalized spikes
def: "EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec." [HPO:jalbers]

name: Hypsarrhythmia
def: "Hypsarrhythmia is abnormal interictal high amplitude waves and a background of irregular spikes. There is continuous (during wakefulness), high-amplitude (>200 Hz), generalized polymorphic slowing with no organized background and multifocal spikes demonstrated by electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO:curators]

name: Severe generalized osteoporosis
def: "Severe degree of osteoporosis." [HPO:curators]

name: Poorly ossified cervical vertebrae
def: "Decreased ossification of the cervical vertebral bodies, i.e., of the Cervical vertebrae set." [HPO:probinson]

name: Absent in utero ossification of vertebral bodies
Hump-shaped mound of bone in central and posterior portions of vertebral endplate
Caudal interpedicular narrowing
def: "Narrowing (becoming gradually narrower) of the distance between vertebral pedicles that gets progressively more severe towards to caudal (lower) end of the vertebral column. Note that normally, the interpedicular distances get progressively wider as one proceeds down the spine." [HPO:probinson]

name: Thoracolumbar interpediculate narrowness
def: "A reduction of the distance between thoracolumbar vertebral pedicles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lower thoracic interpediculate narrowness
def: "A reduction of the distance between the lower thoracic vertebral pedicles." [HPO:probinson]

name: Enlarged vertebral pedicles
def: "Increased size of the vertebral pedicle." [HPO:probinson]

name: Streak ovary
def: "A developmental disorder characterized by the progressive loss of primordial germ cells in the developing ovaries of an embryo, leading to hypoplastic ovaries composed of wavy connective tissue with occasional clumps of granulosa cells, and frequently mesonephric or hilar cells." [HPO:probinson]

name: Glomerular subendothelial electron-dense deposits
def: "Electron dense deposits at the glomerular basement membrane," [Eurenomics:ewuehl, PMID:20301598, PMID:30085237]

name: IgA deposition in the glomerulus
def: "The presence of immunoglobulin A deposits in the glomerulus." [Eurenomics:ewuehl]

name: Glomerular subepithelial deposits
def: "Deposits located between the outer (epithelial) aspect of the glomerular basement membrane (GBM) and the visceral epithelial cell, with varying degrees of incorporation into the GBM. This feature may be associated with a prominent GBM reflecting an diffuse and relativly uniform increase in thickness (subjective estimate)." [PMID:30085237]

name: Mesangial Immune complex deposition
def: "Extracellular meangial accumulation of finely granular material corresponding to immunoglobulin and/or complement by immunofluorescence/immunohistochemistry; most typically electron-dense although this may decrease with resorption of the deposit." [KPMP:arosenberg]

name: Diffuse mesangial sclerosis
def: "Diffuse sclerosis of the mesangium, as manifestated by diffuse mesangial matrix expansion." [HPO:probinson]

name: Abnormal glomerular mesangial cellularity
def: "Abnormal number of its constituent cells of the mesangium of the glomerulus of the kidney." [KPMP:arosenberg]

name: Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis
def: "Segmental accumulation of scar tissue in individual (but not all) glomeruli." [Eurenomics:fschaefer, PMID:16164633]

name: Global glomerulosclerosis
def: "Obliteration of the glomerular capillary lumen by increased collagenous matrix, with or without hyalinosis or foam cells. Sclerosis involves 100% of the glomerular tuft. Relative to other patent glomeruli in the sample, glomerular size is preserved, or increased/decreased by no more than 50%." [Eurenomics:ewuehl, KPMP:arosenberg]

name: Podocyte foot process effacement
def: "An anomaly of podocyte morphology characterized by the loss of the interdigitating foot process pattern (generally called foot process effacement; FPE). The term FPE designates the loss of the usual interdigitating pattern of foot processes of neighboring podocytes, leading to relatively broad expanses of podocyte processes covering the glomerular basement membrane (GBM). It is widely viewed as a pathological derangement that is associated with leakage of macromolecules such as albumin through the glomerular filtration barrier." [PMID:23235479]

name: Left aortic arch with cervical origin of the right subclavian artery
Left aortic arch with retroesophageal right subclavian artery
def: "Aortic arch crosses the left mainstem bronchus. The first branch is the right carotid artery, the second branch is the left carotid artery, the third branch is the subclavian artery, the fourth branch is the right subclavian artery arising from the posteromedial aspect of the distal aortic arch and continuing posterior to the esophagus to the right hand side of the body." [DDD:dbrown]

name: Right aortic arch with mirror image branching
def: "The aortic arch crosses the right mainstem bronchus and not the left mainstem bronchus, but does not result in the creation of a vascular ring. The first branch is the left brachiocephalic artery which divides into the left carotid artery and left subclavian artery, the second branch is the right carotid artery, the third branch is the right subclavian artery." [DDD:dbrown, HPO:sdoelken]

name: Left superior vena cava draining to coronary sinus
def: "A persistent left superior vena cava (PLSVC) that drains into the right atrium via the coronary sinus. This is the case in 80-92% of cases of PLSVC and results in no hemodynamic consequence." [PMID:18847480]

name: Left superior vena cava draining directly to the left atrium
def: "A persistent left superior vena cava (PLSVC) that drains into the left atrium instead of the right atrium via the coronary sinus, resulting in a right to left sided shunt." [PMID:18847480]

name: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG4
def: "A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG4 can be measured." []

name: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG1
def: "A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood." []

name: Blepharophimosis
def: "A fixed reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids with short palpebral fissures." [PMID:19125427]

name: Narrow palpebral fissure
def: "Reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids." [HPO:probinson]

name: Short palpebral fissure
def: "Distance between the medial and lateral canthi is more than 2 SD below the mean for age (objective); or, apparently reduced length of the palpebral fissures." [PMID:19125427]

name: Long palpebral fissure
def: "Distance between medial and lateral canthi is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, apparently increased length of the palpebral fissures." [PMID:19125427]

name: Almond-shaped palpebral fissure
def: "A shape created by an acute downward arching of the upper eyelid and upward arching of the lower eyelid, toward the medial canthus, which gives the outline of the palpebral fissures the configuration of an almond. Thus, the maximum distance between the fissures is offset from, and medial to, the center point." [PMID:19125427]

name: Upslanted palpebral fissure
def: "The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, the inclination of the palpebral fissure is greater than typical for age." [PMID:19125427]

name: Downslanted palpebral fissures
def: "The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations below the mean." [PMID:19125427]

name: Hypoplasia of the lower eyelids
def: "Underdevelopment of the lower eyelid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lower eyelid coloboma
def: "A short discontinuity of the margin of the lower eyelid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Upper eyelid coloboma
def: "A short discontinuity of the margin of the upper eyelid." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lacrimal duct stenosis
def: "Narrowing of a tear duct (lacrimal duct)." [HPO:probinson]

name: Dacryocystocele
def: "A nasolacrimal duct obstruction presenting as a grey-blue cystic swelling just below the medial canthus. Believed to be a result of concomitant upper obstruction of the Rosenmuller valve and lower obstruction of the Hasner valve." [PMID:19205594, UToronto:chum]

name: Lacrimal gland hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the lacrimal gland." [HPO:probinson]

name: Lacrimal gland aplasia
def: "A congenital defect of development characterized by absence of the lacrimal gland." [HPO:probinson]

name: Microglossia
def: "Decreased length and width of the tongue." [PMID:19125428]

name: Aglossia
def: "Absence of the tongue owing to a developmental abnormality." [HPO:probinson]

name: Exaggerated median tongue furrow
def: "Increased depth of the median tongue furrow." [HPO:probinson]

name: Serrated incisors
def: "Incisor teeth with irregular edges said to resemble a saw." [ORCID:0000-0003-3475-564X, PMID:25439729]

name: Incisor macrodontia
def: "Increased size of the incisor tooth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Notched primary central incisor
def: "The presence of a V-shaped indentation (notch) in the primary central incisor." [HPO:probinson]

name: Supernumerary cusp
def: "Additional cusps of a dental crown." [PMID:31468724]

name: Conical incisor
def: "An abnormal conical morphology of the incisor tooth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Screwdriver-shaped incisors
def: "An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth in which the tooth is shaped like a screwdriver blade, i.e., having a rhomboid shape." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Supernumerary maxillary incisor
def: "The presence of a supernumerary, i.e., extra, maxillary incisor, either the primary maxillary incisor or the permanent maxillary incisor." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Solitary median maxillary central incisor
def: "A single maxillary central incisor positioned in the midline with morphological symmetry of the crown and bordered by lateral incisors." [PMID:19125428]

name: Agenesis of incisor
def: "Agenesis of incisor." [HPO:probinson]

name: Crowded maxillary incisors
def: "A type of dental misalignment with crowded central incisors, i.e., of maxillary secondary incisor, or of maxillary central primary incisor." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Natal tooth
def: "A tooth present at birth or erupting within the first month of life." [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

name: Delayed eruption of permanent teeth
def: "Delayed tooth eruption affecting the secondary dentition." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Failure of eruption of permanent teeth
def: "Lack of tooth eruption of the secondary dentition." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Multiple unerupted teeth
def: "The presence of multiple embedded tooth germs which have failed to erupt." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Impacted tooth
def: "A tooth that has not erupted because of local impediments (overcrowding or fibrous gum overgrowth)." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Erythrodontia
def: "Reddish, brown opalescent discoloration of teeth in normal light." [PMID:21731282]

name: Pulp calcification
def: "Pulp calcifications may appear as punctate calcifications, irregular, roughly spherical mineralized masses in any part of the pulp. It may occur isolated or associated to calcifications elsewhere such as the carotid arteries and kidneys. The diagnosis pulp calcifications can be established using radiological studies." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:31468724]

name: Pulp obliteration
def: "Mineralized substance filling the entire dental pulp space." [PMID:162890, PMID:31468724]

name: Taurodontia
def: "Increased volume of dental pulp of permanent molar characterized by a crown body-root ratio equal or larger than 1:1 or an elongated pulp chambers and apical displacement of the bifurcation or trifurcation of the roots." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:31468724]

name: Hypoplasia of the tooth germ
def: "Developmental hypoplasia of the tooth germ, i.e., of the structure that forms in odontogenesis that will develop into a tooth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Abnormal size of the dental root
Fused teeth
def: "The union of two separately developing tooth germs typically leading to one less tooth than normal in the affected dental arch." [PMID:18167487]

name: Generalized microdontia
def: "A generalized form of microdontia." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Mulberry molar
def: "Mulberry molars are irregular teeth generally affecting the first molars and are characterized by a grossly deformed crown imitating, as the name implies, the surface of a mulberry." [HPO:19179952]

name: Abnormality of permanent molar morphology
def: "An abnormality of morphology of permanent molar." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Anterior open-bite malocclusion
def: "Anterior open bite is a malocclusion characterized by a gap between the anterior teeth (incisors), that is, by a deficiency in the normal vertical overlap between antagonist incisal edges when the posterior teeth are in occlusion." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:27615261]

name: Agenesis of mandibular premolar
def: "Agenesis of mandibular premolar." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Agenesis of permanent molar
def: "Agenesis of secondary molar tooth." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Mesiodens
def: "A supernumerary tooth in the midline between the maxillary central incisors." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:18262485, PMID:31468724]

name: Agenesis of permanent teeth
def: "A congenital defect characterized by the absence of one or more permanent teeth, including oligodontia, hypodontia, and adontia of the of permanent teeth." [HPO:probinson]

name: Anodontia
def: "The absence of all teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:31468724]

name: Oligodontia
def: "The absence of six or more teeth from the normal series by a failure\nto develop." [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

name: Selective tooth agenesis
def: "Agenesis specifically affecting one of the classes incisor, premolar, or molar." [HPO:ibailleulforestier]

name: Hypodontia
def: "The absence of five or less teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop." [HPO:ibailleulforestier, PMID:31468724]

name: Cleft of alveolar ridge of maxilla
def: "A gap (cleft) affecting one of the alveolar ridges, which are the protuberances in the mouth that contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth. An alveolar cleft can affect all structures of the alveolar ridge, including the gingiva, other mucosa, periosteum, alveolar bone, and teeth." [HPO:mengelstad, HPO:probinson]

name: Median cleft lip and palate
def: "Cleft lip or palate affecting the midline region of the palate." [HPO:sdoelken]

name: Bilateral cleft palate
def: "Nonmidline cleft palate on the left and right sides." [HPO:probinson]

name: Bifid uvula
def: "Uvula separated into two parts most easily seen at the tip." [PMID:19125428]

name: Submucous cleft soft palate
def: "A cleft of the muscular (soft) portion of the palate that is covered by mucous membrane. Soft-palate submucous clefts are characterized by a midline deficiency or lack of muscle tissue." [HPO:probinson]

name: Submucous cleft hard palate
def: "Hard-palate submucous clefts are characterized by bony defects in the midline of the bony palate that are covered by the mucous membrane of the roof of the mouth. It may be possible to detect a submucous cleft hard palate upon palpation as a notch in the bony palate." [HPO:probinson, PMID:19779505]

name: Median cleft lip
def: "A type of cleft lip presenting as a midline (median) gap in the upper lip." [HPO:probinson]

name: Non-midline cleft lip
def: "Clefting of the upper lip affecting the lateral portions of the upper lip rather than the midline/median region." [HPO:probinson]

name: Incomplete cleft of the upper lip
def: "A subtle unilateral cleft of the upper lip, which may appear as a small indentation." [DDD:jclayton-smith]

name: Submucous cleft lip
def: "A cleft of the lip with overlying mucous membrane." [HPO:probinson]

name: Narrow philtrum
def: "Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the ridges of the philtrum." [PMID:19152422]

name: Hypoplastic philtrum
def: "Underdevelopment of the philtrum." [HPO:probinson]

name: Broad philtrum
def: "Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased distance between the ridges of the philtrum." [PMID:19152422]

name: Short philtrum
def: "Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

name: Smooth philtrum
def: "Flat skin surface, with no ridge formation in the central region of the upper lip between the nasal base and upper vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

name: Tented philtrum
def: "Prominence of a triangular soft tissue area of the philtrum with the apex to the columella." [PMID:19152422]

name: Long philtrum
def: "Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

name: Deep philtrum
def: "Accentuated, prominent philtral ridges giving rise to an exaggerated groove in the midline between the nasal base and upper vermillion border." [PMID:19152422]

name: U-Shaped upper lip vermilion
def: "Gentle upward curve of the upper lip vermilion such that the center is placed well superior to the commissures." [PMID:19125428]

name: Exaggerated cupid's bow
def: "More pronounced paramedian peaks and median notch of the Cupid's bow." [PMID:19125428]

name: Tented upper lip vermilion
def: "Triangular appearance of the oral aperture with the apex in the midpoint of the upper vermilion and the lower vermilion forming the base." [PMID:19125428]

name: Absent cupid's bow
def: "Lack of paramedian peaks and median notch of the upper lip vermilion." [PMID:19125428]

name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the uvula
def: "Underdevelopment or absence of the uvula." [HPO:curators]

name: Broad uvula
def: "Increased width of the uvula (subjective finding)." [PMID:19125428]

name: Long uvula
def: "Increased length of the uvula." [PMID:19125428]

name: Decreased proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells
def: "A reduced proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative." [PMID:22343568]

name: Decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
def: "An decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative." [PMID:15838378]

name: Increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
def: "An increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative." [PMID:20146720, PMID:22343568]

name: Increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
def: "An increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative." [PMID:15838378]

name: Globus pallidus hypointensity on susceptibility-weighted imaging
def: "Hypointence (dark) appearance of the globus pallidus inmagnetic resonance imaging using susceptibility weighted imaging (SWI)." []

name: Abnormal putamen morphology
def: "Any structural anomaly of the putamen, a brain nucleus which together with the caudate nucleus and fundus striati makes up the striatum." []

name: Striatal T2 hyperintensity
def: "Abnormally bright T2 signal from the striatum on brain magnetic resonance imaging." [PMID:27058447]

name: Abnormal caudate nucleus morphology
def: "Any structural abnormality of the caudate nucleus." [HPO:probinson]

name: T2 hypointense basal ganglia
def: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a diffuse hypointensity affecting all of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal T2 hyperintense basal ganglia lesion
def: "A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Focal T2 hypointense basal ganglia lesion
def: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the basal ganglia." [HPO:probinson]

name: Confluent hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
def: "Areas of brighter than expected MRI signal in the white matter of the brain whereby individual patches run together." [PMID:25636970]

name: Cerebral white matter hypoplasia
def: "Underdevelopment of the cerebral white matter." [HPO:probinson]

name: Hypoplastic anterior limbs of the internal capsule
def: "Underdevelopment of the frontal part (anterior crus or anterior limb) of the internal capsule." [PMID:32395406]

name: Multifocal hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
def: "An abnormal area of increased brightness (hyperintensity) that occurs in several distinct areas." []

name: Deep cerebral white matter hyperintensities
def: "Areas of brighter than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from locations distant from the ventricular system." [PMID:15576652]

name: Focal hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
def: "An abnormal area of increased brightness (hyperintensity) that is limited to one particular area." []

name: Focal hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
Dysplastic corpus callosum
def: "Dysplasia and dysgenesis of the corpus callosum are nonspecific descriptions that imply defective development of the corpus callosum. The term dysplasia is applied when the morphology of the corpus callosum is altered as a congenital trait. For instance, the corpus callosum may be hump-shaped, kinked, or a striped corpus callosum that lacks an anatomically distinct genu and splenium." [HPO:probinson, PMID:21263138]

name: Thin corpus callosum
def: "An abnormally thin corpus callous, due to atrophy, hypoplasia or agenesis. This term is intended to be used in situations where it is not known if thinning of the corpus callosum (for instance, as visualized by magnetic resonance tomography) is due to abnormal development (e.g. a leukodystrophy) or atrophy following normal development (e.g. neurodegeneration)." [ORCID:0000-0002-1735-8178]

name: Thick corpus callosum
def: "Increased vertical dimension of the corpus callosum. This feature can be visualized by sagittal sections on magnetic resonance tomography imaging of the brain." [KI:phemming, PMID:10029348]

name: Agenesis of the anterior commissure
def: "Absence of the anterior commissure." [UToronto:bgallinger]

name: Hypoplastic anterior commissure
def: "Underdevelopment of the anterior commissure." [UToronto:bgallinger]

name: Deep white matter hypodensities
def: "Multiple areas of darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the deep cerebral white matter." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16239634]

name: Periventricular white matter hypodensities
def: "Multiple areas of darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the cerebral white matter that surrounds the cerebral ventricles." [HPO:probinson, PMID:16239634]

name: Focal cortical dysplasia type II
def: "A type of focal cortical dysplasia that is characterized by disrupted cortical lamination and specific cytological abnormalities." [COST:neuromig, PMID:21219302]

name: Focal cortical dysplasia type I
def: "A type of focal cortical dysplasia that is characterized by abnormal cortical layering." [COST:neuromig, PMID:21219302]

name: Punctate periventricular T2 hyperintense foci
def: "Multiple pointlike areas of high T2 signal observed upon magnetic resonance imaging of the periventricular cerebral white matter." []

name: Chiari type I malformation
def: "Arnold-Chiari type I malformation refers to a relatively mild degree of herniation of the posteroinferior region of the cerebellum (the cerebellar tonsils) into the cervical canal with little or no displacement of the fourth ventricle. It is characterized by one or both pointed (not rounded) cerebellar tonsils that project 5 mm below the foramen magnum, measured by a line drawn from the basion to the opisthion (McRae Line)" [HPO:curators, PMID:28613730]

name: EEG with periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges
def: "Periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges (PLEDs)are periodic, lateralized, and epileptiform. PLEDs show a relatively constant interval between discharges (0.5 to 3 seconds)." [HPO:probinson]

name: EEG with centrotemporal focal spike waves
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the centrotemporal region of the brain (also known as the central sulcus), i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:probinson]

name: EEG with central focal spikes
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the central region." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with parietal focal spike waves
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the parietal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with frontal focal spike waves
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the frontal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:jalbers]

name: Uni- and bilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
def: "Epileptiform discharges identified at multiple locations temporarily in both hemispheres and temporarily in one hemisphere." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with parietal focal spikes
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the parietal region." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with frontal focal spikes
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the frontal region." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with series of focal spikes
def: "Focal spikes occurring for several seconds." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with occipital focal spikes
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the occipital region." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with temporal focal spikes
def: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the temporal region." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with frontal sharp slow waves
def: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the frontal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with parietal sharp waves
def: "EEG with sharp waves in the parietal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with temporal sharp slow waves
def: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the temporal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (>3.5 Hz)
def: "The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (>3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO:probinson]

name: EEG with irregular generalized spike and wave complexes
def: "EEG shows spikes (<80 ms) and waves, which are recorded over the entire scalp and do not have a specific frequency." [HPO:jalbers]

name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (2.5-3.5 Hz)
def: "The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (2.5-3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO:probinson]

name: EEG with polyspike wave complexes
def: "The presence of complexes of repetitive spikes and waves in EEG." [HPO:jalbers]
